title: taco salad
directions: Cook and stir ground beef over medium heat until brown; drain. Stir in taco sauce and heat. Toss lettuce, green pepper, tomatoes, cheese and chips. Spoon hot mixture and salad dressing over lettuce mixture; toss. Serve immediately.

title: microwave salmon ring
directions: Cooking time 12 minutes.
Butter 6-cup micro-proof ring mold. Sprinkle with paprika and set aside.
Combine all ingredients except parsley in large bowl and blend well.
Turn into prepared mold, spreading evenly.
Cook (micro) on High, about 7 minutes. Unmold onto serving platter and garnish with parsley.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: beef brisket
directions: Place brisket in roasting pan.
Sprinkle with garlic salt. Rub chili sauce over meat and sprinkle with dry onion soup, spreading evenly.
Add enough water to cover bottom of pan. Place onion around roast.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 4 hours.
During last hour, add whole new potatoes and carrots.

title: rosemarie salad
directions: Boil noodles according to package directions, drain and cool. Drain fruit juices into saucepan.
Add eggs, flour, salt and sugar to juice.
Cook over medium-low heat until thick.
Combine noodles, fruit and sauce into a large serving bowl.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator if possible.
Just before serving, add Cool Whip.

title: antipasto salad
directions: Mix together salad dressing, milk, dressing mix and pasta in large shallow bowl.
Arrange remaining ingredients over pasta mixture; chill.

title: mexican salsa
directions: Dip tomatoes in boiling water for 30 to 60 seconds until skins loosen.
Dip in cold water and slip off skins.
Core and chop tomatoes.
In 6-quart saucepot, combine tomatoes, onions, chopped chilies, cilantro, vinegar, garlic and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat and simmer about 30 minutes to desired thickness, stirring occasionally.
Immediately fix hot pint jars with mixture, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.

title: mexican pizza
directions: Grease a 12-inch pizza pan; set aside.
Preheat oven to 375°. In a medium bowl, combine flour, salt and melted butter or margarine.
Stir in eggs, chilies, cottage cheese and Monterey Jack cheese.
Pour evenly into greased pan.
Place tomato slices on top. Bake 15 to 20 minutes in preheated oven until firm and lightly browned.
Cut into thin wedges.
Makes 16 to 18 appetizer servings.

title: pull-a-parts
directions: Melt butter in pan by itself. Combine all other ingredients in a mixture.
Cut each biscuit into 4 parts.
Dip each part into butter and roll in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in a Bundt pan.

title: whispers
directions: Chill stemmed glasses 30 minutes.
Combine all ingredients in electric blender; process until smooth.
Pour into glasses; serve immediately.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: crabmeat balls
directions: Combine first eight ingredients; stir well.
Stir in crabmeat and egg yolks.
Cover and chill one to two hours.
Shape into 1 inch balls; dredge balls in flour.
Pour oil to depth of 2 to 3 inches in heavy frypan.
Heat to 375°.
Fry balls in oil until golden.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve immediately.
Yield: 28 appetizer servings.

title: german meat balls
directions: Brown sauerkraut and tomatoes.
Make meat balls with ground beef and rice.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Melt margarine. Add onions, celery, green pepper and mushrooms.
Saute gently until tender.
Mix with remaining ingredients; pour into buttered casserole.
Garnish with slivered almonds, if desired.
Bake in a 425° oven for about 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy peach sherbet
directions: Peel and thinly slice peaches.
Sprinkle sugar on peaches. Add 2 cups milk and place in freezer in ice cube tray.
When partially frozen, whip with mixer for approximately 5 minutes. Replace in ice cube tray and freeze until firm.

title: roast beef
directions: Cover meat with the dried onion soup.
Wrap tightly in foil. Place in 300° oven for 5 hours.
Open and serve.

title: hearty farm soup
directions: Wash, sort and mix all three beans together.
Cover with water and soak 1 hour.
Drain; cover with water again.
Add ham hock and bring to boil.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender. In a skillet, brown sausage with apple, onion and celery.
Drain off fat.
Stir sausage mixture into beans.
Stir in brown sugar, mustard and tomatoes; add garlic powder, salt and pepper to taste. Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: taco salad
directions: Chop lettuce.
Add tomatoes, beans, cheese and olives.
Add chilled meat just before serving.

title: man traps
directions: Moisten with Miracle Whip and spread on small party rye bread and broil until melted.

title: family reunion potato salad
directions: Mix the potatoes, eggs, cottage cheese and onion and refrigerate overnight.
Add mayonnaise, celery seed, Durkee and salt.
Sprinkle paprika on top.

title: squash casserole #5
directions: Cook
squash
until
tender
and
mash.
Saute	onions, garlic and
peppers.
In	a
large
bowl, mix squash, pepper, onions, butter, eggs, grated cheese (save out some) and pecans (save
out some).
Mix
well and pour into a shallow buttered casserole.
Top with bread crumbs, cheese and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt; make a well in the dry ingredients. Add sugar, eggs and oil. Beat until well blended. Add apples, nuts, vanilla and spices. Bake in loaf pan at 350° until done. Cool and ice with confectioners sugar, margarine and juice and rind of 1 lemon.

title: chocolate chip-pudding cookies
directions: Beat butter until creamy.
Gradually add brown sugar, pudding mix and sugar (beating well).
Add eggs and vanilla, mixing well. Combine flour and soda and gradually add to butter mixture, mixing well.
Stir in chocolate morsels and pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for eight to ten minutes.

title: peach crisp
directions: Slice peaches and make 2 layers in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Mix ingredients and put on top of sliced peaches.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel truffles
directions: Melt chocolate with butter.
Beat in caramel.
Chill until firm and roll in chopped pecans.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Brown and cook beef roast or cubes in salt and water for 2 hours.
If using a pressure cooker, cook for 20 minutes to half an hour.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Combine remaining ingredients with onions and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: lentil soup(from india)
directions: Cool and blend small amount at a time.
Cook plain rice or yellow rice if obtainable.
Put small amount of rice in bowl; add soup.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute
onions
and
garlic in butter until light brown. Simmer broth for 12 minutes with onions, then pour into bowls. Add
bread and top with cheese.
Broil until golden brown and bubbling.

title: layer salad(use 9 x 12-inch pan)
directions: Rinse lettuce in ice water and dry.
Put the chopped lettuce over the bottom of the pan.
Layer celery, peppers, peas and onions over the lettuce.
Spread salad dressing over the ingredients.
Sprinkle sugar and Cheddar cheese on top.
Fry bacon crisp and put on top or use bacon chips.
Cover well with foil and refrigerate.
Can be made 24 hours before using.

title: wanda's vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all of the above except margarine and crackers and pour into a greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly. Mix butter with crackers. Add to top of casserole and brown slightly.

title: frozen margarita pie
directions: Combine pretzel crumbs, margarine and sugar; press on bottom and up sides of buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Chill in large bowl and combine sweetened condensed milk, ReaLime, tequila and Triple Sec.
Mix well.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into prepared crust. Freeze 4 hours, or until firm.
Garnish as desired.
Return leftovers to freezer.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: hot dog bun pie
directions: Butter oblong baking dish and layer buns, brown side up.
Pour melted butter over buns.
Mix eggs, sugar, milk and vanilla and pour over buns.
Bake at 300° until inserted knife comes out clean, about 30 minutes.

title: deep dish pie(peach or berry)
directions: Melt margarine in deep pie pan.
Mix remaining ingredients. Pour over melted margarine.
Add 1 quart fruit, sliced peaches or berries.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn meal rolls
directions: Pour milk over sugar, shortening and salt.
Add water; cool to lukewarm. Stir in 2 cups sifted flour. Add eggs and crumbled yeast; beat with rotary beater for 2 minutes.
Add corn meal.
Add remaining 3 1/4 to 4 cups flour as needed to make soft dough.
Let rise once, then make into individual dinner rolls.
Let rise again.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 12 to 18 rolls.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Place all these ingredients in a crock-pot and simmer all day.

title: oklahoma fried rice
directions: Put rice on to cook. Lightly grease a large frying pan. Saute onions. Put cooked ham in with onions. In small frying pan, scramble eggs until done. When eggs are cooked, mix them in with ham and chopped onions. When rice is done, mix rice in large frying pan with ham. Stir for few minutes and season with soy sauce to taste. Serve as a whole meal. Serves 4 easily.

title: apple blossom cake
directions: Cream together oil, sugar and eggs.
Add apples, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, vanilla, flour, salt and nuts. Mix well and bake in a greased, floured tube pan for about 1 hour and 15 minutes at 300° or 325°.

title: chicken bacon delight
directions: Debone chicken breasts. Wrap in bacon, securing with a toothpick.
Layer baking pan with dried beef. Mix soup and sour cream and pour over chicken and beef. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: diet delights - oatmeal oddities
directions: Add water to cover oatmeal and microwave 2 minutes.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: In double boiler, simmer all ingredients until onion is soft. Use as a dip for corn chips or put over tortillas.

title: miniature holiday cheesecakes
directions: Place wafers flat side down on bottom of each 18 foil baking cups.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, juice, peel and vanilla, mixing at medium speed with electric mixer until blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Pour into baking cups, filling each cup almost full.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cool before removing from pan.
Chill.
Top with preserves.
Yields 18 servings.

title: ham and pierogi lasagna
directions: Peel, cube, boil and mash potatoes.
Cube ham and add to potatoes.
Mix in half of grated Cheddar cheese.
Mix in milk, butter, salt and pepper.
Saute onions.
Prepare lasagna noodles. In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer potato and ham mix, onions and lasagna (in that order) until you get to the top and cover with lasagna noodles.
Sprinkle with remaining grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: yogurt
directions: Mix all ingredients and
put in warm place such as oven with a pilot light or styrofoam cooler or in the sun.
Let sit for six hours, then
put
in refrigerator.	Note:
set aside a cup of this as a starter for the next batch.

title: curried shrimp
directions: Melt butter in frypan over low heat; add flour and stir quickly.
Add curry powder and salt.
Very slowly add milk; stir hard to prevent lumping.
Add sherry and simmer slowly 5 minutes. Add shrimp.
Continue 2 minutes to heat shrimp in sauce and serve over rice.
Yield:
3 to 4 servings.

title: rhubarb salad
directions: Mix Jell-O in cooked rhubarb and then stir in nuts and pineapple. Let jell.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly, shortening, sugar, eggs, and flavoring. Blend in flour. Cover and chill at least one hour.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Roll dough 1/8 inch thick on lightly floured cloth covered board.
Cut into desired shapes.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes or until very light brown.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Place sugar, cocoa, milk, margarine and salt in a 2-quart saucepan; mix well.
Bring to a boil; boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter.
Mix well; stir in oatmeal and vanilla. Drop by spoonfuls on buttered cookie sheet or cookie sheet covered with waxed paper or aluminum foil.
Cool until firm in refrigerator.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Spread popcorn in a large shallow roasting pan.
In heavy 1 1/2 quart sauce pan, stir together sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Continue cooking, without stirring five minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and baking soda.
Pour mixture over popcorn.
Stir to coat well.
Bake at 250° uncovered one hour stirring occasionally.
Break apart when cooled and store in tightly covered container.
Makes one pound.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Cook raisins in tap water, simmer 15 minutes.
Add butter, sugar, cold water, salt, cloves, cinnamon, nutmeg and soda; mix well.
Add flour and pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Melt butter, stir in cracker crumbs.
Put a thin layer in bottom of buttered, shallow baking dish.
Cover with oysters, sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 of oyster liquor and cream.
Repeat and cover with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake 20 minutes at 425°.

title: no fail muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Add ingredients by layers in order listed.
Bake at 325° about 30 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix well and keep stored in tightly covered container.
Does not need refrigeration.

title: noodle and cheese casserole(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package; drain.
Combine noodles and remaining ingredients, except Cheddar cheese.
Mix lightly with a fork.
Place in buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Bake in moderate oven until bubbly and hot, about 25 minutes.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: bran bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients, set aside.
In small bowl beat milk, oil and egg just to blend.
If honey is used instead of sugar, add the honey to this wet mixture now.
If you used brown sugar, put the sugar in with the other dry ingredients.
Pour mixture over flour mixture, stir just until moistened.
Turn into 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in until it comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes, then cool on rack.
Serve sliced thin.
Wrap and store airtight.
Will keep 1 week wrapped, or in the freezer for up to 6 months.

title: vegetable, beef and biscuit casserole
directions: In 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, cook beef until browned.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup, water, mixed vegetables and Worcestershire.
Spoon into 3-quart baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: garlic chicken and sausage
directions: Place chicken in 1-quart casserole with lid.
Place garlic slices on top.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Top with sausage links. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
(Can microwave on High setting for 10 minutes, rotate dish 1/2 turn and cook an additional 10 minutes or until done.)

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into 3 unbaked pie shells. Cook at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: aunt doris' pickled garden delight
directions: Arrange grape leaf and a stalk of dill on bottom and top of a one-gallon glass jar.
Add alum.

title: apple spice muffins
directions: Combine milk with egg; stir in shortening.
Mix dry ingredients thoroughly; stir in apples and raisins.
Add liquid mixture and stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not overmix; batter should be lumpy.
Fill greased muffin pan two-thirds full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk in a heavy saucepan. Stir over medium heat. Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute and 40 seconds. Remove from heat and add peanut butter, vanilla and oats. Mix and drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper. Cool and remove.

title: shrimp-n-dip
directions: Mix ingredients well and serve on crackers.

title: truffles
directions: Heat 6 squares semi-sweet chocolate in heavy 2-quart saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly, until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter, then whipping cream.
Refrigerate, stirring frequently, just until thick enough to hold a figure, 10 to 15 minutes.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto foil-lined cookie sheet. Shape into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Freeze 30 minutes.

title: ham and string beans
directions: Roast ham until tender.
Remove meat from broth; add 1 onion and the parsley.
Boil about 5 minutes.
Next, add 2 pounds fresh or frozen string beans.
Boil about 20 minutes.
Then add the 4 medium potatoes, diced, and 1 small can of kidney beans.
Boil all of this until tender.

title: microwave sugarless apple pie
directions: Place frozen apple juice concentrate in 8-inch square glass baking dish.
Microwave on High until thawed.
Stir in tapioca, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Let stand until cool.
Spoon into pie shell.
Chill overnight.
May be served with whipped topping.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour into crusts.
Chill until firm (about 2 to 3 hours).

title: popeye's biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients.
Shape into biscuits.
Place on greased cookie sheet with sides touching.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: all american meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into two loaves.
Place on lightly greased rack of broiler pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Combine ketchup, horseradish, brown sugar and mustard.
Spoon over meat loaf and bake an additional 5 minutes.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: three bean balsamic salad
directions: In colander, combine kidney beans and garbanzo beans; rinse and drain.
Add drained green beans.
In large bowl, combine balsamic vinegar, water, mustard, oil, sugar, salt, pepper, onion, garlic, basil, thyme and tomato.
Add beans, tossing gently to coat.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator at least 4 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve with a slotted spoon.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mushroom and noodle casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms, onion, lemon juice and garlic powder in melted butter for 10 minutes.
Add the soup and bring to a boil. Now add the cooked noodles and reduce heat; simmer for about 10 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: vanilla extract
directions: Break vanilla beans into 1-inch pieces. Place beans in a jar. Pour liquor over beans and seal tightly. Let stand 2 to 3 months. Gently shake several times a week. Yield: 2 cups.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: golden squares
directions: Separate dough into 4 long rectangles.
Place crosswise in ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Press over bottom and 1-inch up sides.
Firmly press perforations to seal.
Bake and cool.
Combine cheese, sour cream, dill and garlic powder and spread over dough.
Cover and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
Cut in squares and garnish with veggies.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Combine crumb mixture with meat, eggs and next 4 ingredients.
Shape into balls, about 1-inch in diameter.
Place on a broiler pan.
Broil until brown, turning once.
Place meatballs into slow cooker.
Add brown gravy mixture and pepper.
Cook on low 4 hours.
Yield:
3 dozen meatballs.
May serve with rice.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Use a long Pyrex dish; grease or spray with Pam.
Crush chips to line bottom of dish.
Mix soups, broth, tomatoes and cheese in a saucepan.
Heat over medium-low heat until cheese melts.
Layer chips, chicken, soup mixture, chips, chicken, soup mixture, etc. in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.
Yields 6 servings.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Dip chicken breasts in egg, roll in flour and then roll in cheese (Parmesan).
Force cheese into all nooks and crannies. Place chicken in a frying pan and butter; brown on both sides (3 to 5 minutes a side).
Remove; place in a baking dish.
Cover chicken with chopped onion, spaghetti sauce, Mozzarella cheese and any leftover Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° until brown on top, about 30 minutes.

title: blueberry batter cake
directions: Line well-greased pan with berries.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add milk alternately with flour, baking powder and salt, which have been sifted together.
Pour the batter over the berries.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Sprinkle over top of cake.
Pour boiling water over all and bake in moderate oven (375°) for 1 hour.
Can use apple or fruit.

title: fruit punch
directions: Blend together orange, grapefruit, pineapple, lime and lemon juices.

Add sugar to taste. Freeze into fruit mold (may add to mold a few orange slices and maraschino cherries for decoration). When ready to serve, pour one bottle of ginger ale into punch bowl, then slide in fruit juice mold.
Carefully add remaining ginger ale.

title: giammaloo's special polish hamburgers
directions: Soak milk crackers in milk.
After they are well soaked, mix hamburg, egg, onion, salt and pepper.
Flatten into patties and fry until golden brown.
A great way to stretch your food budget. Good warm or cold.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Mix sugar, flour and milk together well.
Gently stir in blueberries into the mixture.

title: smoked salmon dip
directions: Drain salmon and mix all ingredients in a food processor. Scrape into a small bowl and serve with crackers or Melba toast. Can be used as a spread or a dip.

title: ma-maw's chocolate pie
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients until thick, then beat and add egg yolks.
Bake pie crust at 350°.
Whip egg whites.
Pour chocolate in pie shell.
Cover with egg whites and brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Bake in 2 loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: microwave creamy double decker fudge
directions: Line 8-inch square pan with foil.

In small microwave bowl, place peanut butter chips and 2/3 cup sweetened condensed milk. Microwave on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, stirring about 1 minute, until chips are melted and mixture is smooth when stirred.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Spread evenly into prepared pan.
In microwave-safe bowl, place remaining sweetened condensed milk and chocolate chips.
Repeat microwave procedure and stir in remaining 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Spread evenly on peanut butter layer.
Cover and chill until firm.
Cut in 1-inch squares.
Cover and store in refrigerator.

title: strawberry and chicken salad
directions: Toss romaine in large bowl with chicken cuts, oranges, strawberries and onion.
Sprinkle with almonds. Serve with dressing.
Makes 4 servings.
For added flavor, caramelize almonds.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows in microwave for 3 minutes at 70% power.
Stir.
Microwave 1 more minute at 70% power, if needed.
Stir in 6 to 8 cups of Rice Krispies.
Spread into greased 8 x 12-inch baking pan.
Cut into squares.

title: kraft banana mallow pie
directions: Combine coconut and oleo in skillet.
Cook over low heat, stirring frequently until coconut is toasted and golden brown. Press into 9-inch pie plate to form crust.
Chill.
Prepare mix as directed for pie filling on package, except use 1 3/4 cups milk. Cover with waxed paper.
Chill.
Fold in marshmallows and whipped cream.
Slice bananas into crust.
Pour filling over bananas. Chill.

title: apricot glazed pork over fettucini
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions. Combine nectar, broth, soy sauce, lemon juice, sesame oil, cornstarch and cinnamon in small bowl; mix until smooth. Dust pork with flour. Cook in vegetable oil in medium skillet until brown on all sides. Remove from skillet. Add nectar mixture to skillet, stirring to loosen brown bits. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; add pork and cook, covered, for 10 minutes or until pork is thoroughly cooked and sauce is thickened. Serve over hot fettucini.

title: cheese corn sticks
directions: In mixing bowl, stir together cornmeal mix, flour and garlic powder.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Stir in cheese.
Blend in enough milk to make a soft dough.

title: blueberry-peach coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Wash blueberries; drain peaches. Spread fruit on paper towels; set aside.
In a small bowl, combine sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Cut in margarine; set aside.
Mix muffin batter as directed on the label, except do not fold in the blueberries.
Spread batter in a greased 8-inch square pan.
Top with drained blueberries and peach slices.
Sprinkle cinnamon mixture over the fruit; bake for 25 minutes.

title: cornish hens with sweet and sour sauce
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a saucepan, combine butter, honey and mustard.
Salt and pepper the hens.
Place hens in a covered dish; pour sweet and sour sauce mixture over hens.
Bake approximately 1 hour and 20 minutes, basting every 15 to 20 minutes, until hens are tender and brown.

title: pistachio pudding pie
directions: Mix up pudding mix, milk and ice cream; blend well.
Pour pudding mixture into pie shell.
Let set in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: summer slush
directions: Boil together 4 cups of sugar and 6 cups water.
Add fruit mixture to sugar water and freeze in containers.
Seven-Up or orange juice can be poured over spoonfuls of this for refreshing drink or slush may be thawed slightly and served as a dessert.

title: cinnamon-applesauce salad
directions: Dissolve candy in boiling water.
Add gelatin; stir to dissolve.
Stir in applesauce; chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Pour into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: german potato salad
directions: Put the onion, celery, Miracle Whip, sugar and salt in a bowl and set aside.
Mix the bacon grease and vinegar in a blender. Stir in the eggs. Cook this mixture together until well done. Pour over diced potatoes. Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well. Chill.

title: vegetable chili
directions: Heat oil in a large saucepan or Dutch oven over medium heat. Saute onions for 2 or 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes, picante sauce, chili powder, cumin and salt.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes. Add beans, red pepper, zucchini and corn.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve with additional picante sauce, if desired.

title: colorado peach pie
directions: Add sugar and flour to peaches.
Combine a few drops of red food coloring and almond extract to syrup and add to peaches.
Put in unbaked crust and top with a lattice crust.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: pecan cookies
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat whites first, then beat yolks and whites together.
Cream softened shortening and sugars together, and eggs and vanilla.
Sift soda and and flour together; add to mixture. Mix in pecans; form into rolls, 1 1/2 inches in diameter and 12 to 14 inches long.
Makes about 4 rolls.
Wrap in wax paper.
Cut into slices and bake at 250° to 300° for about 10 minutes.
Can be frozen for later use.

title: mexican dip
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread bean dip on the bottom.
Next, layer the avocado dip.
Mix taco seasoning into the sour cream and add it next.
Sprinkle cheese, tomato and olives on top.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: pizza fudge
directions: Shred the cheese and mix together.
Beat eggs.
Mix in cheese and pour into greased 9x13-inch pan.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Season pork chops with salt and pepper.
Trim fat from chops and brown in 2 tablespoons oil.
Place in casserole dish.
Combine other ingredients and pour over chops, covering them.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: spritzkuchen(rich's cookies)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in the egg and flavoring.
Mix in the flour.
Pipe dough through cookie press into any shape desired, following cookie press directions.
Bake at 425°.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: cajun beef stew
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and sprinkle on beef cubes.
Brown in fat in Dutch oven.
Add next 4 ingredients and 1/2 cup water. Bring to a boil and simmer 2 hours.
Add carrots and raisins; simmer 30 minutes longer or until carrots are tender.
Serve with cornbread, brown rice and salad.
Makes 10 servings.

title: blu' bana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Cream together butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs; add vanilla.
Fold in mashed bananas and 2 cups of the flour.
Place 2 remaining cups of flour (less 2 tablespoons) in sifter and add allspice, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Sift and fold into mixture. Sprinkle blueberries with remaining flour.
Coat well and fold into the batter.

title: fiesta cheddar bake(yield: 8 servings)
directions: Combine in a large mixing bowl the rice, cottage cheese, milk, peppers, pimentos, salt and 1/2 cup of the Cheddar cheese.
Stir ingredients thoroughly until well mixed.

title: tomato ketchup
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bring to a boil, cook down until it reaches the consistency you prefer.

title: karen's corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and sugar.
Add corn meal.
Set aside.

title: nibblers (party mix)
directions: Mix seasonings with magarine and pour over 15 cups of mixed cereal, nuts, etc. in shallow pan.
Toss well until every piece is coated.
Bake one hour in a 300° oven and store in covered jars.

title: chocolate melt-away torte
directions: Mix the graham crackers, 2 tablespoons butter and 2 tablespoons sugar; pat into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Keep part of crumbs to cover top.
Cream 2 cups butter and the confectioners sugar. Continue creaming 4 eggs, one at a time.
Add the melted, cooled bitter chocolate, salt and mint flavoring, if desired.
Beat very good with electric beater on high speed, as beating increases volume.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Place extra crumbs on top.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.
Very rich. Can also be frozen.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° or in a slow cooker for all morning, or whenever.
Enjoy.

title: big mac sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Refrigerate well before serving.

title: fruit salad
directions: Blend marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Drain pineapple.
Add pineapple and pudding; blend.
Cover; refrigerate until serving time.

title: cheese crepes with sauce royale
directions: Place 3 tablespoons cottage cheese on each crepe.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Roll and place in a baking dish.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until heated through.
Meanwhile, prepare sauce.
In a 1-quart saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch; stir in orange juice.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Boil an additional 2 minutes.
Stir in butter.
Remove from heat.
Stir in strawberries.
Serve 2 crepes per serving with 1/4 cup strawberry sauce.

title: quick and fancy chicken
directions: Float chicken in milk/ egg mix.
Toss chicken in flour.
Float again in milk/egg mix.
Toss chicken in bread crumbs.
Put butter pads on top of chicken in pan.
Splash wine around pan so chicken can steam in wine.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake about 30 minutes, give or take.
Cut one breast in half to check inside.

title: joann's biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients gently; roll out to thickness of 1/2 to 1 inch.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Yields about 12.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: carrot souffl
directions: Scrape or peel carrots. Wash and cook in boiling water until tender. Drain carrots and mash with potato masher. Mix all other ingredients together in another bowl. Mix carrots and other ingredients together and then spoon into lightly greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. After baking, let cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar. Good served warm or cold.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Peel and chop apples and rinse in lemon juice.
Drain pineapple and save the juice.
Mix pineapple with marshmallows. Put in refrigerator.
In saucepan on medium heat, cook until thick the pineapple juice, sugar, flour, egg and vinegar.
Put in refrigerator; cool.
Combine Cool Whip with pineapple juice mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients. Refrigerate until serving time.

title: better than anything cake
directions: Prepare cake mix and bake in a 9 x 13-inch prepared pan at temperature recommended on box.
Bring crushed pineapple with juice and sugar to a boil.
Cool pineapple mixture completely. Prepare pudding as directed on box for pie filling; add vanilla and let it cool.
Stir pudding mixture while cooling.
When cake is done, remove from oven and make holes in top, using a fork. Spoon pineapple over cake and let cool.
Spread pudding mixture over cake.
Put Cool Whip on top of pudding.
Top with coconut and 1/2 cup pecans.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt
chocolate chips and paraffin wax in top of double boiler.
Dip peanut butter balls in chocolate and let cool.

title: seasoned cheese biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix Bisquick, whipping cream, sugar and grated sharp cheese until dough forms.
Turn dough onto cloth-covered surface well dusted with flour.
Gently roll in flour and shape into ball.
Knead 10 times.
Roll 1/2 inch thick. Cut with 2-inch cutter, dipped in flour.
Melt butter.
Dip each biscuit in the melted butter. Place biscuits on an ungreased cookie sheet. Sprinkle parsley and garlic powder onto each biscuit.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 12 biscuits.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well.
Chill.
Serve with chilled fruit (peaches, pineapple, cantaloupe, bananas, strawberries, pears, etc.).

title: mediterranean pasta
directions: Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Add linguine and cook for 8 to 10 minutes or until al dente; drain. Place bacon in a large, deep skillet. Cook over medium-high heat until evenly brown. Drain, crumble and set aside. Season chicken with salt. Stir chicken with bacon in a large skillet or saucepan. Add tomatoes and rosemary and simmer 20 minutes. Stir in rosemary, Feta cheese, olives and artichoke hearts and cook until heated through. Toss with fresh cooked pasta and serve warm. Garnish with extra Feta if desired.

title: pickling garlic
directions: Do not put salt in pickling recipe.
Use one cup of vinegar to one cup of water.
Use white vinegar for pickling.
Check label to be sure it says for pickling or the garlic will turn blue.
Only use white garlic.
Can be store in plastic jars with lids.
Cut garlic by soaking in water overnight.
Peelings cut off faster after soaking.
Pickled garlic takes the bad taste out of the garlic in about three weeks.
It can be used in all recipes and cuts down on the plaque build up in the blood vessels.
Can also be used in place of garlic pills that have oil in them.
Store in refrigerator.

title: praline sauce
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in heavy saucepan; mix well. Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly; boil 2 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and pecans.
Serve warm or at room temperature over ice cream.
Yields 2 cups.

title: banana cake
directions: Sift together the flour, salt and baking powder.
Beat remaining ingredients together until fluffy.
Add dry ingredients to batter; mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: quesadilla casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Oil a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.
On each tortilla, place one slide of each kind of cheese near edge. Top with a teaspoon each of onion and chilies.
Roll tortillas up; fold ends under to form a small package.
Place in casserole dish, overlapping.
Mash tomatoes in bowl with jalapeno sauce. Pour over quesadillas; garnish with green pepper rings.
Bake in a 425° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: funny face cookies
directions: Allow both crusts to stand at room temperature for approximately 15 to 20 minutes.
Heat oven to 450°.
In a small bowl, lightly beat egg white and almond extract; set aside.
Cut dough rounds from crusts with floured 2 1/2-inch round cookie cutter.
Place 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Brush with egg white mixture; sprinkle with sugar.
Make funny faces with candy.
Brush dough scraps with egg white mixture and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 450° for 5 to 7 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Grease 1 1/2-quart casserole. Slice potatoes thin. Sprinkle with onion and garlic. Sprinkle with flour, salt and pepper. Make about 3 layers. Dot top with butter. Cover all with milk. Cover and bake at 350° about 40 minutes (or until soft; as cools will thicken).

title: chili
directions: Brown ground meat and drain grease.
Add all ingredients together and cook for 2 to 3 hours.

title: herb oleo
directions: Blend in food processor a few seconds, mix well with soft oleo.
Spread on any type bread and grill or toast.
Great just as a snack.

title: three fruit punch
directions: Combine lemonade, pineapple and strawberries in blender. Blend until smooth.
Combine with ginger ale.
Pour over crushed ice.
Makes one gallon (32 servings).

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Do not follow cake mix directions.

title: baked cream cheese appetizer
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Unroll dough on lightly floured surface; press seams together to form 12 x 4-inch rectangle. Sprinkle top of cream cheese with half of dill; lightly press dill into cream cheese.
Place cream cheese, dill side down, in center of dough.
Sprinkle cream cheese with remaining dill.
Enclose cream cheese in dough by bringing sides of dough together, pressing edges to seal.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet; brush with egg yolk.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve with assorted crackers and apple slices.

title: toasty swiss cheese and onion snack
directions: Combine ingredients and spread onto cocktail rye bread. Broil for two to four minutes.
Great appetizer!! Few Ingredients!!

title: cheese stuffed zucchini
directions: Parboil the zucchini in boiling salted water for 5 minutes. Drain.
Cut in half lengthwise and scoop out the centers; finely chop.
Reserve the shells.

title: love cookies
directions: Mix together and bake in a warm oven.

title: shrimp in angel hair pasta casserole(makes 6 servings)
directions: With 1 tablespoon butter, grease a 12 x 8-inch pan.
Combine eggs, half and half, yogurt, Swiss cheese, Feta cheese, parsley, basil and oregano in medium bowl.
Mix well.
Spread 1/2 of the pasta on bottom of prepared pan.
Cover with salsa.
Add 1/2 of the shrimp.
Cover with remaining pasta.
Spread egg mixture over pasta and top with remaining shrimp.
Sprinkle Monterey Jack cheese over top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes or until bubbly. Let stand 10 minutes.
Garnish with snow peas and stuffed plum tomatoes.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend salad dressing, cake mix and eggs at low speed with electric mixer until moistened.
Add peel.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes (dough will be stiff).
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of dough, 2 inches apart, onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes (depending on oven) until lightly browned.
Cookies should still appear soft.
Cool for 1 minute on pan.
Remove to wire racks and cool completely.
Stir together frosting and juice until well blended.
Spread on cookies.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: good stuff
directions: Dip cookies in milk. Layer cookies in oblong pan and layer Cool Whip. Repeat with cookies and Cool Whip. Sprinkle chocolate beads on top. Keep in fridge.

title: jelly
directions: Boil juices and vinegar for 3 minutes.
Add sugar.
Boil for 15 minutes and seal in jars.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: *Or use pudding in the mix cake mix and 3 eggs; add 1/3 cup oil.

title: pecan crisps
directions: Combine sugar, butter, shortening, eggs and vanilla. Beat until light and fluffy. Add flour and baking soda. Beat at low speed until soft dough forms. Stir in pecans. Divide dough in half. Shape each half into a 2-inch log. Wrap in plastic wrap. Chill 2 to 3 hours or overnight. Cut into 1/4-inch slices. Bake at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: kevin's crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt butter, add shallots and bell peppers.
Saute until wilted or clear.
Add water, let it get hot.
Put crawfish tails with fat.
Squeeze the bag or rinse with a little water.
Add tomato sauce and the rest of the seasoning.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes.
Add cornstarch at this time (dissolve in cup of water). Cook until mixture thickens.
You can add more cornstarch if needed.
Simmer about 10 minutes more.
It's done!!!
Serve over rice.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: whipped creamy frosting
directions: Cook milk and flour together until thick.
Sit pan in cold water.
Beat sugar, butter, vanilla and Crisco until creamy.
When flour mixture is cold, combine with sugar and butter mixture. Beat for 3 minutes.

title: apple salad
directions: Put in bowl apples, celery, raisins, grapes and walnuts.
In a small cup, put in mayonnaise, milk and sugar.
Blend well, then pour over apple mixture.
Mix up well.
Refrigerate for awhile until chilled, then you can serve, about 1 hour.

title: pineapple upside-down muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt butter or margarine; add brown sugar, nuts and drained pineapple.
Spoon equal amounts into bottoms of greased muffin cups.
Put Bisquick, sugar and milk into a bowl; add flavoring and drop in unbeaten eggs.
Stir until well mixed but not smooth.
Spoon equal portions of batter over the pineapple mixture.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool before removing from pan.
These are delicious.

title: cheese dip
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Cube cheese. Combine all ingredients in a pretty ovenproof bowl.
Bake at 375° approximately 20 minutes.
Best served hot with crackers.

title: salmon burgers
directions: Melt butter or margarine in a heavy skillet.
Add chopped onion and cook over medium heat until tender.
Remove from heat and place in a mixing bowl.
Add 1/2 cup potato chips, egg, salt and salmon.
Mix well.
Shape mixture into six patties.
Coat with remaining potato chips.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients and fill freezer with homogenized milk.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburger with onion; drain grease.
Add corn and tomato soup.
Mash potatoes.
Take hamburger, mixed with corn and soup, and put into casserole dish (spray with Pam).
Put mashed potatoes on top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sprinkle salt into egg whites.
Beat until soft peaks.
Beat in sugar gradually.
Continue to beat until stiff, but not dry.
Add chocolate and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Place in preheated oven. Turn off heat.
Do not open oven door for 24 hours.
Makes 60 cookies.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the sugar, oleo and vanilla until light. Add eggs and beat.
Sift dry ingredients (except baking soda) which is added to the buttermilk.
Add alternately with the dry ingredients and milk.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough. Roll dough 1/4-inch and cut with cookie cutters.
Place on slightly greased cookie sheets. Bake at 375° until light brown on bottoms, about 10 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Combine together 3 tablespoons sugar and 3 tablespoons cinnamon; set aside.
Grease cookie sheet.
Mix dry ingredients except sugar.
Beat sugar and eggs.
Add rest of liquids and dry ingredients.
Roll into balls and roll in cinnamon sugar.
Bake at 375°.

title: bavarian jello
directions: Dissolve water and Jell-O; put in refrigerator to set.
When mixture has the appearance of cottage cheese or is starting to set, add to mixture 2 packages of Dream Whip that have been beaten stiff.
Return to refrigerator until it is set, probably 2 to 3 hours.

title: pamela's quick applesauce dessert
directions: Mix all the above ingredients together and enjoy.

title: poor man's stuffed cabbage
directions: Brown onion, beef, salt, pepper and rice.
Stir in cheese. In greased casserole, layer cabbage and meat mixture until all are gone.
Combine tomato sauce and water.
Pour over top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: oven stew
directions: Mix meat and vegetables.
Place in casserole dish.
Mix liquids and seasonings.
Spoon over meat.
Cover and bake at 250° for 5 hours.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix together well and place two heaping tablespoons
in a cup of boiling water.
Great for gifts.
Fill a mug with mix, wrap in colored plastic and tie at top with ribbon.

title: spinach salad dressing or dip
directions: Thoroughly rinse, drain and remove stems from spinach.
Place in blender (pack it in).
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover and blend until smooth (50 to 60 seconds).
Turn blender on and off. Can use this as a dressing for a salad or as a dip for fresh veggies.

title: christmas cauliflower
directions: In large saucepan, cook cauliflower in a small amount of water 6 to 7 minutes until crisp-tender; drain well. In medium saucepan, saute green pepper and mushrooms in butter 2 minutes. Add flour. Gradually stir in milk. Bring to a boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Stir in cheese until melted. Add pimientos and salt. Place half of cauliflower in a greased 2-quart baking dish. Top
with half of sauce. Repeat layers. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Put all ingredients in a pan and melt together over low heat. Dip pieces of apples or other fruit, or use over ice cream.

title: new twist potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets.
Cool, peel and cube.
Assemble with onion, mustard, salt, sugar, salad dressing and cheese.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Cut up bacon and place on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cornbread salad
directions: For body use canned or fresh peach halves.
For arms and legs use 4 small celery sticks.
For head use 1 large marshmallow.
For eyes, nose, shoes and buttons use raisins.
For mouth use 1/2 of cherry.
For hair use shredded Cheddar cheese.
For skirt use 1 fluffy leaf of lettuce.
You now have a Raggedy Ann Salad.

title: cottage cheese kugel(polish)
directions: Boil 12 ounce package noodles in salted water (according to directions on package).
Rinse well and drain.
Mix together until smooth the eggs, sugar, sour cream, cottage cheese and melted butter.
Pour mixture over noodles.
Fold in 1 can pineapple (crushed), but drain first.
Pour in large baking dish.
Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar over the top.
Bake in oven at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: pecan waffles
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Combine egg yolks, milk and oil; stir into dry ingredients.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into batter.
Sprinkle hot waffle iron with 2 tablespoons pecans.
Pour 1/4 to 1/3 cup of batter over pecans and bake according to manufacturer's directions until golden brown. Repeat with remaining pecans and batter.
Serve with syrup. Yield:
8 to 10 waffles (4 1/2-inches).

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: In large frypan, saute onion.
Add meat and remaining ingredients, except rice and tomato sauce.
Cover with lid and reduce heat.
After 10 minutes, add 1 can tomato sauce.
Stir well. Cook another 10 minutes with lid on pan.
Set aside.
Wash and cut peppers in half.
Remove membranes and seeds; parboil peppers (upside down) in salted water 10 minutes.

title: cabbage beef soup
directions: In Dutch oven, brown beef.
Add all remaining ingredients except parsley.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until done.
Add parsley.

title: cabbage soup
directions: In skillet, heat butter and saute onion until limp.
In a large saucepan, bring chicken broth to a boil.
Add sauteed onions, potatoes, carrots, cabbage, salt, thyme and pepper. Simmer, covered, until vegetables are tender, but not mushy, about 35 minutes.
Stir in cream; heat, but do not boil.
Serve hot. Yield: 6 servings.

title: bread and tomato soup
directions: In a large Dutch oven, stir together all ingredients.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 1 hour.
Remove the garlic cloves if desired and ladle into bowls.

title: chicken breasts and dressing
directions: Put chicken breasts in 9 x 12-inch shallow pan.
Top each piece of chicken with 1/2 slice of Swiss cheese.
Dilute soup with 1/2 cup water and pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing with margarine and sprinkle over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook carrots 5 minutes.
Mix tomatoes with sugar, tapioca and seasonings.
Heat and pour over vegetables that have been layered in casserole.
Cover with buttered crumbs.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Mix in eggs and vanilla. Combine flour, baking powder and salt in separate bowl.
Then add to other mixture.
Mix well.
Roll into a ball and chill.
Roll out and cut out.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken and cut into cubes. Place in a large bowl and add all but cheese and French fried onions. Mix well and transfer to 13 x 9 x 2 baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese and French fried onions. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 16 servings.

title: ed's sourdough starter
directions: Mix water
and
flour
to make a smooth mixture.
Place mixture in a glass jar or crock-pot.
Let it stand, uncovered, in warm place
for 18 to 24 hours (until bubbles form).
Store in glass
jar
in
fridge.
Replace
used
starter
with equal amounts of flour and water.

title: tutti fruitti nut cookies
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add salt, cinnamon, 1 1/2 cups of flour, and soda.
Mix well.
Mix dates, pineapple and cherries in 1/2 cup flour.
Add this mixture and nuts to dough.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: apple cheese jello
directions: Dissolve red hots in boiling water.
Add lemon jello and stir until dissolved.
Add cold water.
Add applesauce, celery and pecans or walnuts.
Mix and pour 1/2 of the liquid in a square dish to congeal.

title: bacon cheesy potatoes
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish sprayed with cooking spray, layer sliced potatoes (overlapping). Salt and pepper each layer.

title: poached salmon a la dishwasher
directions: You won't believe how good this is.
It comes out perfect every time.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Heat water, oleo and cocoa to boiling.
Add flour and sugar. Add buttermilk, soda, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet-sour spareribs
directions: Parboil ribs for 15 minutes in just enough water to cover ribs. Drain and cool.
Rub ribs with Hawaiian salt.
Marinate 1/2 hour in white wine, soy sauce, ginger and garlic.
Saute ribs in oil until golden brown.
Remove to platter.
Cook the 1/2 cup water, pineapple juice, brown sugar, white sugar and cornstarch until slightly thick.
Add ribs and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve.

title: no peek beef roast
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place roast in shallow roasting pan. Place in oven and bake at 370° for 1 hour.
Turn off oven and leave beef in oven for 3 hours.
Do not open oven door.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add other ingredients.
Rinse out cans with water.
Put in casserole dish and cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with noodles and brown.

title: six layer dinner
directions: In a 2-quart casserole dish or cooker, layer carrots, potatoes, celery, ground beef, onion, tomatoes and pepper.
Add salt between each layer.
Cover dish.
Cook at 350° for 2 hours or on 275° for 1 1/2 hours in slow cooker until carrots are tender.

title: chocolate crinkle cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, then nuts.
Chill dough several hours or overnight. Form small balls and roll in sugar, flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: okra pickle
directions: Pack okra firmly in hot sterilized jars.
Put a garlic clove in each jar.
Pour boiling brine in jars and seal.
Process in boiling water bath at simmering temperature about 180° to 200° for 10 minutes.
Let ripen several weeks before opening.

title: tuna-chip hot dish
directions: Smash potato chips.
Mix soup and tuna.
Layer potato chips, then soup and chips, ending with a layer of chips.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: garden stuffing
directions: Heat butter.
Saute onion and celery.
Brown liver and mushrooms.
Toast bread cubes in skillet.
Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Add apple and seasonings.

title: pork chops and stuffing bake
directions: Prepare corn bread stuffing according to pkg. directions. Spoon stuffing across center of 3-qt. shallow baking dish.
Place pork chops on each side of stuffing.
Mix soup and milk.
Pour over chops.
Cover and bake at 400 degrees for 30 minutes or until done. Sprinkle with cheese.
Also delicious with cream of mushroom soup.

title: upside down pizza
directions: Brown beef with dry onion in 2 Tbsp oil.
When nicely browned, drain of excess oil.
Put meat in skillet, add spaghetti mix and tomato sauce and simmer for about 3 to 4 minutes.
Put meat on the bottom of 13x9 inch glass baking dish.
Spread on top of meat sour cream and mozzarella cheese.
Top with can of crescent rolls or biscuit dough.
Lay the rolls crosswise on the pan mixture, brush rolls with melted butter and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375°F for about 3 minutes.
Let cool for 10 minutes and cut into squares.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, soda, salt, sugar and caraway seed into a bowl.
Cut in the shortening until mixture resembles meal.
Make a well in center and pour in buttermilk. Add currants and mix lightly.
Turn out on a floured board and knead gently.
Shape into a ball and fit into a greased 8 or 9-inch round cake pan.
Cut loaf crosswise into quarters, about 2/3 way through dough with a sharp knife.
Brush top of loaf with melted butter and sprinkle with additional sugar.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat well for 3 minutes. Pour into a well greased and floured tube pan. Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 300°.

title: diet snickers bar
directions: In a medium bowl, mix all of the ingredients together.
Make sure the banana is mixed thoroughly with the other ingredients. Roll into a log shape or into balls and place in freezer for 30 minutes.

title: salsa
directions: Chop tomatoes, onions, cabbage and cilantro into small pieces. Combine everything; let sit in refrigerator 1 hour or more. Serve with chips.

title: jello torte
directions: Prepare a graham cracker crust and press into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan, reserving a little of crumb mixture for the top of the torte.

title: bob's special cole slaw
directions: Rough cut cabbage into bite size pieces.
Dice onions, peppers and celery.
Grate carrots.
In a separate bowl, stir together Miracle Whip, vinegar, sugar and pepper.
Pour over cabbage mixture and mix thoroughly.
Place in refrigerator (covered) the night before serving.
Serves 30.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 10-inch pan.
Mix well and make 3 holes in mixture.
In one put 1 teaspoon vanilla, in one put 6 tablespoons salad oil and in one put 1 tablespoon vinegar.
Over this pour 1 cup water.
Mix well and bake at 300° until done, about 30 minutes.

title: rave reviews coconut cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Stir in coconut and walnuts.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool in pans 15 minutes.
Remove and frost.

title: hot fruit casserole
directions: Drain off all juice and alternate fruit in layers in large casserole dish ending with apple rings on top.

title: oven baked donuts
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients and add to liquid mixture and mix until smooth.
Divide batter equally between 12 Pam-sprayed (not paper-lined) muffin or cupcake wells.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately, as you remove from oven, coat top of each with a drizzle of warmed canned frosting or melted margarine and dust in granulated or powdered sugar.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Combine tomatoes, onion and seasonings; simmer 10 minutes and strain.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons oil; stir in flour. Add next 6 ingredients.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly. Set aside.
In skillet, dip tortillas briefly in small amount of hot oil until limp, but not crisp.
Drain.
Spoon 1/4 cup Chicken Filling on each; roll up.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Pour tomato mixture over all.
Bake, covered, at 350° about 15 minutes.
Uncover; bake until heated through, about 15 minutes. Top with cheese and bake until cheese melts.
Top with olives. Makes 6 servings.

title: carrot raisin salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: mountain dew salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water and add Mountain Dew and juice drained from pineapple; chill until it begins to thicken. Cook pudding according to package instructions and cool.
Mix Jell-O, lemon pudding and Cool Whip together.
Add drained pineapple and marshmallows.
Pour into a large bowl and chill.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Pound out chicken breasts and cut into strips.
Mix bread crumbs and cheese.
Dip chicken pieces in butter, then in crumb mixture.
Put in Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Do not turn.
May freeze or refrigerate before or after baking. Good hot or cold.

title: berry cobbler
directions: Melt butter in an 8 x 8-inch dish.
Mix sugar, flour, milk and baking powder together.
Pour mixture into dish over margarine or butter.
Add berries on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: creme de menthe pie
directions: Crunch cookies in blender.
Melt butter.
Mix together in a pie plate and pat down to form a crust.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Mix altogether and chill.
Serve with green and red apple wedges.

title: anise-whole wheat bread
directions: Combine yeast and warm water in a 2-cup liquid measuring cup. Let stand 5 minutes.
Combine yeast mixture, whole what flour, 1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour, salt, butter and honey in a large mixing bowl.
Beat at low speed with an electric mixer until blended; beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Stir in remaining 1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour.

title: polish cabbage soup
directions: Cook onion in butter until soft; don't brown.
Add remaining ingredients and cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours on low heat.

title: grammy mason's butter cookies
directions: Mix all together, except red and green sprinkles.
Roll out very thin.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Decorate with red and green sprinkles.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Add buttermilk, lemon extract, salt, lemon juice and beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell. Sprinkle top with grated lemon rind.
Bake at 425° until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Stuff the mushrooms and broil for 10 minutes.

title: chicago style coney dog sauce
directions: Mix ingredients.
Makes enough sauce for 6 pounds of hamburger meat.
Brown meat with 6 small onions.
Drain.
Mix with sauce. May be frozen.
Serve on hot dogs with mustard and onions or as Sloppy Joes.

title: turtle cake
directions: Fix cake mix according to box directions.
Pour half batter in long pan and bake 15 minutes at 350°.
In a double boiler melt butter, Pet milk and caramels.
Pour over baked cake.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and pecans over caramel.
Pour rest of batter over chips and pecans.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: torte
directions: Bake in loaf pan at 350° for about 50 minutes.
Can add grated lemon rind if use lemon or vanilla.
If you double the recipe, bake in a tube pan at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix butter and vanilla with mixer until creamy.
Add powdered sugar, a little at a time. Add peanut butter and mix well.
Shape into small balls.
(Put into freezer before dipping.)
Melt 1 pound of morsels and 1 block of paraffin wax in double boiler and dip each ball.
Easy if you use a toothpick for dipping.

title: 6 layer dinner
directions: In a greased baking pan: slice potatoes, add salt, pepper and dabs of butter.
Add sliced carrots.
Sprinkle with rice.
Layer chopped onion.
Fry ground round just until no longer pink and place on top of onions.
Mix soup and water and pour over the top. Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: grape-nut pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Set pan in larger pan.
Add water to larger pan.
Bake at 350° until solid.

title: strawberry cream squares
directions: Stir together pretzels, sugar and margarine.
Press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese with Miracle Whip and juice.
Fold in Cool Whip and spread over crust. Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Stir in frozen strawberries until strawberries separate.
Spoon over cream cheese layer.
Chill until set.

title: zucchini rice with sausage
directions: Brown sausage in a large skillet.
Pour off fat.
Push sausage to one side of skillet.
Add rice, zucchini slices and onions. Cook and stir until slightly browned over medium heat.
Stir in tomatoes, water, mustard and garlic salt.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Stir in cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Serve hot.

title: suzie steak
directions: Brown steak.
Place in casserole.
Prepare gravy from drippings.
Pour over steak.
Place bell pepper rings, onion and lemon on top.
Pour catsup over steak.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°. Place potatoes on top.
Bake 25 minutes longer.
Makes 4 servings.

title: rainbow finger jello
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 pan lightly with mayonnaise. Boil 1 1/4 cups of water.
Add Eagle Brand milk. Dissolve Knox gelatine in 1/2 cup of tap water. Combine Eagle Brand mixture and gelatin mixture. Set aside.

title: texas hash
directions: Saute onions and pepper until yellow.
Fry beef until brown. Stir all ingredients together.
Cover and cook for 1 hour. Uncover last 15 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.
My family loves this meal.

title: famous candy bars(tastes like baby ruth)
directions: In a saucepan, mix sugars and corn syrup over low heat.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Add peanut butter and stir well.
In a large mixing bowl, stir together cornflakes and salted peanuts. Add sugar-syrup mixture.
Press firmly in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over top.
When cool, cut into squares or bars.
Great church picnic dessert!

title: lime sweet pickles
directions: Dissolve lime thoroughly in water before adding cucumbers. Let stand 24 hours, stirring occasionally.
Take out and wash 4 times in clear water.
Let stand in clear, cold water for 3 hours. Drain.
Mix the vinegar, sugar, salt, pickling spices, celery seed and mustard seed (put spices in a bag).
Mix well and pour this mixture over cold cucumbers.
Let set overnight.

title: popcorn caramel crunch
directions: In a large greased bowl, combine the first 4 ingredients; set aside. In a large saucepan, combine sugar, butter, corn syrup and water. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until a candy thermometer reads 280° to 290° (soft-crack stage).

title: miniature ham rolls
directions: Slice rolls lengthwise through center.
Put ham and cheese on bottom.
Put roll top back on.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over top.
Cover with foil and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage pineapple slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients, tossing with mayonnaise until well coated.
Serve in lettuce-lined bowl.
Garnish with apple wedges.

title: sauerkraut casserole(this casserole sounds awful, but tastes so good!)
directions: In a large skillet, brown hamburger and drain grease.
Add remaining ingredients and cook on simmer 10 minutes.
Serve on buns or bread.
Serves 6.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat all ingredients in a large bowl on low speed for 30 seconds.
Beat on medium for 45 seconds. Pour into loaf pans.
Bake until firm to the touch on top (50-60 minutes).
Cool for 10 minutes.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and spread in square cake pan.

title: cranberry fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple real good.
Chop walnuts.
Put cranberries in bowl; add pineapple, apples, bananas, marshmallows and nuts.
Mix together with Cool Whip.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Chop onion and place in skillet with hamburger.
Fry until almost done, then add Spanish rice, beans and tomato sauce.
When done, place in a casserole dish and sprinkle cheese on it.
Cook at 350° until cheese melts.
Serves 6.

title: scotch shortbread cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pat into thick cookies and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip together cream cheese, peanut butter and 1/2 box powdered sugar.
Add Dream Whip.
Pour into large prepared graham cracker crust; sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: chicken in light sauce
directions: In a small bowl, combine tomato sauce, yogurt and 1 cup of water.
Mix well and set aside.
Put garlic and ginger into blender along with 2 tablespoons of water.
Blend into a smooth paste. Divide leg into thigh and drumstick.
Quarter breast.
Remove skin. Heat oil in a heavy-bottomed 10 to 12-inch casserole-type pot over medium-high heat.
Fry chicken to a golden brown.
Put cinnamon, bay leaves, cardamom, cloves and red pepper into the same oil used to fry chicken.
Stir once.
Now pour in the paste from the blender (keep face averted) and add turmeric.
Stir and fry about a minute. Now put in chicken, tomato sauce mixture, salt, pepper and lemon juice.
Bring to a boil.
Cover; lower heat and simmer gently, 20 to 25 minutes, turning chicken gently.

title: gingerbread(low cholesterol)
directions: Sift first 7 ingredients together in a medium bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine water, molasses and corn oil and stir well.
Add to flour mixture, beating at medium speed of electric mixer until smooth.
Spoon into 8-inch square pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Top servings with the applesauce.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Butter a 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole. To cook chicken, simmer in 4 cups of water for about 1 hour. Drain off chicken broth.
Debone cooked chicken and cut into bite-sized pieces.
Combine soup, salt, pepper and paprika. Set aside.
Arrange chicken pieces in bottom of casserole.
Cover with broccoli pieces, then cover with soup.
Sprinkle top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: portabella mushroom sandwich
directions: Sprinkle olive oil with garlic on mushrooms and marinate 1 hour or longer. Grill mushroom fins up for 20 minutes at 375°, hot grill. Saute onion and green pepper with butter until cooked. Chop meat and add to sauteed vegetables to heat through. Once tender, put on top of grilled mushrooms and add cheese of your choice. Melt on grill or under broiler. Put mushrooms on grilled buns.

title: bar cookie crust
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with cooking spray.

title: cannellini bean and asparagus soup
directions: Cut asparagus into 1/2 inch pieces, discarding white ends and any tough parts.
Set aside.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Grease sides of a 9-inch spring pan lightly with Crisco oil. Smash cookies into crumbs.
Mix with melted butter and spread evenly in bottom of pan.
In a large bowl mix cream cheese with milk until smooth.
Add 1/2 cup chocolate chips and mix with a spoon; pour into pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup chocolate chips on top. Bake at 300° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Stick a toothpick in cake, if it is clean, cake is done.
If toothpick is not clean, let bake a little longer.
Let stand 30 minutes to cool.
Pull side of pan off and chill.

title: glazed pecans or walnuts
directions: Combine and boil approximately 3 minutes, stirring constantly. Spread on wax paper until cool.

title: chicken rosamarina noodle hot dish
directions: Cook rosamarina noodles 10 minutes and blanch.
Saute celery, green pepper and onion.
Dice chicken and add all other ingredients.
Put in casserole.
Let stand overnight.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour.
Take cover off during the last 1/2 hour.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Put butter on top before baking.
Bake at 350°.

title: country mustard chicken and pasta
directions: In plastic bag, combine flour, pepper and chicken.
Shake to coat.
In a large skillet, brown chicken in 2 tablespoons of butter.
Remove chicken to heated platter; keep warm.
Add remaining 1 tablespoon of butter to skillet.
Saute onion and garlic until soft.
Stir in cream, mustard and cheese.
Add chicken; keep warm.
Toss hot pasta with 2 tablespoons of parsley. Place on serving platter; top with chicken.
Sprinkle remaining tablespoon of parsley over chicken.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, raisins, onions and crumbled bacon slices (or bacon bits) together well.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and lemon juice together well.
Pour over broccoli mixture; mix well.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Mix butter and sugar; add egg yolk, one at a time.
Add lemon rind, juice, flour and milk.
Beat egg whites and fold in.
Bake in 450° oven for 10 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fresh veggie and dip tray
directions: Arrange vegetables on tray.
Place veggie dip, peanut butter and cheese spread in separate bowls.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Chop up broccoli, saving some of the small buds and flowers for later use.
Saute broccoli in butter with onions and green pepper. Sprinkle with the flour; stir.
Add to soup stock, with bay leaf, parsley, thyme and peppercorns.
Cook for 30 minutes and puree the mixture in a blender.
Add nutmeg, strain the soup and return to pan.
Add egg yolk and milk or cream and pour into hot soup.

title: dixie's chocolate chip brownies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and eggs in mixing bowl.
Add melted margarine and flour; mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased baking pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sweet 'n sour chicken
directions: Sauce:
Mix pineapple juice, ginger, red wine, vinegar, brown sugar, cornstarch and water; set aside.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Sprinkle dry rice in dish, then onion soup mix. Add cup of water and a couple blobs of butter.
Layer chicken on top. Season.
Pour cream soup and milk over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered, then uncover and brown chicken.

title: bachelor nuggets
directions: Pick up box of frozen chicken nuggets at Winn Dixie; take home.
Place desired number of nuggets on top of paper towel on well-used microwave plate.
Make sure no chunks are left on plate from last use; but the paper towel helps.
Follow directions on box. Put unused nuggets back in freezer because they will spoil.

title: old fashion custard
directions: Combine eggs, vanilla and salt.
Add scalded milk slowly.
Line pie pan with pastry.
Pour filling and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Heat oven to 300°.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes, until a knife comes out clean.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a medium bowl.
Let set in refrigerator for about 1 hour before serving.

title: chinese wedding cake
directions: Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.

title: orange smoothee
directions: Combine orange juice, milk, sugar, vanilla, 1 cup water and 10 ice cubes in blender.
Process until smooth.
Serve immediately. Yields 6 servings.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix together very softened cream cheese with powdered sugar. Mix together French vanilla instant pudding with milk.
Add pudding mixture to cream cheese mixture, then add La Creme.
Put in flowerpot.
Crush Oreos and add layer to top of flowerpot.
Stick in plastic plant or flower, etc. to decorate.

title: honey chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Use 1 to 2 teaspoons olive oil in frying pan.
Fry until no pink is present.
Pour off oil.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 2 hours.
(If sauce gets too thick, add more juice.)
Stir occasionally.
You add chunks of pineapple at the end.
Serve with rice and fruit salad.
This is a very delicious dish!

title: taco dip
directions: Brown ground beef; melt cheese.
Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Heat 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Serve with chips (tortilla chips).

title: gumbo pot pie
directions: Bring chicken, 2 quarts water, quartered onion and bay leaves to a boil in a Dutch oven.
Cover, reduce heat, and simmer 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
While chicken is cooking, peel and devein shrimp; refrigerate.
Remove chicken; reserve 1 1/2 cups broth, and discard onion and bay leaves.
Let chicken cool.
Skin, bone, and coarsely chop chicken.

title: pita bread(diabetic recipe)
directions: Dissolve yeast, sugar, salt and liquid shortening in warm water.
Add 3 cups of the flour; stir to mix well.
(Dough should be fairly stiff; if not, add more flour.)
Turn out onto floured surface; knead in remaining flour.
Form into 15 1/2-inch tube. Cut into 15 slices.
Pat to make circles about 6 inches in diameter.
Lay on lightly greased baking pans.
Cover; allow to rise until almost doubled, about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Bake at 475° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until lightly golden brown, puffed and hollow.
These freeze well.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Fill pie plate with sliced apples.
In bowl, mix butter, sugar, egg and flour.
Spoon mixture over apples.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pie pan.
Put fruit or coconut on bottom of pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into pan.
Bake 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: peanut brittle
directions: You will need a candy thermometer.
Boil sugar, water and syrup until it threads.
Add butter and nuts.
Cook slowly to 300°, stirring constantly.
Add soda and vanilla.
Pour onto well buttered pan.
When cold, break into pieces.

title: oatmeal krispies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugars until fluffy. Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Add next 4 ingredients and mix until well blended.
Stir in next 4 ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until lightly browned.

title: hamburger cheese bake
directions: Mix in baking dish and spread.
Add meat mixture.
Sprinkle some grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: mulled new england punch(makes three 8 ounce servings.)
directions: In a medium saucepan, place water, cinnamon sticks and cloves. Bring to a boil over high heat; reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Add tea bags.
Remove from heat, cover and let stand for 5 minutes.
Remove spices and tea bags and discard. Stir in apple juice, cranberry juice and honey.
Heat over medium heat.
Pour into cups and garnish with apple rings, if desired.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Add egg and blend until creamy.
Add soda dissolved in vinegar.
Add vanilla.
Then add flour gradually to make a stiff batter.
Roll very thin.
Cut out and bake in moderate oven until brown.

title: christmas jello(sugar-free)
directions: Dissolve lime Jell-O in 1 cup hot water.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Pour into square glass dish.
Chill until partly set.

title: ginger-glazed carrots
directions: Boil carrots in a small amount of water.
When almost tender, drain off water and add the remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat until glazed and tender, stirring frequently.

title: grandma's rice pudding
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and cook over moderate heat until tender, about 20 minutes, stirring often.
Add next 2 ingredients and remove from heat.
Add to rice mixture.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients for 3 minutes.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Blend in Crisco; dissolve yeast in warm water.
Let yeast stand 5 minutes.
Then mix buttermilk and yeast to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Turn out on floured pastry sheet.
Roll out to desired thickness.
Cut out. Place on greased pan.
Place a pat of butter on top.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes.

title: olives
directions: Cover olives with cream cheese and roll in chopped nuts.
When ready to serve, cut in half.
Makes a nice Christmas dish:
red, green and white.

title: orange cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding, jello, eggs, oil and milk and beat for 3 minutes. Pour into three 9-inch layer pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Make sure cake is cold before frosting.

title: hamburger and shells
directions: Mix all ingredients all in one big pot.
It is good and easy to make.

title: horseradish sauce(to serve on broccoli)
directions: Combine ingredients.
Serve warm or cold.
To serve warm, heat in small saucepan to desired temperature, stirring frequently.

title: cracker jack i
directions: Boil sugar, oleo
and
syrup
5 minutes.
Add soda and pour over corn.
Bake 1 hour in 200° oven.

title: orange-pineapple cheese salad
directions: Mix pineapple and juice with sugar, bring to boil; add jello and stir to dissolve.
Add water, chill until begins to thicken.
Fold in cheese,
nuts and cool whip.
Keep tightly covered in refrigerator.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until it forms a hard ball in cool water or candy thermometer registers 250° to 260°.
Add unbleached peanuts and continue to cook until the mixture turns a golden brown or thermometer reaches 300°.
Remove from heat and stir in butter and salt.
Stir in the soda.
Pour onto a greased slab and pull out to a thin sheet.
Break into pieces when cool.

title: baked pineapple casserole
directions: Mix
flour
and sugar; add pineapple, juice and cheese. Pour into Pyrex (11 1/2 x 7-inch) dish.
Sprinkle with topping of Ritz crackers,
tossed
in
butter.
Bake
at
350° for 30 minutes.

title: kibbee
directions: Wash wheat and drain.
Add water to cover.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Remove excess water.
Mix wheat with meat, salt, onion and pepper.
Knead well.
Butter an 8 1/2 x 11-inch baking pan lightly.
Divide Kibbee in 2 parts.
Spread half on bottom of pan. Spread filling over Kibbee patting down lightly.
Smooth remaining Kibbee over filling and smooth with hand dipped in ice water.
Run a knife around edge and cut out into diamond shape. Pour butter set aside from filling over top of Kibbee.
Bake in a 450° oven for 30 minutes or until done.

title: banana-rum muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line 16 or 12 medium muffin cups with paper baking cups.
Mix baking mix, bananas, brown sugar, rum and egg (batter will be slightly lumpy).
Fill muffin cups about 1/2 full for 16 medium muffins or about 3/4 full for 12 muffins.
