Bake until light brown, about 15 minutes.

title: cherry-cranberry pie
directions: Combine all but butter and let stand 15 minutes.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Dot with butter and cover with pie dough. Bake at 400° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Put sliced onions and cucumbers into cold water with 1 tablespoon of salt.
Let stand 3 hours, then drain.
Heat vinegar, sugar and spices to boiling.
Add drained pickles.
Heat through and can.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Use the steel blade of your food processor to mince the onion. Add the cheese and shrimp; continue to process until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and process until smooth.
Remove and chill. Serve with Pepperidge Farm fish crackers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, place 3 cups boned chicken (can use boiled chicken).
Spread out to cover bottom.
Mix cream of mushroom soup, cream of chicken soup and water.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
In a saucepan, melt butter or oleo and water.
Pour over Pepperidge Farm cornbread stuffing.
Mix lightly with a fork. Spread over chicken and soup mixture.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 30 minutes.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Place chicken between 2 pieces of plastic wrap.
Pound chicken to 1/2 inch thickness.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper; coat with flour.
In large skillet brown chicken in 3 tablespoons butter over medium heat, about 5 minutes or until lightly golden. Remove from skillet and keep warm.
Add remaining butter to skillet and cook garlic and mushrooms until tender.
Return chicken to pan; add wine and lemon juice.
Simmer for 7 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally until sauce slightly thickens.
Top with parsley.

title: nacho cheese soup
directions: In 3 quart saucepan, combine potatoes, corn, tomatoes and water.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 15 - 18 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
Add milk, cheese, and tabasco sauce.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Makes 2 quarts, serves 6.

title: mounds candy
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Shape into balls.
Melt 12 ounce bag chocolate chips over double boiler with 1/8 stick paraffin.
Dip balls.
Place on wax paper to set.
Keep chilled.

title: diet gelatin salad
directions: Add dry orange Jell-O to Cool Whip. Then add cottage cheese and drained Mandarin oranges. Top with chopped pecans (optional). Let set in refrigerator for 15 to 30 minutes, then serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until slightly less than tender.
Salt to taste. Arrange in casserole.
Combine next 3 ingredients and pour over casserole.
Top with Ritz.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: awesome dip
directions: Mix cheese, mayonnaise, chilies, half of olives, garlic powder and half of green onions together.
Add several drops of Tabasco sauce to taste.
Pour into 9 inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Let sit for a couple of minutes.
Sprinkle remaining olives, green onions and tomato on top.
Serve with tortilla or corn chips.

title: easy broccoli stir-fry
directions: In a large skillet, melt oleo. Add meat and saute until brown. Remove and drain. Saute Rice-A-Roni according to package directions. Stir in 2 cups water, onion, garlic, ginger and season packet.
Boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 8 minutes. Stir in meat, broccoli and pepper. Cover and simmer 5 to 7 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.

title: pineapple-carrot bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine the flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
In another bowl, beat eggs; add carrots, vegetable oil, pineapple, nuts and vanilla.
Stir into dry ingredients just until moistened.
Spoon into 2 greased and floured (8 x 4 x 2-inch) loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes, and test for doneness.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.
Cool completely.

title: chocolate chip pancakes
directions: In a bowl, beat eggs together with a fork.
Add sour cream, flour, salt, sugar, baking soda and chocolate chips.
Pour about 1/4 cup of batter for each pancake on hot, lightly greased griddle or frying pan.
Cook until pancakes are bubbly on top.
Turn and cook until golden brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together when they get to room temperature. Shape into ball and roll in crushed nuts, if desired.

title: hungry boy's casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Stir in pork and beans, catsup, water, salt and garlic salt until well blended.
Reserve 1 cup of beans and meat mixture.
Return casserole to oven for 10 minutes while preparing biscuits. Arrange biscuits without centers on casserole.
Spoon reserved mixture in hole of each biscuit.
Top with biscuit holes.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: chocolate no bake cookies
directions: Bring your sugar, cocoa, milk, butter and syrup to a boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Then add the vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal. Mix well.
Spoon out (small spoonfuls) onto wax paper.
Let cool, then enjoy.

title: kahlua
directions: Pour boiling water over sugar and instant coffee.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add brandy and vodka and mix well.
Pour into large bottle; add vanilla bean.
Seal or cork tightly.
Age 30 days.
Shake bottle every 2 to 3 days.

title: shrimp or crab dip
directions: On plate spread softened cream cheese. Spread cocktail sauce over cream cheese. Layer crap meat evenly over sauce. Layer shrimp evenly over crab meat. Chill for 1 hour. Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
(Up to this point, can be done the day before needed.)
When ready to bake, top with crushed potato chips.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Makes approximately 12 servings.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook ground beef.
Add next 7 ingredients; cook until almost tender.
Add frozen vegetables, potato and noodles; cook until all are tender.
Leftover soup makes excellent Manhattan Clam Chowder by simply adding minced clams.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs; set aside.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Combine both mixtures.
Add bananas and nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Combine blueberries, sugar, and flour in a medium bowl. Toss lightly to coat the berries. Pour into bottom pie crust. Dot with butter. Top with the second circle of dough. Trim and flute the edges of the crust. Cut 5 or 6 small slits in top crust to allow steam to escape during baking. Bake for 10 minutes at 450 degrees, then lower the temperature to 350 degrees and continue baking for about 30 minutes. If the edges of the crust seem to be browning too quickly, cover them with aluminum foil the last 10 to 15 minutes of baking. Allow to cool completely before slicing.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Sprinkle half of graham crackers over bottom of pan.
Mix butter and sugar together, then add eggs, one at a time, beating until fluffy.
Pour over cracker crumbs, then add pineapple and Cool Whip.
Then sprinkle rest of graham crackers on top of Cool Whip.
Chill for 12 hours.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and conf. sugar together until crumbly.
Save 2 tbsp for top.
(Optional).

title: hot sauce(salsa)
directions: Put tomatoes in blender (chop) for 2 seconds.
Put in 4-quart pan.
Add all other ingredients, excluding onions.
Simmer 1 hour. Take off heat and add onions.
Refrigerate.

title: quick rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, butter and flour. Stir.
Refrigerate overnight.
Drop by teaspoonful.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Let cheese soften.
Chop beef and add to cheese.
Add all other ingredients.
Form into 2 balls.
Refrigerate for several hours.
Makes 2 medium balls.

title: parmesan pasta salad
directions: In a large skillet heat oil over medium heat.
Add broccoli, scallions, basil and salt.
Toss and stir until broccoli is tender-crisp, about 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Toss with pasta, Parmesan cheese and tomatoes.
Chill well, then serve.

title: baked coated broccoli
directions: Thaw frozen broccoli under running cold water just enough to separate.
Moisten broccoli with mixture of oil and water; shake off excess.
Empty seasoning and coating mix into plastic bag. Shake broccoli, a few at a time, in the bag until evenly coated. Place in ungreased, shallow baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, pumpkin and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and cinnamon. Add to pumpkin mixture and blend well. Add nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Ice with powdered sugar frosting when cool.

title: cranberry orange torte
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Gradually beat in sugar and vanilla.
Fold in flour and baking powder.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Line 2 (9-inch) cake pans with foil, greased. Spread batter in pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from pans by lifting foil.
Cool.

title: mini hot dogs
directions: Cut hot dogs into 3 pieces each.
Wrap bacon around each piece and use toothpicks to hold bacon.
Layer hot dogs in crock-pot. Sprinkle brown sugar on each layer.
Cook on high 1 hour, then turn on low for 2 to 3 hours.
Serve hot as finger food.
Leave toothpicks in hot dogs.

title: out-of-this-world cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Stir in coconut.
Combine graham cracker crumbs and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk to the cream mixture.
Stir in pineapple and nuts.
Turn mixture into a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken divan
directions: To make sauce, combine soup, mayonnaise, oleo, lemon juice and curry powder. Place broccoli in bottom of casserole dish.
Layer chicken on top of broccoli. Pour sauce on top.
Add cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening (margarine) and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, pumpkin and water.
Sift together dry ingredients and spices. Add to pumpkin mixture.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour; or pour into 4 greased 3 1/2 x 7 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: aid society cake
directions: Stew the raisins in 2 cups of water for 15 minutes.
Cool. Add 1 cup of cold water, the shortening, sugar and spices.
Mix well.
Add flour and baking soda.
Pour batter into a large angel food cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: easy french dressing
directions: Put all in blender and mix well.
Keeps well in jar in refrigerator.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine the above ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Pour the mixture into the unbaked pastry shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a knife can be inserted and it comes out clean.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Combine corn, 1/4 cup butter, milk and salt.
Bring to simmer. Cook until corn is tender.
Then blend in egg, crumbs, onions and brown sugar.

title: kraig's kukumber krunch
directions: Peel cucumbers, slice and put in bowl.
Add half and half. Add vinegar and sugar.
Add a dash of salt and pepper.
Slice onion and add.
Mix well and cover.
Place in refrigerator 2 hours.
Mix again and serve.

title: chocolate 'n' oat bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In large bowl, combine flour, oats, sugar and margarine; mix well.
Reserving 1/2 cup oat mixture, press remainder on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crust. Sprinkle with nuts and chocolate chips.
Top with remaining oat mixture; press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Makes 36 bars.

title: 5 cup fruit salad
directions: Cut oranges into small chunks.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Mix all ingredients in casserole dish and chill overnight. Can be frozen.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice zucchini in large casserole dish.
Add butter and water. Layer sliced tomatoes over squash.
Salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle 2 cups cheese over tomatoes.
Cover with herb stuffing mix.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp or chicken curry(microwave)
directions: Arrange chicken in pan.
Cover and microwave at 100% power for 20 to 25 minutes.
Melt butter at 100% power for 1 minute.
Saute onion, celery and curry powder in melted butter 2 to 3 minutes at 100% power.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Cook at 70% power for 1 minute or until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Stir in chicken broth and milk.
Microwave at 70% power for 3 to 5 minutes, until boiling.
Stir every 2 minutes.
Add chopped apple.
Add chicken and lemon juice.
Microwave at 70% power for 2 to 4 minutes. Serve over rice with condiments such as chopped tomatoes, raisins, coconut, pineapple chunks, chopped hard cooked eggs and French fried onion rings.
Serves 8.

title: fig preserves cake
directions: Sift flour, cornstarch and spices in a large mixing bowl.
Pour in buttermilk and beat well.
Stir in figs, nuts and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake in loaf pan or Bundt pan at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in refrigerator.
The longer this sets the better it tastes.

title: cheese cupcakes
directions: Put wafers on bottom of 12 cupcake papers.
Beat together cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Put mixture (2/3 full) on top of wafers.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
When cool, put pie filling on top.
Refrigerate until serving.
Makes 12.

title: ham ball
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; form into a ball on serving dish. Chill.
Blend cream cheese and milk; frost ball with mixture. Keep chilled.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix stuffing and milk.
Then add remaining ingredients together and make into balls. Spray Pyrex dish with Pam and place balls in dish.

title: calamondin bread
directions: Wash calamondins (about 12), cut into halves, seed and puree in blender. Put puree in large bowl and add sugar, walnuts, eggs, milk, oil, salt, raisins, cloves, ginger and cinnamon. Mix until well blended with electric mixer, about 4 minutes. Add flour and baking powder all at once and mix only until blended. Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 350° about 75 minutes or until loaf tests done. Cool in pan for 10 to 15 minutes and turn out on cake rack to cool.

title: nutty banana bread
directions: Combine flours, sugar, baking powder, salt and pecans in a large bowl; mix well.
In a medium bowl, combine oil and eggs; mix well.
Add bananas to egg mixture; mix well.
Add banana mixture to dry mixture.
Mix only until smooth.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Remove from pans when cool.

title: potato soup for two
directions: Barely cover potatoes, onion and celery with water.
Cook until tender.
Mash with potato masher.
Add milk, butter, salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with chopped parsley.

title: swiss enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken in a pot with 4 cups of water.
Once tender, shred chicken and discard bones. Save broth.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix first four ingredients together until creamy. Layer in a deep dish wafers, bananas and pudding mixture, topping with wafers. Serve chilled.

title: macaroni and ground beef
directions: In a skillet, brown the macaroni with butter.
Then add water and cook until tender.
In another skillet, brown the ground beef and add all other ingredients.
When macaroni is tender, add to the rest of the ingredients.
Serve with cheese.

title: old-fashion chocolate pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Put vegetables in pot with some water and steam until cooked. Add more water, tomatoes and bouillon; simmer 1 hour.
Good and lo-cal.

title: cranberry-pear chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Remove from pan. Cook onion until soft. Add pears, cranberries, cinnamon and ginger.
Stir well to combine.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: quick and easy chicken
directions: Coat chicken lightly with margarine, then coat with cornflakes.
Roll chicken loosely in aluminum foil; place on cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven until done (roughly 30 to 45 minutes).

title: marinated antelope roast
directions: Wash the meat in water with a little vinegar added.
Soak if bloody.
Sprinkle on flavored tenderizer salt.
Puncture deeply into roast with fork to let it penetrate. Tenderizer salt should stand an hour before roasting.
Pour over a can of onion soup. Roast until done.
Add pepper and more salt to taste.

title: teriyaki steak
directions: Sprinkle meat with tenderizer, following label directions. Cut round steaks in 12 medium pieces.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Marinate in refrigerator for 12 to 14 hours.
Cook over charcoal.

title: delicious coleslaw
directions: Add evaporated milk to the mayonnaise and blend until smooth; stir in Tabasco sauce, vinegar, mustard, sugar, celery seeds and salt. Put cabbage, carrots and green pepper in a large bowl. Pour dressing over and toss gently. Makes 12 servings.

title: very moist zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Add oil and sugars.
Mix the last 6 ingredients in separate bowl.
Mix in all ingredients. Makes 2 medium or 4 small loaves.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: no bake mint patties
directions: Blend corn syrup, butter, peppermint extract and salt.
Add powdered sugar.
Mix with spoon and hands until smooth.
Divide into thirds.
Knead 1 drop of red food coloring into 1/3.
Knead one drop of green food coloring into 1/3.
Leave 1/3 white.
Shape into small balls.
Flatten on waxed paper.
Let dry several hours.

title: lazy lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat, stirring occasionally, to separate meat; drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.
Reduce heat to low; leave on low and set aside.
Combine cottage cheese and sour cream in medium bowl; blend well.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and cream cheese thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour and add to creamed mixture.
Add flavoring and place in 9-inch tube pan in 300° oven.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 24.

title: fried corn
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large skillet.
Bring to a boil and cook until water is cooked down and corn is just about dry.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Roll in chopped nuts, if desired.
(It is very delicious without the nuts.)
Chill and serve with crackers or bread.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onions; drain well.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Mix with the sausage and onions.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
(This makes a large casserole.)

title: london broil
directions: Combine dressing mix, oil and wine; spread on both sides of steak.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Broil 3 minutes on each side. Slice thin in diagonal slices.

title: low-fat clam chowder
directions: In a large kettle, fry the bacon over medium heat until very dark and crisp.
The bacon should not produce more than 1 tablespoon of fat, if so, drain off all but 1 tablespoon.
Add the onion and fry until soft.
Sprinkle the flour over the onions, stirring well, and cook for about 1 minute.
Stir in the water, juice from the clams, potatoes, evaporated skim milk, salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Bring to a simmer and cook over low heat for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.
Add the clams and skim milk (1 cup) and simmer over low heat 10 minutes until hot. The soup will continue to develop flavor for up to 3 days and it freezes well.

title: pepper steak over fried potatoes
directions: Brown pepper steak; drain.
Add onion, green peppers, garlic, margarine, A-1, salt and pepper; cook over low heat.
Fry potatoes in electric skillet with oil.
Steak will be done when potatoes are done.
Place potatoes over plate and put steak mixture on top. Salt and pepper if needed.

title: sausage stir-fry
directions: Saute vegetables in oil until crisp and tender.
Add sausage and season to taste.
Heat thoroughly.
Mix in 1/2 cup cheese and serve immediately over hot rice, sprinkling with remaining cheese.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Layer in a 10-inch pie plate or 8-inch square pan the first six ingredients, finishing with Swiss cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then cover with unrolled biscuits and bake according to directions on biscuit can.
Serves 6.

title: crab souffle
directions: Melt and pour over all.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 1 more hour at 350°.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Boil potatoes in salted water for 15 minutes.
Fry the bacon in a saucepan until one tablespoon of fat has rendered.
Remove the bacon.
Fry the onion for three minutes in bacon fat.
Add the clam broth from canned clams.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add chopped clams, milk, cream, butter and potatoes; season with salt.
Simmer for 5 minutes, until potatoes are just tender.
Garnish bowls with a sprinkling of pepper and reserved bacon.

title: corn bread - millie style
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Put all mixed ingredients into an iron skillet.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: mixed fruit
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cover for last 30 minutes.
Watch carefully so it does not overbake.

title: 6 layer salad
directions: Layer shredded lettuce in bottom of casserole dish.
Layer bits of cauliflower on top of lettuce.
Layer chopped onion on top of lettuce and cauliflower.
Layer drained pineapple tidbits on top of entire mixture.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix onion and ground steak together.
Shape mixture into bite-size balls.
Brown slowly.
Drain off excess grease, then place in dish for freezing.
Put jelly and ketchup in saucepan. Heat until melted.
Add garlic powder and parsley.
Mix well and simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour over meatballs and cover with foil. Place in preheated oven.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Keep foil over pan until meatballs are heated.
Freezes well for later use.

title: easy chili
directions: Combine and cook in crock-pot all day.

title: fudge
directions: Boil sugar, water, milk, cocoa and butter without stirring to 238° or until mixture forms soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat and let stand undisturbed until lukewarm.
Add salt, vanilla and nuts.
Beat well until it begins to lose its gloss.
Turn quickly into a buttered pan and cut into squares.

title: shrimp fondue
directions: Melt together butter and cream cheese over low heat.
Blend until fluffy with electric mixer.
Add sour cream and heat slowly. Add chopped shrimp.
Heat only until serving temperature.
May be served with French bread, crackers or pastry shells.

title: skewered shrimp grilled or broiled on skewers
directions: Mix sherry, soy sauce (low salt), sugar, ginger and garlic. Heat above; cool to room temperature.
Thread clean shrimp lengthwise on the skewer.
Place on platter; brush with sauce on all sides.
Put in fridge for about 1 hour.
Grill over medium coals or under broiler for 4 to 6 minutes, depending upon size of shrimp.
Turn once; brush again with sauce until glazed to perfection.
Serve hot to delighted guests.
Can be main dish or super party appetizers.

title: apple cake
directions: Pour sugar over apples; let stand 20 minutes.
Mix rest of ingredients; mix all together and bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken breasts in large baking dish.
Pour melted margarine over chicken.
Add potatoes, carrots and onions. Sprinkle Cavender's generously.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in baking dish, arrange Swiss cheese slices over. Mix wine with soup and pour over chicken. Top with dressing mix and margarine mixed together. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: waldeck hoagies
directions: Brown sausage in large skillet.
Drain off grease.
Brown beef and onion in skillet.
Drain off grease.
Mix beef, onion and sausage in large pot. Add the peppers and sauce.
Heat until boiling.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Place mixture on hoagie bun and top with cheese.
Place in oven (microwave) until cheese melts (approximately 2 minutes).

title: aruba sangria
directions: In a large container, pour in wine and add all prepared fruit. Tip the bottle of Cointreau and pour while counting to 10. (Stop at 10!) Cover and
let sit refrigerated overnight.

title: barbecued beef
directions: Simmer all together in large uncovered skillet for 25 minutes or until mixture thickens.

title: chicken sparta
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Saute fresh mushrooms in butter for 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove crusts from bread and line shallow buttered 9 x 13-inch pan with bread.
Top with chicken.
You can add 1/2 cup olive slices here, if desired.
Top with cheese. Combine eggs, milk and salt in small bowl.
Pour over cheese. Combine soups; spread over top.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Next morning, bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle buttered bread crumbs over top and bake 15 minutes longer or until nicely browned.

title: 60 minute rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients with spoon.
Let rise 15 minutes.
Work down and let rise 15 minutes.
Shape into rolls and let rise for 20 minutes in warm place or over bowl of warm water.
Bake in hot oven (450°) for 10 minutes or until done.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cook broccoli 4 to 5 minutes just until crisp-tender.
Add remaining ingredients and toss with dressing just before serving.

title: red and white cabbage salad
directions: Break noodles into small pieces.
Lightly brown noodles, sunflower seeds, almonds and sesame seeds in butter or margarine. In a separate pan, bring to a boil the peanut oil, soy sauce, sugar and rice vinegar.
Cook, stirring often, until sugar dissolves. One-half hour before serving, pour dressing on cabbage.
Just before serving, add noodle mixture to salad.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Cook all the ingredients about 1 hour.
Cool slightly, then process in blender until creamy.
If serving immediately, add 1 cup of white wine (optional), otherwise freeze.

title: turnip souffle
directions: Cook first three ingredients together until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add next four ingredients; stir together and place in buttered casserole.
Top with cracker crumbs and Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until firm.

title: wassail
directions: Combine all ingredients. Bring to a boil, but do not boil. Stir constantly. Strain before serving. Garnish with orange slices.

title: pie crust
directions: In large bowl, stir together with fork the flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in shortening with fork until crumbly.
In small bowl, beat together water, vinegar and egg.
Add to flour mixture and stir until all ingredients are moistened.
Divide dough into 5 portions and, with hands, shape each in flat, round patty for rolling.
Wrap each in plastic or waxed paper and chill for 1/2 hour.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Combine sugar, spices, salt and eggs; mix well. Blend in sour cream and vinegar. Add raisins. Mix. Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool. Serve at room temperature. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: camper's special large ice cream pail pie crust(makes 2 pastry shells.)
directions: In large pail, place all ingredients, except water. Cut through shortening several times with a spatula. Apply seal; burp and shake well. Shake about 50 times. Remove seal and add warm water. Seal again, burp and shake. Dough is ready to form into balls for 2 pastry shells. Results!! A light flakey pie crust.

title: butter tarts
directions: Put several raisins, candied cherries and coconut in each unbaked tart shell.
Beat eggs until thick; add brown sugar, butter, milk and vanilla.
Mix together; fill shell about 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° until crust is light brown, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: orange delight
directions: Mix dry jello with cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Fold in oranges and pineapple.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: iranian spinach
directions: Pour oil in skillet.
Saute onion.
Drain spinach (squeeze if necessary to get out liquid).
Mix beaten eggs, salt, pepper, spinach and onion.
Add flour to thicken.
Pour into remaining oil in skillet.
Spread evenly.
Cook slowly one side, then turn to cook other side.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese before serving.

title: cheese soup
directions: Combine vegetables, water and seasonings in a large pan; cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Gradually add milk combined with flour and stir until mixture boils and thickens. Add cheese.
Lower heat and stir until cheese is melted.

title: susan's fudge
directions: Mix sugar and evaporated milk in large saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil.
Reduce heat and boil for 10 minutes stirring constantly.
Put chocolate chips, Marshmallow Creme and margarine in large bowl.
Pour hot mixture over and blend until smooth.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Mix.
Pour into well buttered 13 x 9-inch, 8 x 8-inch pans.
Chill.
Makes lots!

title: pea and peanut salad
directions: Toss together everything but the peas.
Thirty minutes before serving, fold in the frozen peas.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Beat egg yolks lightly.
Add remaining five (5) ingredients. Pour into crust.
Garnish with cherries.
Chill four (4) hours or more.

title: mama's ice cream
directions: Scald the first 3 cups of milk.
Beat the egg yolks with 1/2 of the sugar.
Add salt and cornstarch.
Stir in hot milk and beat well.
Heat mixture again and add vanilla.
Remove from heat.
Beat egg whites and add remaining sugar.
Pour warm mixture over beaten egg whites.
Place mixture into freezer.
Add enough milk to fill. Freeze according to freezer directions.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Slice bananas into pie shell. Prepare pie filling as directed using 2 1/2 cups cold milk. Fold in 1/2 cup Cool Whip; pour over sliced bananas. Chill at least 3 hours. Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: maidrites
directions: Lightly brown ground beef.
Add remaining ingredients (chop onion); mix and cook over low heat until onion is done, stirring occasionally.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: delicious frozen daequicis
directions: Blend all together and put in the freezer.
Make at least one day before party.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream butter with salt until soft.
Blend in sugar (1/4 cup at a	time) until fluffy.
Beat in egg and extract.
Stir in flour. Pack
dough
in
cookie
press
and shape on sheet. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hay and straw noodle toss
directions: Steam squash until tender.
Combine remaining ingredients; toss gently.
Serve hot or cold.

title: pear cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and spices.
Combine with creamed mixture.
Add vanilla, pears and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into tube pan and bake one hour at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Let cool.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate over low heat; cool.
Sift flour, sugar, soda, baking powder and salt together.
Add 3/4 cup of buttermilk and vanilla to flour mixture; beat for 2 minutes at medium speed with electric mixer.
Add chocolate, eggs and remaining 1/4 cup of buttermilk.
Beat for 1 additional minute with mixer.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Do not let bottoms brown.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together (except lettuce) in a mixing bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 15 minutes. Toss again before serving.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Healthy snack for kids to prepare.

title: apricot nectar punch
directions: Mix nectar and add ice cream. Let set in refrigerator to melt. When ready to use, add 7 up.

title: crunchy beef bake casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Brown ground beef.
Combine all ingredients except onions.
Pour into greased casserole dish; cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and top with fried onions and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: frozen pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pie crust, ice cream and whipped cream.

title: angel food pies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake and cool cake as directed on box. Cut in half horizontally with serrated knife.
Place on plate with cut sides up.
Cut cake 1 1/2-inches from outer edge, down 3/4-inch and through to center.
Gently pull cake out to leave 1 1/2-inch wide rim.
Fill center hole with removed cake.
Do both pieces.

title: rice krispie turtles
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips and butter in large bowl for 2 minutes in microwave.
Stir until blended well and add marshmallows.
Heat for an additional 2 minutes in microwave.
Add pecans and Rice Krispies; stir together and spoon by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Dry and eat!!

title: mayonnaise
directions: Bring vinegar and butter to a boil.
Add well-beaten egg yolks. Add cream or milk, sugar, salt, mustard and paprika.
Replace over low heat and stir until it bubbles; cool.
If it curdles, beat with an eggbeater.
Makes very good slaw dressing.

title: pickled squash
directions: Bring to boil ingredients.
Add vegetables.
Boil 3 minutes. Pack into pint jars.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients and beat well.
Add and mix well the remaining ingredients.
Chill dough overnight.
Roll 1 teaspoonful into ball.
Roll ball in sugar and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix altogether.
Cover bottom of large frypan with oil.
Let get hot.
Drop batter by tablespoon into hot oil (will spread like pancakes).
Brown on both sides.
Place on paper towels to absorb excess oil.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar.

title: miracle cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into 3-inch balls.
Flatten tops with a fork dipped in flour to make a crisscross pattern.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Marinate chicken 1 hour.
In medium size bowl, beat eggs. Drain soy sauce from chicken into eggs; blend.
Flour chicken, then dip in egg mixture.
Roll in sesame seed; spread on wax paper.
Roll in flour mixture again.
Place in glass baking dish; bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Be sure all flour is damp, either by drizzling margarine over or spraying with Pam.

title: squash dressing
directions: After mixing all ingredients, pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamy relish spread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill. Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: oven barbecued rabbit
directions: Cut in serving pieces; salt and pepper.
Preheat oven to 350°. Place rabbit in single layer in well-greased baking pan.
Squeeze lemon juice over rabbit.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Combine other ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a quick boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
While meat is cooking at the end of 30 minutes, pour mixture over meat and reduce heat to 250° and bake 3 hours.
Turn pieces over a couple times during cooking.
Very low in calories and very high in protein.

title: crab mousse
directions: Dissolve gelatin in the cold water.
Heat soup.
Add gelatin mixture.
Cool slightly.
Combine other ingredients.
Mix into soup mixture.
Pour into greased mold.
Chill 3 to 4 hours (best overnight).
Serve with fancy crackers or cocktail toast.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and add water to make 1 cup.
Put this in saucepan with pineapple and butter.
Bring to a boil. While this is cooking, beat egg and 5 tablespoons cold water, then dissolve cornstarch in this, then add sugar to it.
Now add this mixture to the cooked mixture and continue to cook and stir 2 to 3 minutes more.
Cool some and then put in baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers and 1 stick melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.

title: casserole recipe
directions: Put together; add grated cheese over and cook in oven.

title: bloomin' onion and dipping sauce
directions: Beat the egg and combine it with the milk in a bowl big enough to accommodate the onion.
In a separate bowl combine the dry ingredients.

title: cheese ball
directions: Allow the cream cheese to soften to room temperature and add to mixing bowl.
Then add the Cheddar cheese and next 5 ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and roll in the shredded beef.
This cheese ball is much better if allowed to refrigerate for 24 hours before serving.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spray 13 x 9-inch casserole dish with Pam.
Trim edges of bread and butter bread.
Put in bottom of dish.
Cook sausage; drain.
Crumble and sprinkle over bread.
Sprinkle cheese over bread and sausage. Mix eggs and milk together.
Pour over cheese. Refrigerate overnight before cooking; must soak.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: giant epanadas
directions: Saute beef, onion and green pepper in butter for 5 minutes. Drain.
Stir in tomatoes and spices.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally for 15 minutes.
Drain.
Place pie crust on end of greased cookie sheet.
Spoon half the mixture on half the crust, leaving 1-inch border.
Top with egg and raisins.
Fold over parsley; press eggs together firmly.
Brush with beaten egg yolk. Repeat with other crust.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Bake until done at 350°.
Use two 9-inch pans.

title: beefed-up biscuit dish
directions: In large frypan, brown ground beef, onion and pepper.
Drain. Stir in tomato sauce and garlic salt.
Simmer while preparing dough.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Caramelize sugar.
Remove from heat immediately and handle with care.
Add soda, butter and peanuts.
Stir and blend and pour quickly on a greased sheet.
Break into pieces.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli just until tender, drain.
Combine remaining ingredients, except cracker crumbs.
Add broccoli to this mixture. Pour into greased casserole dish and cover with cracker crumbs. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: chow mein chews
directions: Melt chips and peanut butter.
Pour over noodles and marshmallows; toss lightly.
Spoon onto wax paper.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Pour into electric ice cream maker.

title: homemade jello
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup juice.
Bring 3 1/2 cups of juice to a boil in a saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg white, then stir in fruit, if desired.

title: fried cheese
directions: Dip cheese slices into egg yolk mixture, then into flour, coating each side evenly.
Shake off excess flour.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Sift baking soda with flour.
Mix in order given.
Bake in moderate oven.

title: mexican corn casserole
directions: Melt cheese in milk over low heat, stirring constantly.
Add other ingredients; pour into greased 10 x 10-inch casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: english almond toffee
directions: Cook the first five ingredients over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Cook, without stirring, to 236° or until a little dropped in cold water forms soft ball.
Add 2/3 cup blanched almonds.
Continue cooking to 290° (soft crack stage), stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Mixture turns to a deep caramel color.
Stir in baking soda.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Mix all other ingredients and pour into first.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with a little powdered sugar.

title: onion bread
directions: Cool mixture to lukewarm.
Add 1/2 cup onions, chopped.
Add four cups flour and mix well.
Beat the batter well with small amounts of flour and adding more as you progress, 5 to 6 cups in all are needed for complete loaf with kneading, etc.
Cover and let rise 45 minutes, punch down and then turn into either loaf pans or a large pyrex bowl.
Let rise a second time and then bake one hour at 350°.

title: citrus and rice salad
directions: Drain oranges, reserving juice.
Mix juice, water, raisins and spices in saucepan.
Bring to boil; stir in brown rice.
Return to boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and let simmer 5 minutes. Spread in shallow pan.
Freeze 10 minutes to cool rice.
Toss with remaining ingredients.
Makes 5 cups or 8 servings.

title: baked stuffed flounder
directions: In skillet, heat 2 tablespoons margarine. Saute onion and celery for 5 minutes. Add cracker crumbs, egg, clam juice, lemon juice and seafood. Spread some of the mixture on each fillet and roll up. Place, seam side down, in a greased baking pan.
Combine seasoned bread crumbs with 2 tablespoons melted margarine. Sprinkle over fish rolls.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until fish flakes when tested with a fork. Serve with lemon wedges.

title: monster cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, eggs and then remaining ingredients. Mix and bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: basil marinated tomatoes
directions: Place tomato slices in shallow glass dish.
Top each one with an onion slice.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well until blended.
Drizzle onto tomato slices and onion, cover, and refrigerate for at least an hour before serving.

title: oven pancake
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Melt margarine in 9-inch round cake pan. Mix together the flour, milk, eggs and nutmeg.
Pour mixture into pan with margarine.
Bake in the oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut into 4 triangles and sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers.
Soak	overnight in lime water (2 cups lime to 2 gallons
water).
Rinse 3 or 4 times.	Put in kettle you are going
to
cook
in
(cucumbers,
vinegar,	sugar
and spices). Soak 3 hours.
Boil for 30 minutes.
Seal in jars.

title: oven-barbecued country pork ribs
directions: Place ribs in a single layer in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Drain off pan drippings; discard. Pour barbecue sauce over ribs.
Bake at 325° for additional 40 minutes or until tender.
Serves 8.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix pudding with milk; add peanut butter.
Mix well.
Blend in Cool Whip and pour into graham cracker crust.
Can be kept in freezer or refrigerator.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour half of mixture in one 9-inch pie crust and the rest in the other.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until golden brown.

title: zucchini appetizer
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden.
Let stand for 10 minutes and cut into squares. Can be eaten hot or cold.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients. Roll into quarter size balls. Roll in sugar.
Flatten somewhat with a fork.
Bake in a 350° oven. Remove when lightly browned.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, 1 tablespoons milk and sugar in large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping. Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk into bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk 1 to 2 minutes (mixture will be thick).
Stir in pumpkin and spices with wire whisk; mix well. spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until set. Garnish as desired.
Store leftover pie in refrigerator.

title: corn cob jelly
directions: Take corn cobs.
Break into small pieces.
Add 2 quarts of water and simmer in a covered pan for 10 minutes.
Strain into a large saucepan; add 4 cups of the strained water and sugar.
Bring to a boil over high heat.
Stir in Sure-Jell.
Bring to a full rolling boil and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add a few drops of food coloring for desired color. Skim off foam; pour into sterilized jars and seal.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick butter and graham cracker crumbs and line a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat together powdered sugar, 2 sticks of butter, vanilla and eggs.
Beat all together for 10 minutes.
Spread over crust, 1 layer of sliced bananas, 1 layer crushed pineapple.
Cool Whip.
Top with walnuts and half cherries.
Refrigerate at least 5 hours.

title: chicken and vegetables in shells
directions: Follow directions to prepare pastry shells.
In a saucepan, mix rest of ingredients to desired consistency by adding additional milk.
Serve over shells.
Serves 6.

title: white trash candy
directions: Combine cereal (and nuts, if desired) into large bowl.
Place almond bark in microwavable dish.
Heat and stir at 1-minute intervals until completely melted (approximately 4 minutes).
Pour melted candy over mixture in bowl.
Using wooden spoon, stir until cereal is completely coated.
Pour mixture onto wax paper and spread with wooden spoon.
Let cool.
Break into pieces.

title: french bread dip
directions: Cut top off bread.
Hollow out.
Cut inside pieces to bit size; toast for dipping.
Mix equal parts of grated Jack and Cheddar cheese with the chili salsa.
Pour into hollowed out bread.
Place top on bread.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: pizza in a crescent
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles.
Press to form four 7 x 5-inch rectangles, sealing perforations.
Arrange 9 pepperoni slices in center third of each rectangle.*
Spread 1 tablespoon spaghetti sauce over pepperoni.
Fold each slice of cheese in half; place folded slice over pepperoni.
Fold short sides of dough to almost meet in center; securely pinch top and bottom edges together, leaving middle open.
Tuck 4 or 5 pepperoni slices into middle opening.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 13 to 16 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: dutch apple topping
directions: Combine and crumble over apple pie filling and use for top of pie.

title: spinach loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a greased loaf pan.
Bake in a moderate oven for 45 minutes.
Serve with meat loaf, baked potatoes and apple salad.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Combine food coloring, cocoa and vanilla.
Stir with creamed mixture.
Add salt to flour. Alternately add flour with buttermilk to creamed mixture. Combine soda and vinegar; add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into 3 (9-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Thinly slice cucumber and onion.
Mix in sour cream and vinegar.

title: wonderful blueberry crunch
directions: Mix flour, margarine and chopped nuts (will be possibly crumbly).
Can be mixed with large mixer.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan evenly.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned; cool.
Cream the cheese and Cool Whip (which need to be at room temperature) with the powdered sugar.
Pour onto cooled crust.
Spread out evenly. Pour onto top of that the canned blueberry pie filling; spread carefully.
Refrigerate and serve.
Refrigerate any leftover.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Blend sour cream, cream cheese and sugar in mixer until smooth and creamy. Fold in topping and pour into crust.
Chill. Top with cherry pie filling.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Sprinkle apples with mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Set aside.
Combine all other ingredients in order given and beat to a smooth batter.
Pour 1/2 batter into greased angel food pan. Arrange 1/2 the apple mixture over the batter and cover with the remaining batter.
Top with the rest of the apple mixture.
Place in preheated oven at 350° and bake 1 1/2 hours or until cake is golden brown.
Turn carefully out of pan and let stand on rack to cool.

title: chocolate cookie cake
directions: Set first 6 ingredients aside. Boil water and margarine. Add to first mixture. Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla and put in greased 33 x 23-inch glass pan. Bake at 350°.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until done, then cut into medium pieces.
Put in crock-pot.
Warm sour cream, soup, butter and onion.
Pour over potatoes.
Mix in cheese.
Cook until done!

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil and mash potatoes.
Add other ingredients.
Put in casserole dish and top with topping.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sunday pancake
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Beat eggs and add remaining ingredients.
Pour into warm, buttered baking dish. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm with butter, lemon juice and powdered sugar.

title: quick pizza crust
directions: Mix yeast in warm water.
Set aside.
Mix other ingredients; then add water mixture.
Knead well.
Put on floured surface, under a bowl for 10 minutes (I always skip this step).
Roll out into a 12 or 16-inch round or cookie sheet size.
Put sauce and cheese and any other ingredients on top.
Bake at 400° to 425° for 20 to 30 minutes, depending on thickness of crust.

title: ham and broccoli stir-fry
directions: Cut off broccoli flowerets and set aside.
Trim and cut stalks in thin strips.
Heat oil with salt in wok.
Add garlic, celery, green pepper, onion and broccoli stalks.
Stir-fry about 1 minute.
Add tomato, poultry seasoning and ham.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Place broccoli flowerets on top of vegetables and ham.
Cover and steam for 5 minutes. Uncover and stir in cornstarch mixture.
Cook until thickened.

title: maria's fiesta rice
directions: Saute tomato, green pepper and onion in butter until transparent.
Set aside.
Bring chicken broth and water to a boil. Add rice to sauteed vegetables, broth and water.
Boil until water is absorbed. Add seasoned salt and pepper to taste.

title: black bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: tuna twist
directions: Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and dill.
Add rest of ingredients and chill.

title: nacho dip
directions: Pour all ingredients into crock-pot and eat with nacho chips while hot.

title: alfredo sauce
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Add sour cream, cheese and garlic powder. Cook until smooth.

title: italian chicken
directions: Mix together 1/2 cup cooking wine and eggs. Soak meat in this sauce for at least 1 hour (throw sauce away when done).
Gently roll meat in bread crumbs and fry in butter until lightly browned. Saute mushrooms in pan until brown and tender.
Mix together 1/2 cup cooking wine and broth.
Pour over chicken and mushrooms.
Top with slices of Muenster cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix and put in fridge.
Lasts 6 months.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: In
an
oiled casserole bowl, mix the following:
Layer of Fritos,
layer
of chili (canned or yours), layer of minced onion and
layer of sharp Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Combine milk, eggs, spice, salt, sugar and pumpkin.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Crumble butter into cake mix (like pie dough) and sprinkle on top of pumpkin mixture.

title: squash casserole
directions: Peel and thinly slice squash.
Cook with onion in boiling, salted water for 5 minutes.
Combine soup, sour cream and carrots. Add drained squash.
Mix oleo with stuffing mix.
Put 1/2 of stuffing on bottom of casserole.
Layer on squash mixture.
Add rest of stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
If refrigerated, let set out for 30 minutes before cooking.

title: lasagne d'italia
directions: Cook noodles. Heat oil in skillet. Cook garlic and onion until soft. Add beef and seasonings and cook until crumbly. Add tomato paste and hot water. Simmer 5 minutes. Set aside. Blend eggs with cottage cheese in bowl. Put thin layer of the meat sauce, half the noodles, all of the cottage cheese and eggs and half of the Mozzarella cheese. Repeat with half of the remaining meat sauce, the rest of noodles, sauce and Mozzarella cheese. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Let cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: lemonade
directions: Mix lemon juice and sugar.
Stir until sugar is dissolved. Add water and chill.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cut shortening and eggs.
Alternate bananas and dry ingredients.
Add milk and lemon juice.
Pour into prepared loaf pan and bake at 325° for 25 minutes, then 35 minutes at 350°. Cool and remove from pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until fork-tender; drain.
Mix with other ingredients.
Put mixture in casserole dish.
Cover well with grated sharp Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
During last 10 minutes of cooking, top with crackers or bread crumbs.

title: black bean salsa
directions: Mix together with italian dressing.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add dash of hot sauce.
Better if made the night before. Keep refrigerated.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, peanut butter, sugar, oleo and vanilla until smooth.
Fold in whipped cream.
Gently spoon into crust.
Garnish with chocolate or cookie crumbs, if desired.
Refrigerate.

title: pasta primavera
directions: About 40 minutes before serving, in saucepot, prepare spaghetti as label directs.
Drain.
Return spaghetti to saucepot; keep warm.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs until light; blend in sugar and flour.
Add buttermilk, butter and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake in 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: beefy mushroom rice
directions: Mix all soups and butter in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Add rice and mushrooms.
Place in uncovered casserole dish.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Drain and set aside. In saucepan melt cheese and margarine in the soup on low heat. Stir, making sure it doesn't burn.
Put broccoli into soup mixture.
Top with crumbs and sprinkle paprika on top.
Dot crumbs with margarine.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and golden brown on top, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream the sugar, margarine, bananas and eggs.
Add the pecans. Sift the flour and soda.
Mix all and bake in oiled loaf pan at 350° for 40 to 55 minutes.

title: selma's best oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar, and brown sugar.
Add egg. Sift together flour, soda and cinnamon and add to first mixture. Then add oats, nuts, and vanilla.
Chill 1 hour.
Put walnut-sized pieces on greased cookie sheet.
Butter bottom of small glass. Dip in granulated sugar and flatten.
Re-sugar from time to time. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix in a large mixing bowl.
Fold in 2 beaten egg whites. Drop by spoonful on a hot griddle and fry until brown.

title: yellow rice
directions: Cook rice
according to package directions with butter, turmeric and salt (if desired).

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Heat the berries, sugar and flour together in a saucepan.
Add the lemon rind, cinnamon and cardamon; stir.
Sift together the cake flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in the butter with a pastry cutter or fork until the mixture has the consistency of cornmeal.
Add the cream.
Stir with a fork.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill for at least 1 hour before serving.
For a 6 Cup Salad, add to the ingredients 1 cup fruit cocktail, drained.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender. Shred chicken and spread in the bottom of a long casserole dish.
Cook Stove Top seasoning packet, adding water and butter as directed on box. Mix soups and milk together, then pour over chicken.
Sprinkle croutons from Stove Top box on top of soup mixture.
Pour seasoning mixture over croutons. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Stir-fry meat in butter.
Add tomato juice, garlic salt and pepper.
Simmer for about 1 hour.
Add soup and mushrooms; simmer for 30 minutes.
Just before serving, add sour cream and heat through but do not boil.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Beat egg whites until fluffy.
Add salt and beat.
Gradually add sugar and cream of tartar.
Beat until very stiff.
Add vanilla and beat.
Put on pie and bake or broil until brown.

title: broiled parmesan potatoes
directions: Stir together butter, basil, paprika, garlic powder and pepper. Place potato slices in a single layer on the unheated rack of a broiler pan.
Brush butter mixture over both sides of potato slices.
Broil about 5 inches from the heat for 8 to 9 minutes or until potatoes are brown.
Turn potatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese. Broil for 4 to 6 minutes more until potatoes are tender.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Arrange chicken on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Place a layer of vegetables, add a layer of mayonnaise, then layer the onions and cheese. The last layer will be the seasoned stuffing. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Pour a layer of mixture in oblong pan.
Then add a layer of cheese, then a second layer of mixture and top with the rest of cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: quick ginger chicken
directions: Combine ginger, honey and soy sauce in a small bowl; stir well and set aside.
Place each chicken breast half between 2 sheets of heavy-duty plastic wrap; flatten to 1/4-inch thickness, using a meat mallet or rolling pin.
Coat grill rack with vegetable cooking spray; place on grill over medium hot coals.
Place chicken on rack and cook 4 minutes on each side, basting frequently with soy sauce mixture.
Place chicken on serving platter; garnish with green onion strips, if desired.
Yields 4 servings; contains about 201 calories per chicken breast half.

title: saucy skillet chicken
directions: Melt butter or margarine in skillet.
Add chicken and cook over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Turn chicken.
Add onion around edges of chicken and continue cooking 5 minutes more or until chicken is tender and golden and onion is tender.
Remove chicken from skillet.
Add jelly and vinegar to skillet, stirring constantly.
Bring to a full boil for 1 minute or until mixture is slightly reduced.
Stir in yogurt and heat to just boiling.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Serve with fresh, steamed vegetables.
Yields 4 servings.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add enough flour to stiffen. Drop on cookie sheet and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Keep checking.

title: easy breakfast muffins
directions: Cream the shortening and first 1/2 cup sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs and mix well. Add other dry ingredients alternately with milk. Fill greased muffin tins half full.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes. Take out of pan immediately. Dip tops in melted butter, then in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: favorite congealed salad
directions: Mix jello to package directions but cut down to 3/4 cup cold water
per package. Congeal jello in 3 quart oblong Pyrex dish
13-inch)
until
soft	stage.	Drain
pineapple. Reserve juice.
Mix
pineapple
with
jello
and sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Congeal
until
firm.
Soften
cream cheese and add to prepared
Dream
Whip.
Blend well.
Spread over jello mixture and chill several hours.
Cook until thick the pineapple juice, sugar,
flour,
eggs (drain in tea strainer for best results) and
lemon juice.
Stir constantly on low until thick.
Remove from
heat, stirring occasionally, until cold. Spread over cream cheese mixture.

title: oatmeal crispies icebox
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, add eggs (beat well); add vanilla and sifted dry ingredients.
Add water and nuts.
Mix well, shape in large rolls, wrap in wax paper; chill in refrigerator overnight.
Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: zesty baked catfish
directions: Combine bread crumbs, tarragon and seasoning.
Stir well. Brush fillets with French dressing.
Roll in bread crumb mixture. Arrange fillets on rack of a broiler pan that has been coated with cooking spray.
Bake, uncovered, at 450° for 10 minutes. Sprinkle fillets evenly with cheese and bake an additional 2 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Yields 4 servings.

title: hot browns
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; stir in flour.
Cook 2 minutes and add milk gradually.
Stir until thickened.
Season.
Add some of the sauce to beaten egg yolks, then return mixture to saucepan. Heat through and keep warm.
Arrange turkey on muffins.
Top each muffin with sauce, Cheddar cheese, 1 slice tomato, 1 tablespoon butter and a sprinkling of brown sugar.
(May be prepared ahead at this point and refrigerated.)
Before serving, broil 3 to 5 minutes or until lightly brown.
Garnish with bacon and warmed sauteed mushrooms.
Serves 6.
They are rich and delicious.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Prepare pasta as directed on package; drain.
Rinse with cold water.
Mix together the cheeses, eggs, parsley and nutmeg.
Fill cooked shells with mixture.
(Save aside 4 ounces Mozzarella cheese.)
Cover bottom of a roasting pan with some of the sauce. Arrange the filled shells in a single layer in the pan.
Spread the remaining grated Mozzarella cheese over the shells and pour remaining sauce over the shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Crush saltines; sprinkle on top.
Melt margarine; pour over saltines. (Could use Ritz crackers.)
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: christmas pie
directions: Stir together in saucepan the pineapple, cherries, sugar and flour and cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add the box of orange jello.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Add the bananas and pecans. You can also add a few drops of red food coloring for added color. Pour into pie crust and chill.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: baked stuffed potatoes
directions: Cut a thin slice (lengthwise) from each potato.
Scoop out potato, leaving a thin shell.
In small bowl, combine potato, cheese, milk, butter, egg, salt and pepper.
Mash until smooth. Spoon potato mixture into shell; sprinkle with paprika.

title: idaho's ugly duckling cake recipe
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, fruit cocktail and 1/2 cup coconut together.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle top with brown sugar. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top springs back when gently touched.
In saucepan, combine sugar, brown sugar, butter and milk.
Boil for 20 minutes and remove from stove.
Stir in remaining coconut (1 1/3 cups) and pour over cake.
Cool Whip may be topped on cake if desired.

title: sauteed sesame fish
directions: In a bowl, combine the flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge the fish lightly in the seasoned flour.
In a shallow bowl, combine the bread crumbs and sesame seed.
In another shallow bowl, beat the egg with the milk until blended.
Dip the fish into the egg mixture, then into the bread crumb mixture, turning to coat the fish completely.
In a large skillet, melt the butter in the oil over medium-high heat.
When the butter and oil are hot but not smoking, add the fish steaks and cook them until brown, about 5 minutes on each side.
Serve fish hot with lemon wedges and parsley sprigs.

title: sassy caramel apple dip
directions: Mix container of apple dip with 1/2 cup of vanilla flavored yogurt and ground cinnamon; chill. Just before serving, stir in toasted pecans. Serve with sliced apples. Refrigerate leftover dip.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt margarine in large pan.
Add onion soup; stir.
Add soup, water and rice; stir well.
When mixture begins to boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer for about 20 minutes.
Garnish with mushrooms.

title: grandma's caramel-apple pie
directions: In a medium bowl, combine caramel candy pieces and flour. Stir in apples, caramel topping and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into pie crust and top with pecans.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes until crust is golden brown.
Serve with a scoop of vanilla ice cream.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Prepare and bake shortcake in 8 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pan; remove from pan and cool on rack about 5 minutes.
Using a sharp knife, gently split shortcake horizontally into two layers; lift off top carefully.
Place bottom layer on serving plate.
Spread a little softened butter over bottom layer.

title: sugar drop cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients as pie dough.
Beat eggs.
Add lemon or vanilla.
Add to flour mixture.
I like icing on them.

title: mexican chicken and rice
directions: Heat
oil
in
large
skillet on medium-high heat.
Add corn, broth and salsa;
bring to a boil.
Stir in rice; cover. Remove from
heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir.
Sprinkle with cheese; cover.
Let stand 2 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: heath cookies
directions: Bring butter and sugar to boil for 2 minutes.
Break graham crackers into quarter on ungreased cookie sheet.
Pour syrup over crackers and sprinkle with almonds or pecan pieces.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 16 minutes. Cool and remove carefully.
Place on wax paper.

title: strawberry cheesecake trifle
directions: Beat cream cheese until it is softened.
Beat in sour cream. In another bowl, beat whipping cream until soft peaks form.
Stir into creamed cheese mixture.
Stir in confectioners sugar, vanilla and almond flavoring.
Cut angel food cake into 2-inch pieces. Gently fold cake into creamed mixture.
Sugar berries with 1/4 cup sugar, if desired.
Using a trifle or deep glass bowl, layer creamed mixture and strawberries, beginning and ending with creamed mixture.
Garnish top with whole berries.
Serves 10 to 15.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix the cukes, onions and salt. Cover with cracked ice.
Place weight on them and let stand 3 hours.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half; remove seeds.
In a large skillet, fill half with water; parboil peppers until tender.
Mix in bowl hamburg, rice, garlic powder, diced onion and stewed tomatoes; mix well.
Spoon mixture into pepper halves; place in baking pan. (Cover stuffed peppers with sauce, if desired.)
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake 40 minutes in preheated 350° oven.
Serves 6.

title: philly cheese ball
directions: Combine cheese food, softened cream cheese and 2 tablespoons margarine; mix until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Mold into bell shapes, using the cold pack container coated with margarine.
Chill until firm.
Unmold.
Garnish with chopped parsley and pimiento strips if desired.
Makes 2 bells.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain beans and add celery, onion, sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.

title: one-bowl chocolate fudge
directions: Microwave chocolate and milk in a large microwavable bowl on High for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring halfway through or until chocolate is melted.
Remove from microwave and continue stirring until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir in vanilla and nuts. Pour into pan and cool.
Cut into squares.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: ham ball
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients.
Add hot sauce to taste.
Shape into ball.
Chill.
Mix together cream cheese and milk.
Frost ham ball with this.

title: no fail pastry shells
directions: Cut together flour, salt and shortening.
Mix together vinegar, egg and water.
Beat with fork and pour over flour mixture.
Mixture should be sticky/soft.
Divide into 3 parts. Roll out on lightly floured surface.
Makes 3 (9-inch) pie crusts. Bake at 450° until brown, about 10 minutes.

title: billie-jo's saute sauce
directions: Cut meat into strips.
Mix together all ingredients and pour over meat.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours, preferably overnight.
Cook meat in sauce on stove or on grill until finished.
If cooking on grill, use aluminum foil or put sauce in pan and heat separately.
Can also be baked in oven if using a whole beef roast.
This can be used for London broil, beef roasts and thinly sliced chipped steak meat.

title: oyster stew
directions: Mix together in saucepan.
Simmer over low heat until heated well.
Serve with crackers.

title: rummy pears
directions: Put pears in microwave dish at least 1-inch deep.
Put 1 tablespoon butter, 1 tablespoon sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon in each pear.
Pour 1/2 cup rum over pears.
Cook on High for 3 minutes.
Spoon sauce over pears.
Add more rum, if needed.
Cook on High for 3 more minutes or until almost tender.
Spoon sauce over pears.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a large baking dish in oven.
Mix together flour, sugar, salt, baking powder, milk and egg.
If using self-rising flour, omit the salt and baking powder.
Pour mixture over the melted margarine and bake at 325° until golden brown or done, about 45 minutes.

title: navy bean soup
directions: Put the beans, which have been soaked overnight, into a soup kettle with the ham bone and cover with 3 quarts of water.
Cook very slowly; after a couple of hours or when beans are half cooked, add the mashed potatoes.
Stir until thoroughly mixed, then add onions, tomato, celery, garlic and parsley.
After soup has begun to boil, turn the fire low and let simmer for about an hour, then remove the ham bone.
Chop up all pieces of meat on it and return the meat to soup before serving.
Serves 8.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cut up chicken breasts into cubes. Line bottom of casserole dish with chicken. Mix soup, taco mix, cheese and milk together and pour over chicken. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes. Put chips and cheese on top of casserole and bake 10 more minutes or until golden and bubbly.

title: rich pineapple pie
directions: Cream the sugar and margarine together.
Add one egg at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour.
Mix in coconut and pineapple gradually.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: playdough for kids
directions: Mix ingredients together in pan over medium heat.
Stir constantly until ball begins to form.
Remove from pan.
It should be stored in an airtight container in the refrigerator.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease large baking sheet. Bake potatoes about 45 minutes, till tender.
Cool potatoes, peel and mash.
Stir in buttermilk baking mix and sugar.
Add enough water to form a soft dough.
Roll out dough onto a lightly floured surface until a 1/2 inch thick.
Cut out biscuits and bake about 18 minutes.

title: beef stuffed peppers
directions: Cook and drain meat, first.
Cut off tops of green peppers and remove seeds.
Wash.
Combine egg and 3/4 cup sauce.
Then add rest of ingredients.
Stuff peppers with meat mixture and place peppers in lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Cover loosely with wax paper and microwave at High 12 to 14 minutes. Turn dish after 6 minutes.
Spoon remaining sauce over tops of peppers and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: sour pickles
directions: Place cucumbers in quart jars packed tightly.
Add brine, covering cucumbers, leaving air space.
Let set for 3 weeks. Refrigerate before using.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Remove crust from bread and cube bread.
Spread half of cubed bread on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix chicken, celery, onion and mushrooms.
Spread on top of bread cubes.
Place rest of bread on top.

title: beef tips
directions: Bake
sirloin tips and tear into bite size pieces.
Mix onion soup
mix, mushroom soup and water together.
Pour over meat. Cook in oven about 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: georgia cheese grits
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large saucepan, bring salted water to
boiling. Stir in grits and cook as package directs. Remove from heat. Add butter and cheese; stir until both are melted. Then stir in eggs and salt.
Lightly butter 2-quart shallow casserole dish. Spread mixture into casserole evenly. Bake uncovered 1 hour. Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked beans
directions: Do not drain beans.
Cook bacon (not brown) and onions. Use all
fat
from bacon.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 1
1/2	to 2 hours.
Or put all ingredients in crock-pot and bake
on
low
for	several
hours.
(This recipe from Lolabelle Miller.)

title: chewy bars
directions: Combine flour, oatmeal, butter and brown sugar; mix together until well blended.
Reserving 1/2 cup of this mixture, pat remainder into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Remove from oven and pour condensed milk over crust.
Sprinkle chips and nuts over condensed milk.
Top with remaining oatmeal mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut when cool.

title: rainbow ribbon jello
directions: Dissolve 1 package jello in 1 1/4 cups boiling water.
Pour 3/4 cup into 9-inch square pan or 6-cup ring mold.
Chill until set but not firm, about 15 minutes.
Chill remaining jello in bowl. Gradually blend in 3 tablespoons sour cream.
Spoon over jello in mold.
Chill until set but not firm, about 15 minutes.
Repeat with each remaining flavor of jello chilling dissolved gelatin before measuring and pouring into mold.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Cut in wedges or rectangles.
Makes 12 servings.

title: cream cheese cupcakes
directions: Place one wafer in aluminum cupcake holders.
Mix cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla thoroughly.
Put mixture on top of wafer (about 1/2 to 3/4 full).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Remove from oven.
While still hot, put cherry or blueberry pie filling on top.

title: tiny fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray 24 mini muffin tins. Melt butter, semi-sweet chocolate and sugar together in a small saucepan over low heat until smooth.
Beat in vanilla and egg. Fold flour until blended.
Fill tins 1/2 full.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with melted milk or white chocolate.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar in medium mixing bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add alternately with sour cream to butter mixture and beat well.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until cake springs back when lightly touched and has separated from sides of pan.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Shred cake in 9x13 inch dish. Cream the cheese with the pudding, gradually adding milk. Beat slowly until thick, pour over cake. Drain pineapple and put over pudding. Cover with Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry bacon; drain.
Brown ground beef and onions; drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: corn pudding
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Mix 10 seconds at high speed.
Pour into well-greased baking dish.
Dot with butter and bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: corn-bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease 12 muffin pan cups.
Stir cereal and milk in large bowl; let stand 10 minutes.
In medium bowl, combine flour, cornmeal, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Add eggs, oil and vanilla to milk mixture.
Whisk in brown sugar until smooth.
Add dry ingredients.
Spoon batter into prepared cups.
Bake 20 minutes until toothpick inserted in center of muffin comes out clean.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: strawberry pie
directions: *Found in
dairy
or fruit department in most supermarkets; other brand
of
strawberry
glaze	mix can be used, but this is the best I have found.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Place crackers into deep dish.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Pour over crackers, mixing well.
Bake at 200° for 15 minutes.
Toss to coat crackers and bake 15 additional minutes. Cool.
Store in airtight container.
Best if made a day ahead.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Pour melted butter over pecans; stir.
Arrange in single layer on baking sheet; sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 275 for one hour. Stir every 15 minutes.
Drain on paper towel.

title: calcutta chicken salad
directions: Serve with coconut, walnuts and bacon pieces, if desired. Prepare the night before.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Cut, pare and peel enough apples to fill pie tin 3/4 full (about 4 large apples).
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Melt oleo.
Stir in 1 cup sugar and flour.
Set aside to cool.
Beat egg and fold into flour mixture.
(Can add nuts if desired.) Spoon flour mixture over apples as evenly as possible.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate zinger
directions: Mix up the flour, butter and nuts.
Press into pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool. While cooling, mix the powdered sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Spread on top of zinger.
Mix chocolate pudding according to directions on box.
Pour on top. Top with remaining Cool Whip mixture. Shave chocolate on top.
You may use cherries.

title: sauteed squash, potatoes and onions
directions: Melt butter in skillet. Add sliced squash, diced potatoes, sliced onions, salt and pepper and stir-fry slowly until vegetables are done.
(A little water may need to be added.)

title: apple bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes and remove from pan to continue cooling.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: cheesy spaghetti bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a skillet, brown ground chuck and onion; drain fat.
Add spaghetti sauce; simmer for 10 minutes. Break spaghetti into thirds and cook according to directions on box; rinse and drain.
Mix cooked spaghetti with sauce.
In a saucepan, melt butter; stir in flour and salt.
Slowly add milk and water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add 1/2 cup shredded cheese, stirring until melted. Spread 1/2 spaghetti in bottom of 10 x 16 x 2 baking dish.
Spoon all cheese sauce over spaghetti.
Top with remaining spaghetti mixture and shredded cheese.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: quick wiener schnitzel
directions: Combine egg and milk; blend.
Dip veal in egg mixture, then breadcrumbs.
Brown veal in butter over medium heat 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with lemon wedge.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 full minute (time accurately).
Add salt and vanilla.
Blend in peanut butter and oats.
Mix well.
Drop on wax paper and let stand until firm, approximately 30 minutes.

title: lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix approximately 4 minutes with electric mixer.
Bake in greased Bundt pan 45 minutes or in 2 loaf pans for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Fry ground meat and onion until brown. Add celery, bell pepper and tomatoes.
Cover and cook until vegetables are tender.
Mix soup and milk together, then add meat and vegetable mixture.
Pour over parboiled noodles in a large baking dish and bake about 30 minutes.

title: tex-mex chicken
directions: Drain and rinse black beans.
Drain corn.
Sprinkle both sides of chicken with 1 teaspoon ground cumin and garlic salt.
Heat oil in 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken; cook 3 minutes on each side.
In medium bowl, combine beans, corn, picante sauce, red pepper and remaining cumin.
Turn chicken; spoon bean mixture over chicken.
Reduce heat to medium.
Cook covered for 10 minutes or until chicken is done and bean mixture is thickened.
Sprinkle with cilantro.
Serve with white or flavored rice.
Serves 6.

title: mexican chicken
