directions: Grease a large casserole and cover bottom with Doritos that have been dipped in chicken stock.
Next, make a layer of chicken and sprinkle with peppers and onions.
Cover with cheese.
Mix soups, tomatoes, garlic and chili powder separately.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Top with more cheese; sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pork and beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Cook
in
morning
until
nearly done. Heat other ingredients;
add beans.
Put in cans.
Cold pack for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 12 quarts.
You can cook together 1 cup brown sugar, 1 cup
white sugar and 1/2 cup water.
This can be used instead of maple syrup.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes, until the top is soft, but not raw.

title: cheesecake
directions: Blend cream cheese, milk and lemon juice.
Put in crust; top with pie filling.
Chill until firm.

title: smithie's buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and melted margarine, having flour mixed with sugar.
Add vanilla and buttermilk.
Pour into pie shell and bake in moderately heated oven for 45 minutes.

title: cracker cookie bars
directions: Bring all ingredients, but nuts, to a boil.
Make sure sugar is melted and mixture is beginning to thicken.
Pour over graham crackers that have been sprinkled with nuts.

title: pickled beets
directions: In cheesecloth, put 1 tablespoon or more of mixed pickling spices.
Boil until sugar and spices are blended.
Then add cooked beets and slices of onion.
Bring to boil.
Put small slice of garlic in sterilized jar with beets and onion, now seal.

title: grape nut bread
directions: Soak the Grape Nuts in the milk for 10 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into the loaf pan and let rise one hour at room temperature.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Makes 1 large loaf.

title: out of world cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done when toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: green chili coleslaw
directions: Combine all ingredients, except Dressing, and let sit for 2 hours, refrigerated.

title: rivels
directions: Mix.
Stir and stir.
It will break up into small pieces. These little pieces are called rivels.
They are good in soup to give it thickening.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour mixture into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes. Dust lightly with powdered sugar.

title: onion in mushroom sauce
directions: Cook onions; combine soup and milk.
Pour over onions; sprinkle on cheese; then buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes, or until cheese melts.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Drop from wet spoon onto greased baking sheet.
Press ridges across top with fork.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes. Yields 7 to 8 dozen.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Put chicken or browned hamburger in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan. Put crushed Doritos on top and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Mix soups and onion together and spread over cheese.
Put tomatoes on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: Mix together.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice bake
directions: Cook rice separate.
Saute celery and onion in butter.
Add broccoli, cream of mushroom soup, Cheez Whiz, celery and onion to cooked rice.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: dutch dumplings
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir milk in until blended.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto boiling beef or chicken stew (try to drop onto meat, not liquid).
Cook 10 minutes uncovered, then 10 minutes more tightly covered.

title: blender popovers
directions: Put all ingredients in blender jar and beat for 2 minutes. Pour into well-greased muffin tins.
Bake for 35 minutes at 450° and 20 minutes at 350°.
Yields 1 dozen popovers.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Mix sugar, apple cider and cider vinegar in a 3-gallon pot. Save 1/2 cup of liquid to blend your peppers with.
When peppers are pureed, pour into a sugar mixture.
Bring first 5 ingredients to a rolling boil.
Boil for 5 minutes and remove from fire for 10 to 15 minutes.
Put back on fire and add Certo and food color. Bring to a rolling boil for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Pour into sterile jars.
If using jelly jars, melt paraffin wax and seal.

title: graham cracker pie
directions: Mix pudding according to package instructions, but add 2 or 3 egg yolks.
Pour into a precooked pie shell.
Make a meringue topping for top of pie.
Cook in oven until meringue browns. Allow to cool for one hour.

title: tuscan lamb chop skillet
directions: Trim fat from chops.
In a large skillet cook chops in hot oil over medium heat about 8 minutes for medium doneness, turning once.
Transfer chops to a plate; keep warm.

title: one pot dinner
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain off fat and put beef in slow cooker.
Brown bacon and onion; drain off fat.
Add to beef and add remaining ingredients to cooker.
Stir together well. Cover and cook on low 4 to 6 hours.

title: broccoli balls
directions: Mix ingredients well and chill for 2 hours.
Put a little oil on hands and form balls, using 1 teaspoon mixture for each.
Bake on lightly greased baking sheet at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Freezes well in plastic bags.
Bake frozen at 350° for 35 minutes. May be served with hot mustard sauce.
Yields approximately 65 balls.

title: junior pate
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Mound on serving plate and surround with crackers.

title: blue ribbon fudge
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a saucepan. Bring to a full rolling boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Boil 6 minutes over heat, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat. Stir in miniature marshmallows and vanilla and stir until marshmallows melt and mixture is well blended. Remove 2 cups of hot mixture and add semi-sweet chocolate chips. Stir until chips are melted and mixture is well blended. Pour evenly into a greased 8-inch saucepan. To the remaining hot mixture, add milk chocolate chips. Stir until chips are melted and mixture is well blended. Spread evenly over semi-sweet mixture in pan. Chill until firm (about 4 hours). Makes about 2 3/4 pounds.

title: boiled cabbage
directions: Shred or boil cabbage; drain, reserving 1 cup liquid.
Place layer of cabbage in buttered baking dish.
Combine grapes, apples, onion, sugar and salt and arrange in alternate layers with cabbage, making top layer cabbage.
Add cabbage liquid and claret, and dot with butter. cover and bake in moderately hot oven (375°) for 1 hour.
Shake flour over top; mix lightly with fork and bake 15 minutes longer.
Approximate yield:
6 portions.

title: beef rancho
directions: Cube round steak and brown in oil or butter.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook
until
tender.
Cover all with tomato sauce. Add chili powder.
Cover
and simmer 20 to 30 minutes. Prepare rice as meat mixture is simmering.
Serve meat mixture over rice.

title: pow!
directions: Good for the nerves.
Break up enough dried catnip to fill a teaspoon.
Put in a pitcher of boiling water and be sure the water is boiling.
Cover and let stand for half an hour.
Strain and drink just as you put your lights out for the night.

title: garlic bread sticks
directions: Soften 1 package active dry yeast in warm water.
Add salt. Blend in 3 cups flour and garlic cloves, mashed well.
Add 2 to 2 1/2 cups more flour.
Knead until smooth.
Put into a greased bowl. Cover and let stand 2 hours until doubled.
Punch down.
Let stand 10 minutes, covered.
Roll sections of dough into long sticks (about 8 or 10).
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Brush with 1 egg, beaten with 1 tablespoon milk.
Let rise in warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.
Again brush with egg and sprinkle on garlic salt.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: lasagna florentine
directions: In a large pan, saute onion and garlic in oil until brown. Add pasta sauce and simmer for 15 minutes.
In large bowl, mix Ricotta cheese, spinach, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
In a 15 x 9-inch baking dish, layer 2 cups sauce, half the lasagna noodles, half the remaining sauce, all the spinach and cheese mixture, half the Mozzarella, the remaining lasagna noodles and sauce.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and top with remaining Mozzarella.
Bake 15 minutes.
Let stand for 15 minutes before slicing.

title: crunch drop
directions: Sift flour and soda together.
Set aside.
In large bowl, cream butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy. Mix in flour mixture until well combined.
Stir in oats and coconut to make a stiff dough.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 10 dozen.

title: fruit punch
directions: Boil 3 1/2 cups sugar in 2 cups water.
Let cool.
Add the above ingredients.
Just before serving, add 2 quarts ginger ale. Serves 50 people.

title: italian fruit salad
directions: Boil sugar, flour, cornstarch, lemon juice and egg until thick.
Pour thickened liquid over cooked noodles.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
In morning, add fruit and Cool Whip.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°; use 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt butter; sprinkle
crumbs
over
butter.
Pour
milk evenly over crumbs. Top
with
the remaining ingredients;
press down gently.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.
Cool before cutting.

title: salsa recipe
directions: Put all ingredients in blender and blend for a few seconds.

title: simply italian chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in salad dressing overnight.
Place on hot barbecue grill for 30 minutes or until done.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Add cubed Velveeta; heat until melted.
Add rosemary and broccoli; stir until hot.
Hollow a round loaf of pumpernickel bread.
Pour broccoli-cheese mixture into center of bread.
Use pieces of bread to dip into mixture.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Add egg and water.
Beat; sift flour, salt, cayenne and paprika.
Add dry ingredients to mixture; beat well after each.
Chill dough for 10 minutes.
Pack into pastry press; squeeze shapes onto baking sheet.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil noodles according to package; drain and pour into casserole dish.
Melt butter; add flour and mix well.
Add milk and mix over low to medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Add cheese and continue to heat until all cheese is melted.
Must stir constantly as mixture burns easily.
Salt and pepper to taste. Pour cheese mixture over noodles and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes until brown.
For a spicier flavor, use Mexican Velveeta.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Saute the onion in 4 tablespoons butter; add flour and water.
Cook until it comes to a boil.
Remove from heat and add Cheez Whiz.
Drain broccoli and add to the cheese sauce. Add the beaten eggs.
Put in buttered casserole; sprinkle with cracker crumbs and top with rest of butter.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: 8 hour tossed salad
directions: Put in order in a see through container.
Spread mayonnaise over top to seal, then sprinkle Sweet 'N Low or sugar and cheese over top.
Cover and let stand 8 hours or overnight.
Toss well about 30 minutes before serving.

title: spaghetti and meat balls
directions: Mix onions, celery, green pepper, garlic and meat; form into balls. Put small amount of fat in heavy skillet. Roll balls in fat until well browned. Mix spaghetti and tomato paste, juice and water and chili powder. Pour over meat balls. Place in slow oven and bake for 1 hour.

title: cool whip pie
directions: Chill pineapple and pie filling in refrigerator.
Mix remainder of items with pie filling and pineapple.
Add 1 cup of broken pecans (optional).
Pour into bowl and refrigerate.

title: mushroom sauce
directions: Wash and dry mushrooms.
With a greased knife, slice into 1-inch pieces.
In a frying pan, combine oil, butter and pork. Cook for 5 minutes. Add mushrooms and parsley. Cook until lightly brown.
In a bowl, dissolve bouillon cubes in water. Add bouillon mixture, salt and pepper to mushroom mixture. Reduce heat. Cook slowly for 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Saute zucchini and onion in oil until tender.
Add pepperoni and cook.
Stir in tomato sauce, 3/4 can water, 1/2 cup potato flakes, salt, pepper and oregano.
In bowl, combine 3/4 cup potato flakes, flour, grated cheese and salt.
Cut margarine into potato flakes in bowl; mix until crumbly.
Add water; stir dough until it holds together.
Press into bottom and sides of ungreased 9-inch pie pan or baking dish.
Spread mixture into crust.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 20 minutes or until done.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except poppy seed, together for 3 minutes.
Then fold in poppy seed.
Pour into greased Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, until knife inserted in the middle comes out clean.
Makes a good coffee cake.

title: slow ball dip
directions: Hollow out round bread (save pieces).
In large bowl, cream cream cheese.
Add clams.
Reserve juice add 1/4 cup liquid.
Add onion, beer, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, hot pepper sauce and salt.
Put mixture into hollowed out bread.
Cover entire loaf with foil.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.
Serve with veggies and bread pieces.

title: marc's broccoli casserole
directions: In a large pan, melt margarine.
Cut onion up coarsely.
Add chopped broccoli and saute.
Cook rice according to package directions.
When onions are limp, add soups and mix thoroughly. Add cooked rice to mixture.
Add milk and 1/2 of the package of cheese.
Mix well.
Turn into a deep 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake at 350° until cheese is well melted and starting to brown.
Remove from oven and serve. Freezes well also, but leave off cheese on top.
Enjoy.
Serves 12.

title: goya with soul
directions: In medium roasting pan, place wings neatly.
Add 2 1/4 cups of water, onion soup mix and olive oil in bowl (stir).
Pour mixture over chicken in roasting pan.
Heat oven to 375° to 400°.
Place covered roasting pan in oven.
Bake chicken 45 minutes or until almost done.
Add Goya rice mix into roasting pan with wings and mixture.
Cook at 350° for 1/2 hour; juice will cook rice.
Take out of oven and let stand, uncovered, 20 minutes.
Mix lightly with large fork.
Ready to serve.

title: baccala and potatoes
directions: In a 6-quart saucepot, saute onion, celery, salt, pepper and oregano for 10 minutes.
Add potatoes and cook 15 minutes.
Add tomatoes and water; cook 30 minutes on low heat.
Add baccala and simmer 30 minutes more.
Good lenten meal.

title: hominy casserole
directions: Cook hominy 15 minutes; drain.
Mix soup, sour cream, onions and chilies.
Add to hominy.
Pour into buttered baking dish. Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: spiced lentils
directions: Cook the lentils in 2 1/4 cups water (bring to boil, cover and lower heat to simmer) 30 to 40 minutes or until tender.
Meanwhile, cook everything else (except the apples) until tender, in deep heavy skillet, adding water if necessary to avoid sticking.
Add apples to the saute; cook 10 minutes more (covered) and then combine this mixture with the lentils in a casserole.
Cover and keep warm in a 250° oven.
Serves 4 to 6 folks.

title: tomato delight
directions: Sprinkle tomato slices with oregano.
Put small amount of mayonnaise on each slice.
Sprinkle with bacon; cover with cheese. Broil on cookie sheet until cheese is melted.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Microwave peanuts for one minute.
Mix syrup and sugar, add peanuts and stir well.
Microwave for 3 minutes and stir. Microwave for 3 1/2 minutes and add oleo and vanilla.
Stir well. Microwave for one minute, add soda.
Stir well and fast.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet as thin as you can.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix soda in buttermilk.
Mix sugar, melted butter and eggs. (Set aside 1 1/2 cups flour to flour nuts and raisins.)
Mix the remaining 2 1/2 cups of flour and spices.
Add to sugar and egg mixture, alternating with soda and buttermilk mixture.
Add preserves, applesauce and pineapple.
Fold in floured fruit and nuts.
(Take out 3 cups batter to put in icing.)

title: party meatballs
directions: Blend together meat, egg, onion, salt and pepper.
Form into 100 small meatballs.
Combine chili sauce, jelly and lemon juice. Pour over meatballs and simmer in electric skillet for one hour. Serve in heated chafing dish.

title: stephanie's hamburger supper
directions: Brown meat and cook noodles.
Mix all together except cheese and pour into casserole.
Grate cheese and put on top of meat mixture.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips in saucepan until shiny.
Add peanut butter; mix well.
Pour over cereal in large bowl; mix well.
Place confectioners sugar in large bag.
Add cereal mixture.
Shake to mix well.
Package in new dog food bowls for gifts, if desired. Yield:
16 servings.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread everything by order.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Great with ice cream.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Sugar cookie dough needs to be room temperature.
Pat into a 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Put cream cheese in a small bowl, heat in microwave on Low for 2 minutes. Stir in 4 tablespoons sugar.
Spread on crust.
Drain apricots, reserving 2/3 cup syrup.
In 4-cup glass measure, combine cornstarch, remaining sugar and spices.
Stir in reserved syrup and jelly.
Cook, uncovered, on High in microwave for 3 to 4 minutes until boiling.
Arrange fruit on top of pizza, beginning in center with pineapple rings, arrange raspberries around pineapple, then apricot halves and then strawberries.
Spoon syrup over fruit; chill.
Cut into wedges.

title: beef and potato nacho casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and 1/2 cup onion.
Drain off fat.
Stir in taco seasoning, water and tomato sauce.
Bring to a boil and simmer 1 minute.
Spread into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top mixture with green chillies, beans and potatoes.

title: heavenly delight
directions: Mix butter, flour and 1/2 cup pecans and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix 1 cup Cool Whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Spread over first layer.
Use pudding mix whipped in cold milk.
After it sets, spread this over second layer.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with chopped nuts. Serves 12 or more.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut beef into bite size strips.
Mix together sour cream, flour and tomato paste.
Stir in water, bouillon and pepper; set aside. Cook fettucine according to package directions.
Omit salt and oil; drain well.
Meanwhile, spray cold large skillet with nonstick spray.
Preheat skillet over medium heat.
Add beef to hot skillet. Stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove beef from skillet.
Add mushrooms, onions and garlic.
Stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes.
Add sour cream mixture to skillet.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Return beef; cook for 2 more minutes.
Serve mixture over fettucine.
Garnish, if desired.

title: mrs. j's chili
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Drain well and set aside.
Saute onion until soft.
Combine all ingredients in skillet.
Simmer, covered, for 2 hours.
Remove garlic before serving.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Combine sugars and shortening until creamy and fluffy.
Beat in eggs. Stir in sour cream, blending well. Sift flour with dry ingredients.
Add to the batter with lemon extract or vanilla. Add enough flour
so dough can be easily rolled out.
Roll out on floured board to 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with a large cookie cutter. Sprinkle with sugar.
Place a raisin or pecan half in the center of each cookie.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheets and bake at 350° until lightly browned (about 10 minutes).

title: potato pancakes(polish)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat well.
Drop mixture by heaping tablespoonful on well-greased hot griddle or pan and spread thinly.
Fry both sides until a golden brown.
Add more shortening as needed.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Bake, cool and crumble Jiffy Mix, add tomatoes, pepper, onion and relish.
Set aside.
Mix pickle relish juice and the salad dressing.
Pour dressing over the other ingredients.
Do not mix.

title: english toffee
directions: Warm a baking sheet with sides in oven.
Combine butter and sugar in a medium size saucepan.
Cook over high heat, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon, until mixture reaches the soft crack stage (280° on candy thermometer).
Reduce heat to medium-high and continue stirring constantly.

When mixture reaches the hard crack stage (300° on candy thermometer), pour mixture onto baking sheet and spread as thin as possible with a rubber spatula. (Mixture will not cover entire baking sheet.)
Immediately sprinkle with chocolate chips and let set 5 minutes.
Spread chocolate until smooth.
Sprinkle with nuts and gently press into warm chocolate. Cool uncovered in refrigerator.
When chocolate hardens, break into bite size pieces.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: quick apple crisp
directions: Add ingredients in order.
Mix as you add each ingredient. Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fresh corn cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 475° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: layered crab spread
directions: Mix well the first 6 ingredients and spread on a flat dish. Pour 1/2 to 2/3 jar of cocktail sauce over the cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle crab meat on top of sauce and sprinkle chopped parsley on top.
Serve on Ritz crackers.

title: mexican beef stir fry
directions: Cut beef steak into 1/8 inch thick strips.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat after each addition.
Stir in pineapple.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Add nuts.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Frost, if desired.

title: come on over cake
directions: Grease 10 x 13-inch pan.
Crush crackers; mix with nuts and baking powder.
Beat egg whites with white sugar and vanilla. Fold cracker mixture into egg whites.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes; cool completely.
Mix Cool Whip and softened cream cheese, powdered sugar and drained pineapple.
Spread on cake. Refrigerate overnight.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans.
Pour into baking dish; top with pecans.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Delicious served hot or cold.
Serve with crackers.

title: banana fruit pudding
directions: Drain fruit and combine 2 cups juice with pudding.
Add water if necessary to make 2 cups.
Cook and stir until it comes to a boil.
Let cool; fold into fruit and refrigerate.

title: beef and potatoes
directions: Mix beef, salt, pepper, mashed potatoes, milk and egg.
Shape into patties.
Brown on both sides.

title: bill clinton favorite tortilla recipe chicken enchiladas
directions: Remove seeds from chilies and chop.
Then in large skillet, heat amount of oil.
Add chilies and garlic and saute.
Drain and break up tomatoes.
Reserve 1/2 cup liquid.
Add tomatoes, onion, 1 teaspoon salt, oregano and reserved tomato liquid to the chilies and garlic.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until thick. Set aside.
Combine the chicken with the sour cream, grated cheese and other teaspoon of salt.
Heat 1/3 cup oil, dip tortillas in oil until they become limp.
Drain well on paper towels.
Preheat the oven to 250°.
Fill the tortillas with chicken mixture.
Roll them up and arrange side by side, seam down in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour chili sauce over enchiladas and bake about 20 minutes, or until heated through.

title: pilau (spiced rice)
directions: Heat the oil in a pan and, over moderate heat, fry the onion for 2 minutes, or until turns golden.
Add the rice and stir well. Add the turmeric and salt and continue to fry the rice lightly for 2 minutes.
Add water, cloves and bay leaves; stir.
Bring to a boil and immediately turn the heat to low.
Cover the pan and cook for 15 minutes.
Stir once toward the end of that time.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Add jello.
Mix well.
Add drained fruit cocktail and nuts.
Mix.
Keep refrigerated.

title: raspberry kisses
directions: Beat egg whites with salt until foamy.
Combine gelatin with sugar.
Add gradually to the egg whites, beating to stiff peaks. Make sure sugar is well dissolved by rubbing a bit of the mixture between your fingers.
It should not feel grainy.
Blend in vinegar, then fold in chocolate.
Drop by teaspoons onto ungreased brown paper-lined or nonstick pans.
Bake 25 minutes in a preheated 250° oven.
Then turn off oven, but do not remove cookies for another 20 minutes.
The kisses are light and fragile, remove carefully with spatula.
Ideal for those on low-cholesterol diet.

title: freezer tip:  for green beans, peas, lima beans, etc.
directions: Prepare and clean vegetables.
Place in quart Ziploc freezer bag.
Add water to each bag, set in microwave opened.
Heat 3 minutes on High.
Take out, place on towel to cool.
Zip closed and place in refrigerator to cool before freezing.

title: tijuana casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and chopped onion in a skillet; drain excess grease.
Cut corn tortillas in half and layer in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

Spoon half of the ground beef and onion onto tortillas, then pour 2 cans of Ranch Style beans on top of meat. Put sliced cheese on top of beans, then layer more corn tortillas, then the rest of the meat and onion.

title: career girl dessert
directions: Layer above ingredients in order of listing in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Drizzle Eagle Brand milk over the layers.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken divine
directions: Melt the butter in a 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Place the broccoli evenly over bottom of dish.
Sprinkle half the Cheddar and Parmesan cheeses over the broccoli.
Top with chicken breasts.

title: crab cakes
directions: *(The jumbo is best for large patties, but not good for tiny ones.
The backfin is good for both.)

title: macaroni casserole italiano
directions: In large skillet, crumble meat; cook until almost done. Drain.
Add onion; cook until onion is tender.
Add water, tomato paste, sauce mix and salt; stir until blended.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Stir pasta into sauce; spoon into 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese; broil 5 to 10 minutes until cheese is lightly browned. Makes 6 servings (1 cup each).

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan. Bring to full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 15 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: barbecued flank steak
directions: Combine all ingredients for marinade.
Add flank steak and marinate overnight.
Barbecue each side of flank steak 5 to 7 minutes over hot coals (or until cooked to your liking).
Happy eating!

title: barbecue onions
directions: Take several large onions and remove outer shell (the thin skin).
Remove center about 1/2 way down, place in foil.
Fill center to overflowing with barbecue sauce; seal with foil.
Cook on grill about 1 hour.

title: apple pandowdy
directions: Place sliced apples
in
bottom of baking dish.
Mix in sugar and cinnamon.
Pour
on the apple juice.
Dot the butter here and there.

title: border mix
directions: Stir taco mix into butter.
Combine all other ingredients in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; drizzle taco mixture over it and stir well. Bake 30 minutes at 275°, stirring occasionally.
Cool and store in an airtight container.
Makes 7 cups.

title: chicken lasagne
directions: Cook lasagne and drain.
Cook onion and green pepper in margarine until tender.
Stir in soup, mushrooms, pimento, milk and basil.
Lay 1/2 noodles in a 9 x 13-inch pan; top with 1/2 each of the soup mixture, cottage cheese, chicken, Parmesan and American cheeses.
Repeat layers except the American and Parmesan cheeses. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Top with remaining cheese and bake a few minutes more until cheese is melted.
Let sit 10 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in mixing bowl or blender.
Pour into 1/2 gallon ice cream freezer and add enough homogenized milk to fill to within 3-inches of the top.
Freeze in one part ice cream salt and six parts crushed ice.
For firmer ice cream, remove dasher and repack in salt and ice, wrapping freezer with heavy cloth, such as canvas.
Let stand 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine
broccoli,
pecans, raisins, bacon and onion in bowl. Mix
mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar in small bowl.
Pour over broccoli
mixture
and
mix
well.	Chill well and serve. Yields about 6 servings.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Prepare pudding according to directions on box.
After it has slightly set, add pineapple, about half of bag of marshmallows and container of whipped topping.
Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: murphy brown's sauce potatoes
directions: Let bacon, onion and bell pepper cook for a little while. Stir and mix in potatoes.
Put all in a big pot and put on top; let cook on low until all is tender.
Serve topped with cheese.

title: simple oven roasted vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Put veggies and all ingredients in a plastic bag.
Shake all together.
Put vegetables in shallow baking pan.
Bake 20 minutes, stirring once.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Stir milk and egg yolks together.
Then add lemon juice to mixture.
Pour into pie shell.

title: orange crunch cake
directions: In small bowl combine crunch layer ingredients until crumbly. Set aside.

title: dill pickles
directions: Place washed and speared cucumbers in quart canning jars.
Add 2 to 3 heads of dill in each quart jar; place 2 to 3 cloves in bottom of each jar.
Add a pinch of alum and a strip or ring of red pepper to each jar.
Bring vinegar, canning salt and water to a boil.
Make sure that all the salt dissolves.
Pour liquid over cukes in each jar up to 1 inch from the top.
Wipe rims.
Seal jars; place in a boiling water bath to cover tops by 1 inch. Continue to boil for 10 minutes.
Take out quickly; place jars upside down for 5 minutes.
Stand jars upright; let cool.

title: herbed chicken bake
directions: Grease a 2-quart dish.
Put in 4 chicken breasts.
Sprinkle stuffing mix over chicken.
Drizzle soft butter over stuffing. Pour orange juice over all.
Cover tightly and bake in oven at 350° about 1 hour.
Serve with wild rice.

title: beets in raisin sauce
directions: Drain beets and pineapple, reserving juices.
Put beets and pineapple in separate bowls; set aside.
Combine butter, sugar, flour and salt in a saucepan.
Gradually stir vinegar and reserved juices into saucepan mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Add raisins and pineapple.
Pour over beets. You may let stand for several hours for flavors to blend.
You can serve cold or heat before serving.

title: pumpkin pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into long pan.
Bake at 450° for 1 hour.

title: sausage potato soup
directions: Brown sausage, stirring to crumble.
Drain and set aside. Combine potatoes, onion, water and salt in a large Dutch oven. Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for about 25 minutes.
Slightly mash potatoes while cooking.
Add sausage, parsley and milk.
Heat well.

title: congealed waldorf salad
directions: Dissolve gelatine in 1/4 cup apple juice.
Heat 3/4 cup apple juice, 1 teaspoon lemon juice and pinch of salt.
Add to gelatine mixture.
Chill in refrigerator until consistency of egg white. Add apples, celery and pecans; chill until firm.

title: coconut-caramel pies
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet. Add coconut and chopped pecans; cook until golden brown, stirring frequently. Set the mixture aside. Combine cream cheese and sweetened condensed milk; beat until smooth. Fold in whipped topping.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread pizza pan very thin with 1/2 of sugar cookie batter. Bake until lightly brown; cool 5 to 10 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread over crust.
Arrange fruit on top of cheese layer and glaze with marmalade or jam to keep it from turning brown.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine sugar, margarine, syrup, salt and molasses in pan. Bring to boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Stir well.

title: great barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Add corned beef (crushed).
Add chili powder and brown sugar.
Simmer at least 1 hour.
(This freezes great!)
Serves 10 to 12.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well.
Shape into balls and brown in large skillet.
Remove meatballs.
Pour off fat.
Heat chili sauce and jelly.
Add meatballs.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: cloud nine
directions: Melt oleo.
Add flour and nuts.
Spread in a 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let crust get completely cold (not cool).

title: broccoli casserole(6 to 8 servings)
directions: Saute onion in 4 tablespoons butter until soft.
Add flour and water.
Blend until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Blend in Cheez Whiz; mix well.
Combine sauce and broccoli; add eggs. Mix gently until blended.
Turn into well-greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs; dot with remaining butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Saute onion and celery.
Cook rice according to package instructions.
When rice is done, put all ingredients together and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Saute onions.
Remove from heat. Stir in flour and spices.
Drain mushrooms, reserving liquid.
Add water to make 1/2 cup liquid.
Gradually stir into flour mixture. Blend in milk until smooth.
Add mushrooms and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens.

title: hershey's velvety chocolate cream pie
directions: Prepare pie shell; set aside.
Combine cocoa, sugar, cornstarch and salt in medium saucepan.
Gradually blend milk into dry ingredients, stirring until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils; boil and stir 3 minutes. Remove from heat; blend in butter and vanilla.
Pour into pastry shell; carefully press plastic wrap directly onto pie filling. Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Garnish with whipped topping and chocolate curls if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cool lime salad
directions: Place marshmallows, jello and sugar in a bowl.
Pour hot water over mixture and mix together to allow melting.
Allow to cool. Add softened cream cheese, pineapple and nuts and mix.
Add Cool Whip, then mix and chill.

title: lime pickles
directions: Pour the lime and water mixture over the cucumbers and leave 24 hours. Wash in cold water.
Leave for 3 more hours.
Combine the vinegar, salt, sugar and pickling spice.
Pour over cucumbers and cook 30 minutes, then can.

title: potato salad
directions: Wash potatoes.
Boil whole until done (done when potato skin begins to peel).
Drain.
Peel after cooking.
Dice onion, potatoes, pickles and eggs.
Add olives.
Mix in pickle juice, mayonnaise and mustard.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Allow to set approximately 1/2 hour before serving.

title: potato casserole
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Mix cream of mushroom soup, sour cream, cheese and onion together and pour over potatoes.
Top with 1 1/2 cups crushed cornflakes mixed with one stick melted butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pear salad
directions: On a large platter, arrange lettuce. Place pear slices. Sprinkle with cheese, walnuts and raspberries. Cover and refrigerate.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix rice, soups and milk. Pour into 9 x 13 pan. Place chicken on top. Sprinkle onions soup mix over all. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until rice is done.

title: sausage cheese muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in greased muffin pan. Bake in a 375° oven for approximately 20 minutes.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into meat balls.

title: fairyland sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, oil and sugars; beat well.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour along with baking soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Mix well.

title: rolls
directions: Melt butter, sugar and salt in hot water.
Add beaten egg. Melt yeast in warm water and add flour, 1 cup at a time, until a stiff dough is achieved.
Dump onto floured pastry cloth or board. Knead until elastic.
Put in bowl with little oil, turn to coat. Cover, let rise until doubled in size.
Knead to get air out. Make out into rolls.
Place on greased pans, brush with melted butter.
Let rise until doubled in size.
Bake at 450° until golden brown.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix oil and eggs.
Add Bisquick and mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients; pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top should be slightly brown.

title: creole baked fish
directions: Dress
and
split
fish.
Place in oiled pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Heat butter in pan and saute vegetables for five minutes.
Stir in thyme, lemon juice and water.
Pour over
fish. Mix
bread
crumbs, 1 tablespoon butter and lemon peel.
Sprinkle over fish.
Bake uncovered in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: green rice
directions: Cook rice and broccoli according to package directions.
Saute onion in margarine until soft.
Add soup, Cheez Whiz and almonds. Then add rice and broccoli.
Simple, easy and delicious.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Thaw and drain vegetables.
Mix soup and sour cream together. Add 2/3 cup of Swiss cheese and 1 can onions.
Mix with vegetables.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle rest of cheese and onions on top and bake 5 more minutes.

title: easy fudge
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients together in pan over medium to low heat.
Stir in nuts and spread in baking pan.
Refrigerate for about 3 hours.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Boil water, vinegar and salt.
Pour over jars filled with cucumbers.
Add dill and 1 clove garlic (while hot).
Add alum, size of a butter bean, to each quart jar.
Seal and process in hot water bath at least 5 minutes.

title: buttermilk pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Beat the eggs and sugar until mixed. Blend in the flour, buttermilk, butter, vanilla and salt.
Beat briefly until smooth.
Add the pecans and pour into the pie shell. Bake until done, about 30 minutes.
Serve hot or cool on a rack.

title: turkey meatballs
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Shape into 40 balls.
Brown 1/2 in 2 1/2 tablespoons oil in large skillet about 6 minutes.
Remove to a platter.
Brown remainder.
Saute mushrooms.
Add to meatballs.
Add broth, lemon juice, lemon rind and pepper.
Boil 1 to 2 minutes in skillet.
Serve on noodles or rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: low cholesterol dinner rolls
directions: In a large bowl of electric mixer, combine oil, sugar, salt and hot milk.
Mix well.
Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water (105° to 110°).
Let set 5 minutes.
Gradually add Egg Beaters, yeast and 2 1/2 cups flour.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed. Stir in enough remaining flour to make soft dough.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut butter into dry cake mix until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.
Reserve 1 cup mixture.
Pat remaining mixture lightly into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch oblong pan, building up 1/2-inch edge.
Spread pie filling over cake mixture to within 1/2-inch of pan edge.
Mix walnuts and the 1 cup reserved mixture; sprinkle over top.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes. Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: "shoney's" strawberry pie
directions: Cook pie crust as instructed.
Let cool.
Place strawberries in cool crust.
Cook sugar, water and starch until thick.
Add jello.
Mix well.
Cool before pouring over strawberries. Refrigerate.
Add Cool Whip before serving.

title: coconut cake
directions: Combine Crisco, salt and lemon rind.
Add sugar and cream until light.
Add beaten eggs; mix well.
Add flour and baking powder alternately with milk.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apple swirl bread(sugar-free --- great for diabetics)
directions: *Apple juice concentrate is usually frozen. Thaw and use.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: In a mixing bowl, toss the chicken with the dressing.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 to 24 hours.
Preheat oven to 450°. Pulverize the stuffing mix with a rolling pin or in a blender or food processor until finely ground.
Transfer to large plate or waxed paper.
Lift chicken from marinade and roll each piece into stuffing mix until well coated.
Arrange chicken pieces in a single layer in a non-stick baking dish or pan.
Bake for 50 minutes, until brown and crisp.

title: clam puffs on toast
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heap mixture on toast rounds and broil.
Serve hot.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, peas, grated Swiss cheese and onion rings. Cover with mayonnaise.
Sprinkle sugar over bowl.
Cover with sprinkled Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle with bacon.
Cover with foil and store in refrigerator overnight.
Bring to room temperature and mix to serve.

title: banana pudding
directions: Bring to boil milk, eggs and sugar, constantly stirring.
Add vanilla and remove from heat.
Allow to cool 30 minutes.

title: guacamole
directions: Mash avocados until smooth.
Add onions, salt, lemon juice and choice of chili powder or chopped chili, garlic salt and sour cream.
Mix together well.
Keep covered until serving time.

title: rumaki
directions: Bake livers at 300° for 10 minutes.
Cool and cut in halves. Combine soy sauce, ginger and sugar; marinate livers for 30 minutes.
Cut bacon in half or thirds and wrap around liver and water chestnuts and fasten with toothpicks.
Broil until bacon is crisp, 4 inches from broiler.
Makes approximately 3 dozen.

title: sour cream enchiladas(serves 12 to 16)
directions: Need 2 pans.
Mix together ingredients (not tortillas).
Put heaping teaspoonfuls into each tortilla, rolling up and placing into 2 (13 x 9-inch) loaf pans.
Cover with remaining mixture and cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: diabetic pineapple cake
directions: Mix ingredients together carefully.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 300° until cake tests done.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Mix sausage, cheese and onion; chill.
Beat eggs, mustard, half and half, salt and pepper.
Pour sausage mixture into unbaked pastry.
Pour egg mixture over sausage.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes, until egg is set.

title: sauteed turkey sausage(with peppers and herbs)
directions: Put the sausages into a medium size saucepan and cover with water.
Bring just to a boil, reduce the heat and simmer 8 minutes.
Remove the sausages from the water and cut into 1 inch slices.
Heat the olive oil over medium heat in a large nonstick skillet.
Add the sausage slices and saute for about 3 minutes, just until lightly browned.
Remove from the pan.
Add the garlic and onion to the pan, sauteing 3 minutes.
Add the bell peppers; saute 10 minutes.
Stir the sausages back into the pan with the salt, pepper, milk, basil and vinegar.
Stir 2 minutes and serve.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients thoroughly.
Add eggs, oil and milk and mix well.
Good served with maple syrup and milk.

title: banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions on box.
Blend in Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk and whip.
Add bananas and cookies to mixture.

title: swedish coffee cake
directions: Cream oleo, sugar, eggs and milk together.
Sift baking powder and baking soda.
Add
to
margarine
and sugar mixture alternately with buttermilk and vanilla.

title: mounds candy
directions: Mix well.
Shape into oblong flat pieces.
Chill.
Melt together 1/2 cake paraffin wax and 1 large package semi-sweet chocolate chips.
Dip candy pieces in chocolate mixture.
Place on waxed paper.,

title: dunbar macaroni
directions: Cook hamburger meat and onion in 1 cup of water until water is cooked away.
Add salt and pepper.
Add tomato juice and partly cooked macaroni.
Simmer until well done (30 to 45 minutes).
Pour into casserole dish and sprinkle grated cheese over the top while hot.
Ready to serve.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Cook in long casserole dish until brown on 450°.

title: beef sticks
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Divide into 3 portions.
Place each on 24-inch piece of foil; shape into 15-inch stick.
Seal foil around stick.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Bake, wrapped in foil, at 300° for 1 hour.
Yield: 3 beef sticks.

title: blueberry nut crunch
directions: Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch pan or dish and spread undrained, crushed pineapple in dish first.
Add a layer of blueberries and sprinkle with 1 cup sugar.
Sprinkle cake mix on top of the fruit. Drizzle melted butter over dry cake mix.
Top with nuts and add remaining 1/2 cup sugar on top.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for about 45 minutes.
After cake has baked 25 minutes, take a spoon and insert through the cake several times to permit juices to come up.

title: sausage and mushroom quiche
directions: Cook sausage and mushrooms.
(Can use other ingredients like cooked frozen broccoli pieces.)
Beat eggs with milk and cheese. Add salt and parsley.
Add sausage and mushrooms.
Pour into slightly baked pastry shell.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Add margarine to warm sweet potatoes.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes or until congealed.
Serve warm.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Microwave chocolate and margarine in glass bowl.
Combine all ingredients.
Beat with electric mixer on high for 4 minutes. Immediately pour into an unbaked small pie shell and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon biscuits coffee cake
directions: Grease a Bundt pan.
Sprinkle bottom with chopped nuts.
Take 1 biscuit at a time and dip it into butter, then into the sugar-cinnamon mixture, coating well.
Stand biscuits on their side around the pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: spicy steak
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Pound into steak.
Melt shortening in skillet and brown steak.
Place in a large casserole. Blend catsup and water.
Pour around steak. Add onion, lemon, green pepper and cloves. Cover tightly and bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: good peach pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, milk and baking powder together.
Dot bottom of a baking dish generously with margarine.
Pour batter into dish.
Add the juicy peaches by pouring over batter in dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
When baked, a light and fluffy cake-like batter will rise to top and peaches will be on bottom.

title: homemade minestrone soup
directions: Remove bone and fat from beef shanks.
Cut beef into 1-inch pieces.
Heat oil in Dutch oven over medium high heat.
Saute beef, garlic and onion until beef is light brown.
Stir in romaine, cabbage, potato and carrot.
Cook uncovered for 5 minutes, stirring frequently, until romaine is wilted.
Stir in remaining ingredients except rotini.
Heat to boiling, then reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 40 minutes.
Stir in rotini.
Add more water if needed. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes or until rotini is tender.
Remove bay leaf and serve!

title: dirt dessert
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat together the instant pudding, powdered sugar and milk.
Add the cream cheese and mix thoroughly. Fold in Cool Whip.
In a large planter, approximately 1 gallon size (with bottom covered with foil or wrap to block holes), place a layer of crushed Oreos, then a layer of pudding mixture.
Keep layering ending with cookie layer.
Be sure to reserve enough for the top layer to cover pudding totally.
Refrigerate.
Add flowers just before serving.
Choose flowers that are light in weight because the mixture won't support them upright otherwise.
Real or artificial flowers may be used.
Strip the stems and wrap in foil or wrap.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add garlic and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Serve with topping:
Crushed tortilla chips, grated cheese, sour cream, avocado, chopped green onions and shredded lettuce.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Mix in corn syrup, sugar, margarine, vanilla and salt.
Add nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes; then lower to 350° and continue baking for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: beef tomato swirls
directions: Combine meat, eggs, 1/2 can of soup, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Put onto wax paper to form a rectangle 15 x 8-inches.
Combine remaining ingredients and spread over meat. Roll up, using wax paper to lift.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch thick slices and place on greased baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Makes 10.

title: french dip sandwiches(yield: 12 servings)
directions: 1. Place trimmed roast in a 5-quart slow cooker.

title: garlic pickles
directions: Let cucumbers, garlic, onions and sweet peppers stand in ice water for 3 hours.
Then mix all ingredients together in one container and bring to a boil.
Pack in pint or quart jars.

title: j.p.'s barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Use more water for a thinner sauce, if desired.
Heat and simmer.
Makes about 3 cups.
Stores well in refrigerator.

title: frosted orange drink
directions: Mix all ingredients together in blender until smooth.
Kids enjoy this; it resembles an Orange Julius.

title: cornmeal-breaded catfish
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray.
On wax paper, mix yellow cornmeal, ground pepper and onion powder.
Pour milk into shallow bowl.
Dip catfish fillets, one at a time, into milk, then into cornmeal, lightly coating both sides and using all milk and cornmeal.
Place fillets on prepared baking sheet.
Drizzle each with 1/2 teaspoon olive oil.
Bake for 10 minutes, or until fish is cooked through.
Place under broiler for 1 minute to brown slightly.
Serve fillets with Creole sauce.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cut up 2 ounces cheese into hunks and set aside.
Grate other 6 ounces cheese and mix with 1 pound pork sausage and 1 1/2 cups Bisquick mix.
Knead well.
Set aside.
Slit and scrape seeds from each pepper (leave stems on peppers).
Rinse peppers and then stuff each with the 2 ounces cheese hunks. Separate dough into patties and form around peppers.
Make sure ends are closed and only stems are showing.
Beat eggs in a small bowl and set aside.
Spread coating mix on a plate.
Dip each coated pepper into egg and then roll into coating mix.
Bake on cookie sheet for 30 minutes but after 15 minutes flip each pepper. Makes 18 peppers.

title: noodles for soup
directions: Sift flour and salt together into a bowl.
Make a well in center of flour mixture and add eggs; blend thoroughly.
Knead dough on a floured surface; cover and let stand 30 minutes.

title: 3-cheese dip
directions: Alternate layers of cheese and chilies in greased casserole. Mix together milk, eggs and flour.
Pour over cheese and chilies. Bake at 350° until top is brown.
Good with vegetables or corn chips.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cut together sugar, flour and butter.
Set aside 1 cup of the mixture.
Into the remaining mixture sprinkle the soda, spices and unbeaten eggs; mix.
Stir in buttermilk.
Pour into ungreased square pan and sprinkle the remaining cup of reserved dry mixture evenly on top.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: broccoli cream soup
directions: Combine liquids; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer on low for 20 to 30 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: chocolate-peanut butter bars
directions: In mixing bowl, mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar, melted butter and peanut butter; spread on cookie sheet.
In saucepan on low heat, melt chips and margarine, stirring well to blend. Spread over top of peanut butter mixture.
Allow to cool and set. Cut into bars.

title: fancy franks
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Add franks and pineapple chunks.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve warm with picks. Yield: 10 servings.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix, batter and 2/3 cup of milk together.
Put 1/2 of batter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: fruit slush
directions: Boil water and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients; freeze.
Stir often while freezing.

title: fried eggs
directions: In a skillet over medium heat, melt a small dab of butter.
Add eggs; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
When whites are set and edges are cooked, add 1/2 teaspoon of water per egg.
Cover skillet; cook eggs for 2 minutes for soft or 4 minutes for firm.
For "over easy" eggs, carefully lift eggs with spatula and flip; cook briefly to set yolks.
Serves 2.

title: kentucky baked ham
directions: Wash ham carefully.
Lay in baking pan, skin side down.
Fill pan half full of hot water, adding molasses, cayenne pepper, vinegar and whole cloves.
Bake rather slowly, allowing 5 hours to a 16 pound ham.
Then skin, trim and dress with a paste made of yolk of egg made thick with equal proportions of brown sugar and mustard.
Bake to a light brown.

title: pie crust
directions: Put flour, salt and sugar into bowl; add vegetable shortening. Mix well until crumbly.
In small bowl, beat 1/2 cup water, vinegar and egg.
Combine two mixtures together.
Divide dough into four equal portions; shape into flat round patties.
Wrap in wax paper.
Chill for 1/2 hour.
Roll out on wax paper.

title: fruit pie
directions: Melt butter.
Beat eggs.
Add all together.
Pour into crust. Bake at 350° until set.

title: easy does it german chocolate cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine pecans and coconut.
Sprinkle in the bottom of pan.

title: sour cream stroganoff
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Cut meat in bite size pieces. Coat with flour mixture.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in pan and brown slowly on all sides.
Add to meat the onions, garlic powder, water, Worcestershire sauce, catsup and mushroom liquid.
Cover and simmer until meat is tender (about 2 hours).
Stir in mushrooms and sour cream.
Cook only until heated through.
Serve over noodles or buttered rice.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Drain all fruit except cherries.
Combine with rest of ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: apple bundles
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Unroll and separate crescent roll slices; cut each in half to make 16 triangle strips.
Place 3 to 4 apple slices at the wide end of each strip and roll up.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Mix orange juice, sugar, butter and cinnamon together, then pour into (not over) the Apple Bundles.

title: slow cooker spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown onions, if desired.
Add tomatoes, sausage and remaining ingredients.
Put in slow cooker, or you can simmer for 2 hours, until reduced to the thickness you want, stirring regularly.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Slice cookie dough and pat into 12-inch round pizza pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Cool.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in greased shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine dry ingredients; add melted butter, mixing until crumbly.
Sprinkle crumb mixture on top of apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 minute or until apples are tender.
Served warm or cold topped with milk or cream, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hot bologna
directions: *May use ring bologna if you prefer.

title: sour cream twists
directions: Cut Crisco into flour like for pie crust.
Add sour cream, eggs, salt and vanilla.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water; add 4 teaspoons sugar and mix well into stiff dough.
Put in refrigerator for 2 or 3 hours.
Roll out on sugared board.
Cut in strips and twist.
Bake in oven at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: zucchini bread (mom's)
directions: Mix zucchini, eggs and oil.
In large bowl, mix flour, sugar, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add zucchini mixture and stir enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Add vanilla. Pour into 2 (9 x 5-inch) greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour.

title: honduras chicken
directions: Cook chicken with next 7 ingredients. When almost done add peas & olives. Serve over cooked rice.

title: copper coins(carrots)
directions: Slice and cook carrots in salted water.
When cool, drain and alternate layers of carrots, pepper rings and onion rings in a 1 1/2-quart casserole or bowl of equal size.
Make marinade of remaining ingredients, blending well.
Pour over vegetables and refrigerate overnight.
Drain to serve.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: For the caramel sauce: Add butter to saucepan. As it starts to melt, add the corn syrup, then brown sugar. Cook on medium heat until all ingredients are well blended and begins to bubble. Do Not Boil. Pour mixture into a greased 9 x 13 inch casserole pan. Next, slice French bread 3/4 inch thick. Put one layer of bread on the caramel sauce side by side. Do not overlap. Smear all of the cream cheese on top of first layer of bread. Top with second layer of bread, placing each piece directly atop the last.

title: spiced applesauce salad
directions: Heat applesauce until hot, then dissolve Jell-O in it.
Add pop.
Use large bowl, as it foams.
Chill.

title: coq au vin
directions: Fry 6 strips of bacon in 3 tablespoons oil until crisp in large Dutch oven.
Remove bacon and crumble; set aside.
Meanwhile, cut up uncooked chicken into bite-size pieces or leave as breasts, legs, etc., but remove skin.
Combine flour, garlic salt, salt and pepper in bag.
Add chicken to bag and shake.
In bacon grease, cook onion, then add chicken and flour.
Stir and let chicken brown for about 10 minutes.
Add carrots, water, bouillon, wine and crumbled bacon, stirring frequently.
Bring to boil, then simmer, covered, until carrots are tender, 30 to 45 minutes.
Stir frequently.
It should thicken on its own.
Serve over rice.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Work together and chill.
Make small balls; put in muffin tin and "thumb out".

title: soft pretzels
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Let rise for 15 minutes.
Shape into pretzels.
Lay on a cookie sheet which has been greased. Let rise.
Mix cold water and baking soda; brush soda water over pretzels.
Sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 10 or more pretzels.

title: watkins country-style vanilla ice cream
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually add sugar; beat until thickened.
Add cream, vanilla and salt; mix thoroughly.
Pour into can.
Add milk to line on can; stir well. Follow your ice cream maker's instructions for proper freeze. Makes 4 quarts.

title: crockpot lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef, drain. Mix with spaghetti sauce. Layer in crockpot starting with noodles, the meat sauce, then the cheese. Repeat layers until pot is filled, with mozzarella being the last layer. Cook on low for 3-3 1/2 hours.

title: plantation okra
directions: Coarsely chop tomatoes.
Combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil in a heavy skillet; reduce heat, cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: the "best" chocolate cake
directions: Heat milk and cocoa.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, then cooled chocolate mixture, buttermilk with flour, soda, and baking powder sifted together and vanilla.
Bake in two 8 or 9-inch cake pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cover with Seven Minute Icing.

title: glazed wild duck
directions: Combine all ingredients except duck and onions to form glaze. Pour over duck.
Place onion rings over duck and roast in shallow pan at 400° for 1 hour.
Baste often.
Season to taste.
Serves 2 to 4.
Preparation Time:
1 hour.

title: venison roast
directions: Prepare marinade of 1/2 cup vinegar, 2 cloves garlic, 2 tablespoons salt and cold over to cover roast.
Allow roast to marinate overnight.
Pat dry.
Roll in flour and brown in skillet. Place in slow cooker; add remaining ingredients and cook on high for 2 hours.
Turn to low and cook for 8 to 10 hours.

title: swedish meatballs(serves 6)
directions: Heat milk; do not boil.
In separate bowl combine beef, onion and spices.
Add flour slowly, blending thoroughly.
Gradually mix in milk.
Add eggs and beat until mixture is light and puffy, about 5 minutes.
Cover and refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Then roll beef in 1-inch balls.
Brown meatballs under broiler.
Remove; set aside.
Add 4 tablespoons of flour to broiler beef drippings and stir until smooth.
Gradually stir in beef stock and sherry; bring to boil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add meatballs to sauce.
Simmer, gently covered, for 15 minutes. Place in serving dish.

title: gold carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots until tender; drain and cool. Layer carrots, onion and pepper in alternate layers in a deep bowl. Mix together the rest of the ingredients. Pour over vegetables. Marinate for 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: fisherman's stew
directions: Mix the ground beef, bread crumbs, eggs, onion, salt and pepper well. Shape into small balls.
Brown in oil.
Add to the remaining ingredients. Simmer 45 to 60 minutes.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Cook raisins until soft; set aside.
Cream sugar and oleo; add eggs.
Dissolve soda in hot juice and add to sugar mixture.
Add dry ingredients and cooked raisins.
Drop on ungreased pan about 3 inches apart.
Bake at 450° about 7 minutes.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: Cut up cabbage.
In skillet, cook cabbage slowly with 1 cup of water.
When cabbage is tender, add oleo.
Cook noodles separately; drain.
Add to cabbage.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: okra fritters
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients; stir in okra.
Pour oil to depth of 2 inches into a Dutch oven; heat to 350°.
Drop mixture by tablespoonfuls into oil and cook until golden brown, turning once. Drain on paper towels.
Sprinkle with salt and serve immediately. Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: deviled hamburgers
directions: Combine ground beef, ketchup, worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Split rolls and toast uncut surface under broiler.
Spread the cut sides with the meat mixture.
Return to the broiler and broil about 6 minutes, having meat surface about 3 inches from heating unit.

title: sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Wash sweet potatoes and pierce several times with fork.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 1 hour or until fork pierces them easily.
Cool.
Peel apples and slice thinly.
Skin potatoes and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Grease casserole dish with shortening or butter.
Cover bottom of dish with half of potato slices.
Put half of apple slices on top of potatoes.
Add remaining potatoes.
Top with remaining apples.
Dot with butter.
Pour maple syrup over top.
Cover casserole and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beating well after each addition.
Mix 2 1/2 cups flour, cinnamon and soda together.
Add to mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Mix 1/2 cup flour with the fruit and nuts.
Add to the batter.
Drop from spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in slow 275° oven for 20 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Boil hamburger.
Drain; add remaining ingredients.
Add as much sugar as you like. Simmer for about 20 minutes.

title: hollandaise sauce
directions: Place the yolks in a stainless steel bowl and place over low heat, stirring constantly, until the yolks are thick and creamy. Remove the yolks from heat and slowly stir in the clarified butter, stirring vigorously.
Add the lemon juice, salt and cayenne pepper.
Hold the sauce in a warm place until needed.

title: german chocolate pie(in honor of ralph wilfong)
directions: Over medium heat, prepare the chocolate pudding mix according to directions on the package box.
When nearly thickened, pour in the box of dry frosting mix.
Stir until well mixed.
Remove from stove.
Pour into baked pie shell.
One can either prepare one's favorite meringue to top with and bake until meringue is lightly browned, or one can serve with a spoon of whipped cream on each slice of pie.
I prefer either sweetened whipped cream, Cool Whip or Reddi-Wip, to a topping of meringue.

title: easiest ever cocoa fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, butter and milk in a microwave bowl. Cook on high for 2-3 minutes or until butter in melted.
Stir until mixture is smooth.
Stir in the vanilla, blend well.
Spread in buttered 8-inch square pan; cool.
Cut into 1" squares.
Makes about 5 dozen pieces.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg onto wax paper.
Combine raisins and water in a small saucepan.
Bring to boiling.
Remove from heat. Cover. Cool to room temperature.
Beat shortening and sugar well. Beat in eggs and vanilla. Blend flour mixture into shortening mixture until smooth. Add cooled raisins and liquid and oats.
Mix well. Cover bowl. Chill at least 1 hour.

title: apple cranberry salad toss
directions: Toss salad greens, apples, walnuts, cranberries and onions in large salad bowl.
Add dressing, toss to coat.
Serve immediately.

title: easy ice cream
directions: Beat eggs and sugar well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly and freeze in an ice cream freezer.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: banana muffins(low-fat)
directions: Spray 12 muffin cups with a nonfat cooking spray.
In a medium bowl combine flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
In a large bowl, using a wire whisk, beat egg substitute.
Stir in mashed bananas, milk and corn syrup.
Add flour mixture.
Stir until blended.
Spoon into muffin cups. Bake at 400° for 22 to 25 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes in pan.

title: super pie crust
directions: Blend flour, salt and shortening.
Add vinegar, cold water and egg.
Mix well.
Chill.

title: easy chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken in large pot. Drain some of the water, leaving about 3 cups in the pot. Remove chicken and let cool. Pull apart into bite-size pieces and return to pot. Reduce heat and add cans of soup. Stir into mixture. Quarter the biscuits and roll into tiny balls. Drop into soup. Continue simmering over medium heat until the dough balls are cooked through. (Do not overcook.)

title: sweet icicle pickles
directions: Put cucumber strips in a stone jar or stainless steel container.
Add salt to boiling water.
Pour over cucumbers. Cover with plate. Fill quart jar with water and use to hold plate under brine.
Cover with cloth and let stand for 1 week (cool place).
Remove scum daily.

title: apple dip
directions: Beat 2 minutes with electric mixer.
Tart apples are best.

title: no-bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine in a saucepan.
Bring to boil and remove from heat.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal. Stir until well mixed.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Cool and serve.

title: orange cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400 for 12-15 minutes.
Cool and ice with a mixture of powdered sugar, orange rind and juice.
Make consistency your choice.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, then hot water.
Add sifted flour and soda.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Stir in oatmeal, chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop by teaspoon on slightly greased cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain the beans and mix with the pepper and onion. Set aside and mix the rest of the ingredients very well.
Mix everything together in one bowl and refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: choco peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat brown sugar, peanut butter and butter until fluffy. Blend in water, egg and vanilla.
Add oatmeal, flour and soda. Mix well.
Cover and chill 1 hour.
Shape in 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Using bottom of glass dipped in sugar, press into circles.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips in oil, mixing until smooth.
Top each cookie with 1/2 teaspoon chocolate.
Sprinkle with peanuts.

title: crock-pot meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together in small bowl.
Shape mixture into round loaf to fit crock-pot.
Place in foil-lined crock-pot. Place 1/3 cup of water under foil to keep meat loaf moist while cooking.
Cook at low setting (2) for 4 to 5 hours.

title: toasted sausage bites
directions: Remove crusts from bread. Mix horseradish and mustard together; spoon on bread and cut each slice in half. Cut sausage in half crosswise. Fold bread slices around each sausage. Fasten with toothpicks. Place in shallow pan. Brush with melted butter. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. These can be frozen before baking.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together; put in greased casserole.
Top with grated cheese and the can of water chestnuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: file gumbo
directions: In large pot cover the bottom with cooking oil.
Add flour little by little (over medium heat) to make a smooth roux.
Stir constantly until brown; add seasonings and meat.
Simmer and add water to cover completely.
Cook, covered, for about 1 1/2 hours. Add salt, pepper and file seasoning.
Cook another hour.
Serve over rice.

title: fettuccine with ham and peas
directions: Saut garlic in 1 tablespoon butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Stir in shredded ham and peas.
Saut over medium heat 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; cover and keep warm.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In heavy sauce pan, over medium heat, bring to boil sugar, corn syrup, salt and 1/4 c. water, stirring frequently until it reaches 300°.
Remove from heat and quickly stir in butter and baking soda.
Immediately pour onto greased cookie sheet.
With two forks, lift and pull peanut brittle mixture into about 14 x 12 inch rectangle.
Cool.
With hand shape candy into pieces.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: In a small bowl, whip together mayonnaise and salad dressing. Layer above ingredients in bowl.
Pour mixed dressing over layers. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with plastic wrap. Refrigerate and toss just before serving.
Serves 8.

title: pastie
directions: Chop or cube potatoes, carrots, onions and rutabaga.
Mix all ingredients well with hands.
Use own pie crust recipe for double crust pie (10-inch pie pan).
Put mixed ingredients into pie crust; vent top of crust.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pie crust
directions: Put flour, Crisco and salt in a large bowl and, using two knives, cut the Crisco up into small pieces.
In another bowl, beat the egg.
Add the ice water and vinegar and mix well.
Then add the mixture to the flour and Crisco.
Blend together well. This makes four single crust or two double crusts.

title: orange rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Add orange juice and next 4 ingredients; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until well blended.
Gradually add 3/4 cup flour, beating 2 minutes at medium speed.
Gradually stir in enough remaining 3 3/4 cups flour to make soft dough.

title: lasagna shortcut style
directions: Brown meat slowly, spoon off excess fat.
Add the four ingredients. Cover and simmer 40 minutes, stirring occasionally. Salt to taste.
Cook noodles in boiling salt water until tender. Drain and rinse in cold water.
Place half the noodles in an 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Cover with 1/3 of the sauce, add 1/2 the Mozzarella, then 1/2 the cottage cheese. Repeat layers, ending with sauce.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Combine mayonnaise, milk and sugar first.
Add remaining ingredients (except dressing) and pour into greased dish.
Top with Pepperidge Farm dressing.
Bake, uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: torte
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts and apples.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Top with 1 tablespoon whipped topping.
Yield:
15 servings.
Carbohydrate 64 g, protein 5 g, fat 13 g, calories 393.
One serving = 2 bread exchange, 3 fruit exchange, 2 1/2 fat exchange.

title: rolled rib roast of beef
directions: Select a boned and rolled rib roast or a boneless rib eye roast.
Sprinkle with salt (garlic flavored optional) and cracked pepper.
Place fat side up on rack in shallow roasting pan. Insert meat thermometer into center of roast.
Do not add water. Roast uncovered in a slow oven (325°) to desired doneness.
Allow 30 to 32 minutes per pound for rare beef.
Allow 34 to 37 minutes per pound for medium; and 39 to 42 minutes per pound for well done.

title: easy sponge cake
directions: Combine eggs and sugar; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake in 9 x 9-inch pan or comparable oblong pan.
Makes a good batter for upside-down cakes and shortcakes.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick butter, mix with crushed graham crackers.
Pack into oblong pan.
Mix not less than 15 minutes the following ingredients, eggs, 2 sticks margarine (not melted) and powdered sugar; after mixing pour this over the crust.
Cover with sliced bananas, drained pineapple and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts, decorate with cherries.

title: potato and onion pancakes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Peel and chop onion.
Shred potatoes hair fine julienne.
Drain well on towel.
Mix potatoes, onion and cheese. Add salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Heat part of butter in a pan. Spread and press part of mixture into pan in a thin layer.
Cook until bottom is browned.
Loosen edges with spatula as you would with a pancake.
Turn and brown the other side.
Repeat with remaining mixture.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Remove shells and devein shrimp.
Rinse well and drain on paper towels.
Melt butter in oblong baking dish.
Add garlic and 1 tablespoon parsley.
Mix well.
Add shrimp in single layer.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Turn shrimp and sprinkle with lemon peel, juice and remaining parsley.
Bake 5 minutes more or until pink.
Overcooking will toughen.
To serve, garnish with lemon wedges.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together; add shrimp.
Serve with chips.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken until cooked.
Boil broccoli until tender.
Mix cans of soup undiluted with 1 cup of mayonnaise; mix well.
When chicken is done, debone and arrange in baking pan.
Layer broccoli spears on top of chicken.
Pour soup and mayonnaise mixture over top of chicken and broccoli.
Combine bread crumbs with butter and layer next.
Sprinkle cheese as last layer.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, butter and milk.
Bring to a rolling boil and cook no longer than 1 minute.
Remove from stove and add crunchy peanut butter and vanilla. Stir until dissolved.
Add oatmeal (uncooked) and drop on wax paper.

title: meatball-spinach soup
directions: Mix meat, egg, crumbs, onion, parsley, cheese and salt.
Make very small (1 bite) meatballs and saute in skillet or in the microwave on bacon rack for 4 minutes; drain fat.
Freeze half for soup next time.

title: zucchini pizza
directions: Mix well; spread in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in preheated 350° oven until golden brown.
Cut and serve bite size pieces or larger.

title: tea time tassies
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Spoon into muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 18 minutes.

title: carrot and zucchini muffins
directions: In large bowl, mix flour, sugar, wheat germ, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Beat egg; add vanilla, raisins and nuts to flour mixture and veggies with the milk.
Mix until flour is moistened. Spoon into muffin pans.
Bake about 25 minutes in a 350° oven. Makes about 18 muffins.

title: chicken
directions: Coat chicken with flour mixture. Cook 10 minutes or until brown. Remove from skillet.
Spoon off fat.
Combine soup and water.
Heat to boiling. Return chicken to skillet and cook until done, stirring occasionally.

title: plantation pralines
directions: Combine sugar, cream of tartar, salt and milk.	Stir over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Cook until soft ball stage.
Cool. Add butter or oleo, vanilla and pecans.
Beat until creamy.
Drop from large spoon onto buttered surface or waxed paper.
Yield 1 1/2-2 dozen.
Very good.

title: 3 bean bake with chili biscuits
directions: Mix beef, onion, brown sugar, catsup, mustard and beans in an ungreased 3-quart casserole.
Cover and bake in a 375° oven until bubbly, about 45 minutes.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into buttered 2-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook
macaroni	and
drain.
Hard boil the eggs.
Smash egg yolks.
Add sugar, vinegar, mayonnaise and mustard.
Chop egg whites and chopped celery.	Add to macaroni.

title: pear dessert(bavarian tart)
directions: Cream together.
Pour over crust and put thinly sliced pears on top of mixture.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Top with cinnamon and sugar when it comes out.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Mix first six ingredients until well blended.
Stir in cheese, spinach and onion.
Pour into lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: dessert in bloom(better known as dirt dessert or dirt cake)
directions: You will also need an 8-inch clean clay or plastic flowerpot.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats; let stand.
Sift together cinnamon, salt, sugars, oil and eggs.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Raisins and nuts may be added if desired.

title: cream cheese danish
directions: Spray 11 x 14 inch glass cake pan with Pam.
Spread out one package of rolls in bottom of pan.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla, sugar, and egg yolk with mixer until smooth.
Spread over crescent rolls.
Place 2nd package of rolls on top of mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.

title: homemade bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and add shortening, sugar, salt, egg and 3 cups flour.
Mix until smooth.
Add remaining flour, mixing with a spoon.
Let it rise until it doubles in size.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into well greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: plum cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: jiffy corn bread casserole
directions: Mix together ingredients and put in baking dish.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease pan.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: pasta con broccoli
directions: Cut broccoli into bite sized pieces.
Slice mushrooms. Combine butter, garlic, mushrooms and half and half into saucepan. Simmer 10 minutes.
Add broccoli and bring to a boil.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together, press into spring-form pan.
