Reserve 3 tablespoons crust crumbs for topping.

title: cool and creamy fruit salad
directions: Combine cream cheese, juice and rind, mixing until well blended.
Add Cool Whip; then chill.
Layer fruit in a 2 1/2-quart bowl.
Spoon cream cheese mixture over fruit; sprinkle with nuts. Chill.
Tastes really good!

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Grease ovenproof dish.
Arrange zucchini, tomatoes and onions. Cover with cheese.
Mix eggs, Bisquick and milk.
Pour over vegetable mixture.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Scald milk and set aside.
Combine dry ingredients and beat in egg yolks.
Gradually add the scalded milk to the mixture.
Pour over vanilla wafers and bananas layered in bowl.

title: hot mocha sauce
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter and chocolate.
Stir in coffee, corn syrup, sugar and salt.
Bring the mixture to a boil.
Boil the sauce gently, without stirring, until thick and smooth, about 10 minutes.
Stir in vanilla.
Serve hot over ice cream, cheesecake or pound cake.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Cream together butter, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes. These will have soft centers when taken from oven.
Will be chewy when cool.
Bake at 350°.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; cover and refrigerate.
Spread over cream cheese; serve with assorted crackers.
Also good with meatballs, sliced ham or sausage.
Yields 3 1/2 cups.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Mix and cook 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburger and drain grease.
Add spaghetti sauce to hamburger in skillet.
Add corn and green beans to mixture and simmer for about 10 minutes.
Pour hamburger mixture into large oven safe casserole dish (deep).
Spread mashed potatoes over the top of the hamburger mixture until all the mixture is covered. Bake Shepherds Pie, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until mashed potatoes are brown on top.
Add cheese after cooking if desired.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat until mixed well.
Fold in crushed Ritz crackers and chopped pecans.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 10-inch pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Spread with well-drained strawberries.
Top with 1/2 pint Cool Whip.
Chill and serve.

title: quick party pitcher
directions: In a large pitcher, combine limeade, apple juice and water. Shake vigorously.
Put crushed ice in glasses.
Pour in mixture. Top with maraschino cherries.
Serves 6.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix together with frozen strawberries; then add Jell-O.
Then add oil and eggs.
Bake in a Bundt pan at 350°.
Put frozen strawberries in powdered sugar and pour over cake.

title: cream cheese potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Place in greased casserole.
Refrigerate all day or overnight.

title: filet of beef cabernet(for four)
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Season tenderloin with the spice mix and let stand at least 2 hours.
Heat oil in a large saute pan or skillet.
Brown the medallions on both sides and remove.
Add mushrooms and shallot and saute until tender.
Replace the beef. Deglaze the pan with wine.
Reduce wine by half.
Remove the beef and finish the sauce with heavy cream.
Return to the boil; simmer two minutes and serve.

title: chocolate chip kiss cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees.
Remove wrappers from Hershey's kisses.
Beat butter, granulated sugar, brown sugar and vanilla in large bowl until well blended.
Add flour to mixture, stir in semi-sweet chips.
Mold scant tablespoon dough around each Hershey's kisses covering completely shape into balls.
Place on ungreased baking pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, cool slightly. Remove from pan, cool completely, drip Hershey's chocolate over cookies.
About 4 dozen.

title: chinese chicken and rice
directions: Melt butter in heavy skillet.
Add onions and mushroom soup. Cook until golden.
Pour in chicken broth and heat to boiling. Stir in rice, cover and simmer gently for 10 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients, cover and cook for
10 to 15 minutes or more.

title: roman bread
directions: Place onions, peppers and tomatoes on the garlic roll (half). Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Serve with spaghetti or linguini.

title: fish kebabs
directions: Use wooden or metal skewers.
If using wooden skewers, place them in water for 30 to 60 minutes to prevent them from burning. Brush skewers with oil.
Alternately thread fish, pineapple, onion and red and green peppers on skewers.
Brush with oil.
Place on hot grill and turn several times during cooking, until fish is done and vegetables are crisp-tender.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine all ingredients but the soda and popcorn; boil 5 minutes.
Mix in the soda and pour mixture over popcorn that
is on a cookie sheet.
Bake for 1 hour at 250°.
Stir occasionally.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix
Cool Whip, pineapple and cottage cheese.
Sprinkle dry jello and stir; mix well.
Chill.

title: new south easy delight
directions: Prepare one box of vanilla instant pudding according to directions.
Let thicken.
Add one 8 oz. carton of Cool-Whip, mix well.

title: peach-mandarin whip
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender. Blend until frothy.
Serve immediately in tall glasses over crushed ice or chill well and serve in dessert cups.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Add ingredients to rice and water.
Mix together.
Put in lightly greased baking dish.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: eggplant lasagna
directions: Prepare spaghetti sauce and set aside.
Cook lasagna noodles as label directs; drain.
On wax paper, combine crumbs, pepper and salt.
In small dish with fork, beat eggs with water.
Dip eggplant into egg mixture, then crumb mixture.

title: chunky vegetable spaghetti(a favorite of mary sue and bruce lambert)
directions: Chop in large bite size pieces the zucchini, yellow squash, green peppers, onions, sweet red pepper and mushrooms.
Chop in small
pieces the celery.
Heat the onions, celery and green peppers in large deep skillet; add the stewed tomatoes (drained). Simmer until vegetables are hot.
Add the zucchini, yellow squash, sweet red pepper, mushrooms, oregano and garlic salt (powder) to taste.
Simmer until vegetables are cooked but still crunchy.
Add the spaghetti sauce and heat until hot.
Serve over the spaghetti (pasta) with grated cheese on top.

title: mystery cake
directions: Sift the first 4 ingredients together.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 13 x
9-inch pan. Sprinkle 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup chopped nuts over top. Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: baked fudge
directions: Blend cocoa, flour and sugar. Add eggs and blend. Pour in 9 x 9 pan. Place pan in larger pan filled with 1 to 1 1/2-inches of hot water. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
(It will get real brown.) Cool in pan.
Frost with Pineapple Cake Frosting.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate for one hour before serving.

title: andrew's party chicken
directions: Arrange cooked chicken or turkey in baking dish and top with cooked broccoli.
If fresh broccoli is used, separate it.
Mix flour, salt, pepper and mayo in saucepan and gradually blend in broth and milk.
Stir constantly over low heat until thickened. Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle top with paprika and dill weed.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: I soak yeast in 1 cup warm water.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat eggs and mix with oil.
Add dry ingredients and mix together.
Blend in grated carrots.
Add nuts and orange.
(Cut orange in half and take pits and center out.
Cut orange in chunks and pulverize in blender, skin and all.)
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Top with 1 cup of crushed corn flakes, buttered, the last 3 minutes of cooking time.
Can be frozen.

title: cracker cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place a layer of saltine crackers on a foil-lined cookie sheet.
In a saucepan, melt butter and brown sugar.
Bring to a boil; boil for 3 minutes only.
Spread over crackers.
Bake for only 5 minutes at 400°.

title: candy bar pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake pie crust for 5 to 7 minutes or until very light golden brown.
Remove from oven and let cool. Reduce oven temperature to 325°.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix hamburger, bread crumbs, onion, soup and eggs as for meat loaf.
Make into patties; dip in flour and brown on each side. Arrange in a greased baking dish.
Mix celery soup, tomato soup and water.
Pour over the patties and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Drain fruit cocktail; mix rest of ingredients.
Let set in refrigerator several hours or overnight before serving.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt butter in a pan over hot water, add sugar and beat.
Add eggs one at a time.
Then add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes then 350° for 35 minutes.

title: microwave chocolate pie
directions: Place in large microwave-safe bowl. Cook ingredients at 3 minute intervals until thick. It will take around 9 or 10 minutes. Whip batter in between each interval. When batter is ready, put into a baked pie shell.

title: haroset
directions: Grind hazelnuts with walnuts and sugar in a food processor fitted with a metal blade.
Grind until fairly fine, leaving a few small chunks.
Transfer to a bowl.
Chop apples fine in food processor; add to nut mixture.
Stir in wine, orange juice and grated rind.
Spoon into a bowl.
Serve at room temperature or chilled, accompanied by matzos.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pear cake
directions: Combine sugar, eggs and oil.
Beat well after each addition. Stir in vanilla and pears.
Bake in tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from pan and allow to cool.
Glaze with 1 1/2 cups powdered sugar mixed with 2 to 4 tablespoons milk.

title: snowflake cookies
directions: Mix oleo, sugar, eggs and almond extract.
Add flour, dry milk, potato flakes and baking powder alternately with the milk.
Mix well.
Drop by tablespoon about 2 inches apart onto cookie sheet and flatten slightly.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes until very lightly browned.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions, adding salt and onions to water.
When spinach is cooked, pour off most of excess water and add cream cheese to spinach.
Heat, stirring, until cheese melts.
Cover pan and let stand a few minutes, then serve. Serves 4.

title: cranberry loaf
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix egg and milk or orange juice.
Mix liquid with dry ingredients only until well moistened. Stir in 1 cup fresh cranberries, sliced in halves and nuts.
Bake in greased loaf pan about 1 hour, until toothpick comes out clean.

title: mom's rolls(yields 24 rolls)
directions: In a large bowl, combine sugar, salt and Crisco.
Pour boiling water in bowl and stir until dissolved.
Cool mixture.
In measuring cup of warm water, add dry yeast and dissolve.
Pour into cooled Crisco mixture.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time.
Rub top of mixture with Crisco and cover.
Set in refrigerator to raise at least 4 to 6 hours (I leave it overnight).
Punch down and let raise again in a warm place.
Shape into 24 rolls and bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Butter the tops.
Dough may be stored in refrigerator 4 to 5 days and used as needed.

title: cornmeal pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Beat egg and buttermilk together.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Blend well.
Add molasses and butter.
Bake on hot griddle.
Makes about 8 servings.
Batter will be thick.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, sugar, salt, eggs, milk, margarine and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish.

title: corn scallop
directions: Mix corn, eggs, milk and flour together.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and crackers and dot with margarine.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
This is done when knife inserted comes out clean.

title: sausage-lentil soup
directions: Remove sausage from casing; chop.
In Dutch oven, brown sausage; drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients except mustard. Simmer, covered, 1 hour or until lentils are soft.
Stir in mustard.
Remove and discard bay leaf before serving.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry and drain the bacon, hamburger and onion.
Mix all ingredients together and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry dream dessert
directions: Combine graham crackers, sugar and butter; put in bottom of a 12 x 8-inch glass pan.
Combine in a separate bowl the eggs, cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar.
Spread over graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until custard is solid.
Cool.
Pour blueberry topping over custard.
Spread whipped cream over blueberry filling.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs on the top (if desired).
Chill.

title: bologna biscuits with vegetables
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
In large skillet, cook onion in shortening until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in tomatoes.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly. Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in bologna, carrots and beans.
Heat to boiling. Pour into 8 x8
x 2-inch ungreased baking pan.
Drop 8 or 9 tablespoons of biscuit dough onto hot vegetables.
Bake, uncovered, 25 to 30 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown. Serves 5.

title: icing in the cake(german chocolate)
directions: This one won't crawl. Put everything in mixing bowl and blend on low 1 minute. Then beat on medium 2 minutes. Pour into 12-cup Bundt pan sprayed with Pam. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes. Cool in pan 20 minutes, then remove and put on a rack to cool completely. Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Blend cheese and butter.
Add flour, then nuts and pepper. Roll into a log 1-inch in diameter and chill until firm.
Slice onto a cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: fudge
directions: Place butter, chocolate, vanilla and nuts into a large bowl. In a large saucepan, place sugar and evaporated milk; bring to a full rolling boil and continue to boil for 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from stove and pour over chocolate mixture. Stir until margarine and chocolate dissolve, then pour into a large greased platter or pan.
Set aside or put in refrigerator until firm enough to cut into small squares.
Makes 5 pounds.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans and rinse with cold water.
Add sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper to mixture.
Mix and let stand several hours before serving.

title: incredibly easy cherry crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine cake mix and butter.
Using 2 knives, cut over and over until mixture is coarse and crumbly.
Press mixture to bottom and halfway up sides of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan, reserving about 1/4.

title: tomato sage chicken
directions: Saute chicken with garlic and onions until chicken is brown and onions are soft.
Add chicken stock and white wine.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, balsamic vinegar and sage.
Cover partially and simmer over medium heat, stirring occasionally for 30 minutes.
Uncover and cook 5 to 10 minutes if sauce needs to thicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: homemade macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix all ingredients, reserving 6 slices of cheese.
Pour into a lightly greased casserole dish. Top with reserved cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and milk is about gone.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cut up squash and boil with 1/2 of onion until tender.
Drain. Mix squash, soup and remainder of onion. Add 1 cup stuffing and mix. Pour into casserole dish.
Mix other cup of stuffing with butter and sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Bake until almost done and then add cheese and top and cook until melted.

title: et's hamburger soup
directions: In
a
large pan add Ranch Style beans, tomatoes, cubed potatoes
and
onions.
Cook
to boiling; continue to boil and add frozen
meat
to
mixture.
Continue
to boil rapidly and flake off with a fork as it browns.
When meat is all browned, soup will be ready.
With cornbread, it makes a complete meal.

title: bird's nest clusters
directions: Place chocolate chips and peanut butter in pan.
Heat until chocolate chips are completely melted.
Add the chow mein noodles. Mix the noodles by using one or two forks or spoons as though you were tossing a salad to get them evenly coated.
Lay a piece of waxed paper over two cookie sheets.
Drop golf ball size clusters on the covered cookie sheets to cool and set.
Add a few colored candies as eggs in the nests.

title: date filled cookies
directions: Boil 1 minute and cool.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in deep casserole in oven.
In bowl, mix flour, sugar, cinnamon and milk.
Pour batter over melted margarine in casserole.
Spoon peaches, with juice, evenly over batter.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: brownie cupcakes
directions: Combine chocolate and butter in saucepan.
Cook over low heat; stir constantly, until melted.
Cool.
Combine sugar, flour, eggs and vanilla in large bowl.
Add chocolate mixture.
Stir until smooth.
Spoon batter into paper-lined muffin pans.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: blueberry cheese bars
directions: Combine flour and brown sugar.
Cut in margarine until fine crumbs form.
Add 1/2 cup finely chopped nuts and coconut.
Remove 1/2 cup and set aside.
Press remaining crumbs in bottom of greased 13x9 pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 12-15 minutes.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla in small bowl until smooth. Spread over hot baked crust.
Return to oven and bake 15 minutes longer.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and add water gradually.
Stir in blueberries and mix until thickened.
Spread over cream cheese. Sprinkle reserved crumbs over top.
Bake an additional 10-15 minutes.

title: ice cream biscuits
directions: Cut each biscuit round in half. Place in greased 9x13 pan curved side up. Boil first 4 ingredients for 5 minutes & pour over biscuits. Bake 450 for 8-10 min.
May be served as a breakfast treat.
Best served warm, but may be served later.

title: pitcher punch(serves 8)
directions: Mix all in large pitcher.
Float orange slices on top if desired.

title: apple pizza
directions: Bake a sugar cookie dough on a pizza pan.
Mix together the above ingredients.
Spread mixture over cooled cookie dough.

title: two minute fudge
directions: Put ingredients into microwave-safe mixing bowl.
Cover and microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Remove mixture and beat until smooth.
Pour into buttered dish.
Let cool and cut into serving pieces.

title: crunchy coleslaw
directions: Toss cabbage, green pepper, onion and carrot in large bowl. Blend oil, vinegar, sugar, salt, mustard and pepper in a jar. Shake well to blend.
Pour over greens and toss to coat.
Cover and place in the refrigerator overnight to blend flavors.

title: harvest potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle on top 1 cup corn flake crumbs or cracker crumbs mixed with 3 tablespoons melted oleo.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: salt substitute
directions: Mix together and put into a big hole shaker.

title: sweet beer bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar and beer together and pour into a lightly greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
Pour melted butter over loaf and return to oven for an additional 10 minutes.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Using a food processor cut cheese and pimento with slicer disk.
Exchange blade to steel blade and mix rest of ingredients until right for spreading.
Will refrigerate for several weeks. This can be made by mashing with a fork.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Fry pork chops in small amount of grease real fast until they are brown on both sides.
Put the rice in bottom of a large casserole dish.
Begin layer of onions (slice round) and a layer of bell peppers.
Lay the browned pork chops on top and layer with the onions and bell peppers on top.
Add the soup and water.
Cook in oven, covered with tinfoil, for 1 hour.

title: refreshing punch slush
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar in boiling water.
Add cold water and juices.
Place in clean milk cartons or plastic soft drink bottles, leaving room for expansion when frozen.
Place in freezer for at least 8 hours.

title: ice coffee
directions: Pour coffee in glass.
Add milk and sugar.
Then add cubes of ice.
Make ice cold.
So refreshing.

title: salmon patties
directions: Open can of salmon and take out bones.
Put in bowl and add flour, meal, salt and onions.
Add just enough water to mix up good.
Make patties and fry in hot cooking oil until brown.
Drain on paper towel to get off excess oil.

title: pineapple yum yum cake
directions: Bake yellow cake mix in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool cake.
Blend in vanilla instant pudding with 1 1/2 cups milk; add this to cream cheese and 1/2 cup of milk.
Add large can of crushed pineapple, drained and spread on cake.
Spread Cool Whip on top of that and sprinkle almonds on top.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and shape into 15 (1-inch) balls. Broil until brown.
In a saucepan, combine tomato juice, chili powder and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Add the meatballs; cover and simmer gently for 20 minutes, stirring a few times.
Yields 5 servings.

title: imperial crab
directions: Flake crabmeat; mix with bread crumbs, mayonnaise and seasonings.
Fill buttered ramekins (seashell dish).
Cover with buttered crumbs and bake in preheated moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: punch
directions: Mix together and chill.
Just before serving, scoop pint of ice cream on top of punch.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In casserole dish, mix all ingredients together. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: sunrise slush
directions: Boil water and sugar.
Let cool.
Add orange juice, limeade, ReaLemon and vodka.
Put in freezer.

title: no-bake yummies
directions: Mix ingredients; roll into small balls.
Chill and eat. Serves 10 to 12 children.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix nuts and cherries.
Add pineapple, sour cream, sugar, lemon juice, salt and strawberries.
Add banana.
Freeze in glass loaf pan or something similar.
Slice as needed.
Keeps a long time.

title: sourdough bread starter
directions: In the morning, mix yeast and 1 cup warm water together.
Set aside until dissolved.
Add sugar and potato flakes; set aside until evening.
To make bread mix starter, add the 3 teaspoons sugar, 2 1/4 cups warm water, corn oil and bread flour.
Mix with starter; set aside overnight.
Knead dough and separate.
Put in 3 small pans, also keep enough for rolls.
Let set and rise all day. Bake in afternoon.

title: pink stuff salad
directions: Bring pineapple to a boil.
Add 1 small carton small curd cottage cheese and stir until dissolved.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook all until tender.
Add thickening: 1/4 cup flour and milk (more or less flour to desired thickness).

title: spinach casserole
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, mix spinach, soup, 1/2 package of dressing and melted Cheez Whiz. Sprinkle extra dressing on top and bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: baked cheesecake
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 5 minutes at 350°.
Beat the cream cheese, 3/4 cup sugar, eggs and 1 teaspoon vanilla together until well blended.
Pour over crust; bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Mix the sour cream, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla; spread on cake and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix together eggs and sugar.
Add oil and blend well.
Add to dry ingredients.
Pour pumpkin in and blend slowly.
Pour mixture into well-greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Ice or glaze as desired.

title: bundt pan rolls
directions: Generously grease a Bundt pan and sprinkle bottom of pan with 1/2 of the pecans.
Place rolls on top of nuts and sprinkle with rest of pecans.
Combine cinnamon and brown sugar with melted oleo.
Pour over rolls.
Let rise overnight at room temperature. In the morning, preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes. Remove from pan as soon as possible.
Invert on plate.

title: potato soup
directions: Heat potatoes, onion and 1 quart of milk in a soup pot. Work butter into flour, add egg and 1/4 cup cold milk. Mix well. Add this mixture slowly to hot mixture. Cover and simmer 10 - 20 minutes. Sprinkle with chopped parsley.

title: low country shrimp boil ("frogmore stew")
directions: Fill a large stockpot with water and bring to a rolling boil. Add salt, sausage, corn and seasoning; boil for 5 minutes.
Add shrimp and cook at a rolling boil for 5 minutes (no longer or shrimp will shrink and toughen!).
Remove from heat and drain off water.
Serve with soft margarine and/or seafood cocktail sauce. Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt peanut butter morsels, 1 cup milk and 2 tablespoons margarine.
Press into waxed paper-lined glass 8-inch square pan. Melt remaining margarine, milk and 1 cup chocolate morsels. Spread on top of peanut butter mixture.
Refrigerate for 2 hours and remove.
On cutting board, slice into tiny squares.

title: almond hershey bar
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk and cool.
Add crushed Hershey bars, Cool Whip and vanilla.
Mix graham crackers and melted butter.

title: macaroni, oil and garlic
directions: In a saucepan, carefully heat oil and garlic until garlic is browned (about 3 to 4 minutes).
Add a dash of black pepper.
Boil capellini as desired and drain.
Put capellini in bowl; stir in oil mixture as dressing.
Top with grated cheese.
Can add steamed rapini.
Can add Ricotta cheese.

title: lulu's pound cake(yield: 1 cake)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: sausage chowder
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Combine all ingredients, except sausage, and cook, covered, until potatoes are done.
Add sausage. Heat 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Remove bay leaf and serve.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and chill before serving.

title: homemade noodles
directions: In a bowl, combine egg, salt and milk. Add 1 cup flour. Mix until a stiff dough forms.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in microwave for about 10 minutes.
Drain.
Cut butter in cubes and add to broccoli.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Mix together sour cream and cream of celery soup; spread over the top of the broccoli mixture.
Sprinkle more Parmesan cheese over the top (as desired).
Cover with foil and bake in a preheated 425° oven for 1 hour or until lightly browned.

title: oven roasted potato slices
directions: Peel potatoes and cut into quarter-inch slices. Combine potatoes, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper in a Ziploc bag and shake until potatoes are coated. Arrange potatoes in a single layer on a baking sheet coated with cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until tender, turning once.

title: raisin oatmeal mix
directions: In a bowl, combine the first 7 ingredients.
Store in airtight container for up to 1 month.
Yield:
14 batches (about 7 cups total).

title: jean's dijon salad dressing
directions: Combine mustard and vinegars in blender.
Add everything except oil. Whirl until blended. With blender running, add oil, one tablespoon at a time.
Chill.
Serve on salad greens. Yields 1 1/4 cups.
Keeps several weeks.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook macaroni until tender; drain liquid off. Brown ground beef; season with salt, pepper and onions. Drain fat. Mix all other ingredients together, except cheese. Pour into 9 x 13 baking dish. Sprinkle with cheese to edge. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with salad and bread sticks for a complete meal.

title: will's southern style beans
directions: Use cured meat and cook until fully done.
Rinse in cold water. Add snap beans, onions and a little pepper (no salt).
Cook slowly until beans are done.
Add a little love and serve.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Pour into prepared 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Combine pineapple, butter, sugar and flour in saucepan.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Stir in coconut.
Spread over cake.

title: hearty chicken stew
directions: In a deep skillet or Dutch oven, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Saute onion and garlic until onion is soft, about 3 minutes.
Add flour and cook 1 minute, stirring quickly to prevent sticking.
Stir in tomatoes and allow to cook another 2 minutes. Wrap peppercorns, cloves and cinnamon in a small piece of cheesecloth.
Add chicken, cheesecloth package, water and Worcestershire sauce to onion mixture.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in mixing bowl.
Mix well. Add remaining ingredients except pecans.
Mix well.
Stir in pecans. Pour into shell. Bake in preheated oven at 375° to 400° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix all spices and dry salad dressing mix into the oil and stir well.
Place oyster crackers in large shallow pan.
Pour seasoned oil over crackers and stir well.
Continue to stir occasionally as crackers are baked at 250 degrees for one hour. Crackers will absorb oil.
Store in an air-tight container.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding nutmeats last.
Pour into pastry-lined plate.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and continue baking until a silver knife blade inserted in center of filling comes out clean.

title: tomato relish
directions: Cook all ingredients until tender; fill into sterilized jars. Seal tight.

title: apple popover pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs and sugar until thick; beat in vanilla and cinnamon.
Add flour and milk alternately, ending with flour.
Melt butter in an 8-inch square pan.
Put in apples and mix with butter until they sizzle.
Pour batter on top; sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: apple mold salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling apple juice.
Add 3 3/4 cups cold apple juice.
Chill until slightly jelled.

title: flank steak teriyaki
directions: Mix ingredients and pour over scored flank steak.
Marinade 4 hours or more.
Broil 4 minutes on each side or until done. Serve with rice and stir-fried vegetables.

title: andrea's special p. s. soup
directions: Fry the sausage, green pepper and onions.
Mix with soup and corn; heat. Enjoy with hot rolls and butter.

title: beer biscuits
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add beer.
Bake in muffin pans in 425° oven for 20 minutes.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Fold yogurt and fruit into whipped topping.
Blend and spoon into crust.
Freeze about 4 hours.
Remove from freezer about 30 minutes before serving.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fried corn meal mush
directions: Bring the water to a boil. Combine the corn meal, cold water, salt and sugar. Gradually add to boiling water. Cook until thick. Reduce heat, cover pan and cook 5 minutes.
Stir often.
Pour in loaf pan and cool.
Slice and fry until crisp.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake on cookie sheet 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: great ice cream dish
directions: Melt first 2 ingredients in frying pan.
Add the next 3 ingredients to frying pan.
Stir entire mixture constantly for 5 minutes.
Press half of the mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer in 1/2 gallon of vanilla ice cream, top with remaining mixture; freeze.
Serve with strawberry topping and whipped cream.

title: ruth's baked beans
directions: Mix all these ingredients together.
Put into a baking pan and put slices of bacon on top and bake in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: family best beef loaf
directions: Mix ground beef lightly with bread crumbs, onion, egg, chili sauce, salt and pepper until well blended. Shape into a loaf in shallow pan. Tuck a bay leaf under each end of loaf.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour or until brown. Discard bay leaves before serving.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix well crushed pretzels, margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool completely!

title: baked apple
directions: Core apple.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and pour 1/2 can of soda over apple.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Yields 1 serving.
Serving Size:
1 apple.
Exchange:
1 fruit.
Calories: 60.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Moisten bread cubes with the milk.
Cream sugar, butter and eggs.
Mix with other ingredients.
Put in casserole and bake for 1 hour.
Delicious!

title: chicken enchilada dip
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Let cool & shred.
Place in bowl and mix in cream cheese, mayo, cheddar cheese & green chili peppers.
Place in a baking dish and bake about 30 minutes or until the edges are golden brown.

title: crisp and chewy gingersnaps
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Mix together ingredients (butter, sugar, molasses and eggs). Cream mixture for 2 1/2 minutes. Stir in ingredients (flour, baking soda, salt and spices). Blend well. Roll dough in balls the size of walnuts; roll in sugar and place on greased cookie sheet. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes until cookies are barely set and just starting to brown on the edges. Remove from oven and let cool on cookie sheet for 3 to 5 minutes. Place cookies on paper towels to finish cooling, then enjoy!!

title: marinated shrimp kabobs
directions: Combine pineapple juice, Italian dressing, tomato sauce, sugar and mustard.
Mix well.
Add shrimp, tossing gently to coat. Cover and marinate 2 hours.
Using kabobs, alternate shrimp, green pepper and pineapple.
Grill over hot coals 3 to 4 minutes.

title: opal's sweet potato fluff
directions: Mix with electric mixer.
Beat potatoes until color starts to look lighter; add margarine, eggs, sugar, milk and orange juice. Whip this mixture until it is fluffy.
Fold in coconut and marshmallows.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle on topping and bake for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: dill dip for fresh vegetables
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.

title: sausage pie
directions: Cook sausage and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Saute peppers in oil.
Place in 3-quart casserole.
Add sausage and next
8 ingredients.
Combine bread crumbs and margarine.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: "old fashion rice custard with less fat"
directions: In double boiler with water in bottom pot, cook rice with 2 cups milk.
Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.
Cook until rice is tender and most of the milk evaporated.
Remove from heat; add Butter Buds.
Stir in beaten eggs, sugar, sweetener and vanilla; stir well into the cooked rice.
Add in the rest of the milk.
Pour in a well-sprayed 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until firm.

title: grandma's hungarian cheesecake
directions: Mix butter and graham crackers together and pat into the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In bowl, mash cottage cheese a little and then beat in milk, yolks, sugar, flour, vanilla and salt until smooth.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form a ball.
Roll in 1 cup pecans.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Bake pie crust at 450° for 10 minutes.
In bowl stir together eggs, milk, onion, salt, and pepper.
In skillet, fry bacon, drain, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings.
Cook onion in drippings until tender.
Add crumbled bacon and onion to egg mixture.
Toss together cheese and flour and add to egg mixture.
Pour into hot pastry shell.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: fresh fruit ice cream
directions: In ice cream freezer container, combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.

title: whipped fruit jello salad
directions: Drain the fruit and empty into a large bowl.
Set aside.
In another large bowl, mix the whipped cream and jello.
Stir thoroughly. Fold fruit into whipped cream and jello mixture. Chill.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix cider and cinnamon mix together. Heat and serve.

title: midnight madness cake
directions: Cooking time: 50 to 55 minutes.
Temperature: 350°.

title: easy creamy raspberry pie
directions: Drain yogurt in cheese cloth lined colander 4 to 6 hours or over night. Drain syrup from berries. Reserve berries. In small sauce pan sprinkle gelatin over syrup and let soften 1 minute. Stir over low heat just until gelatin is dissolved.
Place yogurt cheese in large bowl and whisk in gelatin. Fold in berries. Pour into crust and refrigerate until set.

title: taco bean soup
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Adjust with water so soup has desired consistency.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour. Serve hot.
Serves 12.

title: chinese vegetables
directions: Drain first 7 ingredients for 1 hour.
Add water chestnuts, celery, onion and bell pepper.
Bring remaining ingredients to a boil and pour over vegetable mixture.
Refrigerate 24 hours.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease the bottom of a 13x9x2 in. baking pan. Spread coconut and nuts evenly over the bottom. Prepare cake mix and spread over the coconut and nuts. Combine the melted butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar, beating until smooth. Pour over the cake batter. Bake at 350° for 45-55 minutes. Top of cake will crinkle.

title: caramel corn
directions: Melt margarine; stir in brown sugar, syrup and salt.
Bring to boil. Boil for 5 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat and stir in baking soda and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn.
Put in buttered pan and bake at 300° for 30 minutes, stirring after 15 minutes.
Remove and loosen to eat.

title: carrot cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars together.
Add vanilla.
Add cooked carrots that have been mashed and cooled.
Sift flour.
Measure and add salt and baking powder.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cut powdered sugar into peanut butter with pastry cutter (or fork).
Stir in egg yolks, vanilla and milk with beaters.
Add in flour, salt and butter.
Mix well.
(Add milk if too stiff until mixture looks smooth and spreadable.)
Pour mixture into prepared pie shell and bake at 300° until filling rises and top begins to "brown."

title: meat, onion and potato bake
directions: In a bowl, mix beef, egg, bread crumbs, garlic, sauce, milk and salt to taste.
Set aside.
Arrange potatoes in greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Pat meat mixture over potatoes.
Separate onion rings over meat.
Bake, covered, in 400° oven for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.
Let rest, covered, 10 minutes before serving.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pudding.
Add pineapple, pecans, Jell-O and marshmallows.
Blend well and put in dish.
Chill.

title: wild rice and pepper salad
directions: Prepare rice as directed on package.
Mix salad dressing, oil, pepper and lemon peel.
Add remaining ingredients and lightly mix.

title: rum cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl, cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat to light and fluffy.
Add sifted mixture alternately with rum, beating smooth after each addition.
Chill dough for 1 hour.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain water from artichokes (squish with hands to get all water out).
Chop artichoke hearts; mix hearts with mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven, uncovered; top should brown.
Drain oil as it bakes.
Serve warm with Fritos or Triscuits.
